title: american chop suey
directions: Brown hamburger, celery and onions.
Add other ingredients. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
The last 10 minutes, cover with Chinese noodles.

title: sweet and sour cooked cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw frozen spinach and squeeze dry.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and soup mix until well blended.
Stir in spinach, chestnuts and onions.
Cover and chill 2 hours before serving. Serve with crackers, Melba toast and/or chips.

title: cooked salad dressing(for potatoes or macaroni)
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Gradually add eggs, vinegar and water. Cook until thick.
Add butter and celery seed.
Put on salad hot. Let cool and refrigerate salad.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil 6 chicken breasts; debone chicken and cut into bite size pieces.
Mix chicken, sour cream and can of cream of chicken soup. Put mixture into casserole dish.
Put broken Ritz crackers on top of mixture.
Melt oleo and pour over crackers.
Top with 1 or 2 tablespoons of poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: meringues
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg whites with salt until stiff, then beat in sugar gradually.
Add vanilla.
Remove from beater and add chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Place in oven and turn off heat.
Leave in oven overnight (do not peak!).
Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: salad delight
directions: Mix and whip everything together.
Let set for several hours before serving.

title: diet hamburger casserole
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add rinsed sauerkraut, salt and pepper.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Bake until dry.

title: kielbasa with kraut
directions: In a Dutch oven cook onion, bacon until onion is tender but not brown. Drain off fat. Stir in beer. In a 2 c. glass measure water, cornstarch, brown mustard, molasses, caraway seed, allspice, and pepper. Stir in bacon mixture. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Add rutabaga; cover and cook for 15 minutes. Stir in Kielbasa, apples and kraut.

title: missouri cookies
directions: Boil together sugar, cocoa and milk for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, salt, peanut butter, quick oats and butter.
Mix well.
Drop on wax paper; let cool.
Do not dabble.

title: five flavor cake
directions: Cream oleo, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately the flour mixture and milk.
Add flavorings.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Bake in
Bundt pan.

title: frank's fantastic hawaiian fruit salad
directions: Drain all the juice out of both cans of cocktail and oranges. In a large bowl combine these two followed by the sour cream.
You can add the coconut with as much as you like.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions with margarine in skillet until browned.
Add next 5 ingredients; blend well.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Place 1 slice of French bread in a bowl.
Add soup.
Sprinkle with cheese. Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: turkey parmigiana
directions: Combine crumbs and 2 tablespoons cheese.
Dip cutlets in milk and dredge in crumb mixture.
Heat nonstick skillet to medium-high.
Add 1 teaspoon oil and cook cutlets about 3 minutes on each side, adding up to 1 more teaspoon oil, if necessary. Remove cutlets to warm platter.
Heat tomato sauce and seasonings. Pour over cutlets.
Sprinkle with remaining 1 tablespoon cheese and serve on a bed of noodles.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Cream butter and sugar at high speed with mixer. Add eggs, one at a time, and continue to cream. Put mixer on low speed and add crushed pineapple. Fold in by hand 1-quart bread cubes.
Bake in foil-lined pan or dish for 1 hour at 375°.

title: quick french bread
directions: Mix 2 cups flour, sugar, yeast and salt in a large bowl.
Add hot tap water gradually, beating on low speed for 2 minutes.
Add margarine and 2 cups flour, beating for 2 minutes on medium speed. Mix in 2 1/2 to 3 cups flour on medium speed to make a soft dough. Mix well from the bottom of the bowl with a spoon.
Cover, let rise for 45 minutes in a warm place, or until double in bulk.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all together.
Put into 2 bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in large casserole dish.
Add onion soup, mushrooms, water and rice.
Stir until mixed.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Slice cabbages thin and cut up in big pieces.
Slice onions and bell pepper thin.
Add pepper and a very small amount of salt. Pour Italian dressing over mixture and let set in refrigerator several hours before serving.
Can use fat free dressing.
Good with barbecue or hamburgers.

title: dishpan soup
directions: Simmer first 3 ingredients for 1 hour.
Then add the rest of the ingredients, except for spaghetti.
When vegetables are done, add chopped spaghetti, if desired.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350. Saute sausage and drain, save drippings. Saute mushrooms and onions in sausage drippings in black skillet. When mushrooms and onions are cooked put sausage in the black skillet.

title: pineapple cream cake
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 12-inch pan for 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix cream cheese and 1/2 cup cold milk until smooth.
Then add instant pudding and 2 cups cold milk; mix until smooth and thick.
Spread over cooled cake.
Spread crushed pineapple on pudding, then spread Cool Whip and sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: split second pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and mix.
Add flour and flavoring.
Mix and pour into greased tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Thoroughly mix pineapple tidbits (well drained), thawed Cool Whip, flaked coconut, miniature marshmallows, chopped maraschino cherries and milk.
Chill about 1 hour.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: chicken parmesan italiano(makes 2 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Line cookie sheet with foil; spray foil with nonstick cooking spray. In shallow dish, combine bread crumbs, cheese and oregano; mix well. In small cup or bowl, combine lemon juice and garlic. Brush both sides of chicken with lemon juice mixture. Coat with bread crumb mixture. Place on sprayed foil-lined cookie sheet. Lightly spray chicken with cooking spray. Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender and juices run clear.

title: nifty nachos
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spread tortillas in single layer in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan or 12 inch pizza pan.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over chips.
Bake for 2 to 3 minutes, until cheese melts.
Dip chips in salsa.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat milk and pudding mix; blend in whipped topping and sweetened condensed milk.
Alternate wafers, bananas and pudding mixture in large dish, ending with pudding mixture on top.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Fry bacon; remove from skillet.
Crumble when cool.
Mix vinegar with brown sugar; add salt and pepper to taste.
Add to bacon grease.
Tear washed garden lettuce; add chopped onion and radishes, if desired.
Get grease dressing nice and hot, then pour over lettuce.
Add bacon bits; mix and serve immediately.

title: pie crust (never fail)
directions: Cut together shortening, flour, sugar and salt.
Add beaten egg, water and vinegar.
Mix all together, but add a little at a time for good consistency.
Will keep a week in refrigerator in airtight container.
Makes 4 crusts.

title: cheese grits casserole
directions: In a saucepan, cook 1 cup of grits per package directions. While the grits are cooking, melt the butter in another pan and add the garlic cheese, blending until all is melted.
Beat the eggs; add milk and blend.
Add the egg mixture to the melted butter and cheese, blending until smooth.
Add the cheese sauce mixture to the grits and pour into a buttered casserole.

title: chicken tortilla soup
directions: Boil chicken; save broth.
Skim grease and discard.
Combine chicken meat, broth, cilantro, potatoes, carrots, onions and celery and boil.
When nearly done, add remainder of ingredients (except cheese and chips).
Put tortillas in bowl; add soup and top with cheese.

title: cheese ball or rolls
directions: Mix cheeses and garlic powder together after cheeses have softened.
Roll into a ball or 3 rolls and roll into pecans.
Wrap and chill until ready to serve.
This is better made 24 hours ahead.

title: veal and mushrooms
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Roll veal cubes in flour and sear on all sides.
Will probably have to work in batches.
When seared, put veal in 6-quart casserole alternately with raw mushrooms and butter from skillet.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Serve with rice or couscous.
Serves 16.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients until creamy on low speed. Mix all dry ingredients together. Add to creamed mixture until well blended. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, wash in cold water and drain well.

title: cream cheese cake(italian)
directions: Beat egg whites and set aside. Cream the butter or oleo and shortening. Add sugar and beat until smooth. Add egg yolks. Combine flour and soda.

Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk, starting with flour and ending with flour. Stir in vanilla, coconut and pecans. Fold in egg whites. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Check at 35 minutes.
Makes 3 round 9-inch layers.

title: jewish honey bread
directions: Beat together honey, oleo (melted and cooled), 2 eggs, 1/2 cup milk and 2 tablespoons lemon juice.
Add flour, soda, salt and cloves.
Fold in the cup of chopped walnuts and 2/3 cup candied orange peel.
Pour into well-greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake approximately 1 hour at 325° or until done when tested.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove and cool completely. Wrap when cool and store at room temperature.

title: snowball cake
directions: Mix gelatine with boiling water; add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple.
Let stand in refrigerator until firming begins.
Beat 2 packages Dream Whip; fold into mixture.

title: squash casserole
directions: Steam squash; place in casserole 1 layer of squash, slices of Velveeta cheese to cover squash and layer of crackers; continue with another layer of squash, cheese and crackers. Melt margarine in microwave. Pour over dish and bake at 350° until brown, about 20 to 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8. Can do ahead.

title: different tuna
directions: Slice or quarter tomatoes.
Combine all the rest of the ingredients.
Toss slightly but well.
Embed the tomatoes into the tuna.
Serve on Ritz crackers.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Combine carrots, peppers, onion, sugar and garlic salt; mix well.
Add vinegar and olive oil; let stand overnight.
Serve as a salad or a vegetable.

title: tomato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, using the amount of hot pepper according to taste. Chill and serve.
Serves 2.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine the chicken broth, chicken, butter, garlic and pepper.
Bring the mixture to a boil; lower the heat and simmer for 1 minute.
In a mixing bowl, combine the flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend in the vegetable shortening until the mixture is coarse and mealy.
Stir in just enough ice water to make a light dough.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles as directed; brown beef, add garlic, oregano, tomato paste, water, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
In an oblong baking dish, place 3 noodles, 4 slices of Swiss cheese, 1/2 of cottage cheese and 1/2 beef sauce.
Make second layer like first.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pizza breakfast
directions: Spread crescent rolls in pizza pan to form crust.
Brown sausages; cut into bite size pieces.
Sprinkle sausage on dough, then spread hash browns and cheese on top.
Beat eggs and milk; pour over other ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Pat hamburger in 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Layer the remaining ingredients, do not mix.
Bake in oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pineanna nut cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 3 round cake pans.
Mix flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon in a large bowl. Add oil and eggs.
Stir until all dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat!
Stir in bananas, 1 cup pecans, vanilla and pineapple. Divide batter evenly among pans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pans and cool completely on wire racks. Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: mincemeat cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add beaten eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with 1/2 cup buttermilk.
Add the mincemeat and the nuts.
Bake in 2 layers in a 375° oven.
Frost with Caramel Frosting.

title: red velvet cake and icing
directions: Mix color and cocoa together.
Set aside.
Cream Crisco and sugar until light.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add cocoa mixture to Crisco mix and beat until creamy.
Add buttermilk and flour alternately to cake mixture.
Mix well after adding salt and vanilla, then add vinegar and baking soda.
Mix by hand.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: congealed salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in one of boiling water.
Then add lime jello.
Stir until cool, then pour over the remaining mixture.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Stir well and serve.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake at once or store in covered bowl for later use.

title: cheese pizza
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread and mushrooms.
Mix thoroughly into a paste.
Spread paste on each slice of French bread.
Place slices on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes or until bacon is well cooked.
Mushrooms may be placed on top, if desired.

title: cherry surprise balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except wax and chocolate chips.
Chill. Roll into small balls.
Place on wax paper and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add cut strawberries.
Put in a baked pie shell.
Add topping of Cool Whip or whipped cream.
Garnish with sliced strawberries.

title: scalloped barbecue potatoes
directions: Pare potatoes, slice thinly and sprinkle with flour.
Combine water, barbecue sauce, vinegar and salt in Dutch oven and heat to boiling.
Stir in floured potatoes and onion.
Simmer 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley.
Baking time: 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: maggie's foiled roast
directions: Place roast in foil lined baking pan.
Sprinkle soup mix over roast.
Add 1-inch of water around roast.
Bake at 300° in oven for 3 or 4 hours.
When roast is near done, add onions, potatoes and carrots around roast and cook until vegetables are done.

title: quail in grape leaves
directions: Season quail with salt and pepper.
Wrap each, first in a strip of bacon and then in a grape leaf and tie with thread.
Put in Dutch oven or large covered saucepan in hot oil.
Add wine and a little water until the quail are half immersed in liquid.
Stew until the quail are tender; undo the string.

title: oven shoyu chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Bake in aluminum foil lined pan at 325° for one hour, turning twice.

title: skillet taco
directions: Brown ground beef with garlic in skillet, stirring until ground beef is crumbly; drain.
Add green chili pepper, tomatoes, chili con carne and beans.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir in half and half.
Sprinkle with shredded lettuce, corn chips and cheese. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 9-inch square pan with whip, mix well the flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add carrots, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Mix until blended.
Stir in pineapple, coconut and walnuts.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Double recipe for large cake pan.

title: spiced apple tea
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine juices, honey, cinnamon and cloves.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add tea bags; strain and serve.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Put crushed pineapple and orange jello in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Cool.
Mix in Cool Whip, buttermilk and nuts. Refrigerate.

title: peeled baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Peel potatoes; remove any blemishes. Rub entire potato with butter/margarine, then roll in flour, coating potato completely.
Place in shallow pan and bake in a 450° oven for 40 to 50 minutes or until soft.

title: fruit punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in 1 quart boiling water. Add the cool water and pineapple juice. Store in refrigerator.

title: jogging in a jug
directions: Two to four ounces daily is said to help to maintain good health and energy.
Also said to help reduce weight.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Melt margarine; cook onions and celery until clear.
Mix all ingredients in a casserole dish. Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion (do not season this); drain fat.
Pour Doritos in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread beef on Doritos; set aside. In saucepan mix and heat to boiling soups and taco sauce.
Pour this over beef.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
You can refrigerate this overnight and bake next day or divide into 2 (8 x 8-inch) pans.
Bake one and freeze one for later.
Serve with salad and hot bread.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, and evaporated milk in heavy saucepan; bring to full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate chips until melted add marshmallow creme, nuts and vanilla extract; beat until well blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 baking pan.
Cool at room temperature; cut into squares. Makes 3 pounds.

title: hot sausage and cheese puffs
directions: Gently fry the sausage.
With slotted spoon, remove to a bowl and cool completely.
Add the cheese, baking mix and water.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place on baking sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes until puffed and browned.

title: rum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube or 12-cup (large) Bundt pan.
Sprinkle nuts over bottom of pan.
Mix cake ingredients together. Pour batter over nuts.
Bake 1 hour.
Cool. Invert on serving plate.
Prick top.
Spoon and brush glaze evenly over top and sides.
Allow cake to absorb glaze.
Repeat until glaze is used up.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix together pudding (can use sugar-free) and pineapple, then add in other ingredients and chill overnight.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine.
Use 1/3 cup mix to 1 cup hot water.

title: fudgy mocha nut pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan over low heat, melt butter.
Add cocoa; stir until smooth.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk, water, eggs, instant coffee and chocolate chips; whisk until well blended.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake for 50 minutes, or until center is set.
Cool completely.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: vegetable meat balls
directions: Grind the potatoes, carrots and onion or use food processor. Mix all ingredients together.
Form in large balls, firmly packed. I use my ice cream scoop to make balls uniform.
Fry nice and brown in limited amount of Crisco.
Pack in deep baking dish. Cover with tomato juice and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: dandy candied yams
directions: Place butter in saucepan under low flame.
Add 1/4 teaspoon of lemon and 1/4 teaspoon of orange juice.
Add other ingredients and stir well until smooth consistency.
Slice yams and place in baking pan.
Pour mixture over yams and let sit for 3 minutes.
Place yams in preheated oven (350°) until bubbling brown on top, approximately 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 5 people.

title: meal in one casserole
directions: Put raw ground beef in casserole; season with seasoned salt and pepper.
Add package of frozen vegetables.
Spread the mushroom soup over the vegetables.
Cover with Tater Tots.
Lay foil on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake another 30 minutes.

title: golden almond bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine cake mix and butter at low speed until crumbly.
Reserve 1/2 cup crumbs for topping.
Press remaining crumbs into bottom of prepared pan.

title: quick and easy chicken-vegetable soup
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add carrots and cook 10 minutes.
Add celery and cook 10 minutes.
Add chicken, onion and potatoes. Continue to boil.
Add noodles, bouillon cube, salt and spices to taste. Cover and simmer about 20 minutes.
Serve with saltine crackers.

title: taco casserole
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam. Press the crescent rolls on the bottom of the pan and bake until done.
Layer half of each ingredient as follows:
taco meat, sour cream, cheese, salsa and chips. Repeat layer. Cook at 375° for 15 minutes. When it comes out of the oven, top with shredded lettuce and diced tomatoes. Cut into squares.

title: fluffy fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1 cup juice in a small saucepan; set pineapple aside.
In saucepan, add sugar, flour, eggs, orange juice, lemon juice and oil.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil for 1 minute or until thickened; remove from heat and let cool in a bowl.
Combine pineapple, fruit cocktail, oranges and bananas. Fold in Cool Whip and chill.

title: guacamole
directions: Put lemon juice over avocados, stirring until all avocados are covered.
Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly and chill before serving.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent roll dough in pan, smoothing out all seams. Bake according to directions until browned.

title: chocolate chip peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.
Do not bake longer.
Let set and cool.
Remove from pan.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix together and pour evenly over first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until tests done with knife.
Let set until firm.

title: quick italian meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
In a large baking pan, shape into loaf.
Bake 1 hour or until done.
Makes 8 servings.

title: ginger-lime swordfish
directions: Spray frying pan with 3 squirts of lite oil.
Saute swordfish 3 minutes on each side over low heat.
Chop garlic, basil and ginger in bowl.
Add lime juice and pine nuts.
Transfer fish to microwave dish.
Pour mix over fish and microwave for 3 minutes or until thoroughly cooked.
Garnish and serve.

title: cappuccino cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Blend in cappuccino, cinnamon and salt. Mix in flour and nuts.
Mold into 1 inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes until cookies are just set.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking powder and salt.
Beat butter until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in sugars.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture until well blended.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets, placing cookies about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: lemon glaze cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix all ingredients together.
Mix and beat at high speed for 4 minutes.
Pour into oiled and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes; cool and remove from pan. While cake is still warm, glaze with icing.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Bring soup to boil.
Soften gelatin in water and add to soup. Beat cheese
with
soup
mixture.
When
cool,
fold in celery, onion, shrimp and mayonnaise.
Put in mold and chill.

title: scalloped tomatoes and artichoke hearts
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a shallow earthenware or other casserole.
Drain the tomatoes and artichokes.
Combine tomatoes, artichokes and basil and heat for 2 or 3 minutes, stirring gently. Season with the sugar, salt and pepper.
Turn into the prepared casserole and bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes or until the vegetables are heated through.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add butter and sugar, then milk and chopped nuts. Pour into deep crust.
Bake at 325° until set.

title: chew bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in 8 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Slice cucumbers, onion and bell pepper.
Mix with the salt and celery seed.
Let sit for 1 hour.
Heat the lemon juice and sugar until sugar has dissolved.
Pour over mixture.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: great oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together sugars and Crisco.
Add eggs.
Add flour, soda, salt and vanilla.
Mix in oatmeal.
Roll dough in wax paper. Chill in freezer.
When ready to bake, slice and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 11 to 12 minutes.
Great stored in tin for gift.
Cookies are crunchy.

title: cream filling for cupcakes
directions: Cook together flour and milk, stirring constantly as it thickens.
Cool.
Mix at high speed the Crisco, oleo and sugar for 5 minutes.
Add vanilla and then add to the first mixture. Continue to beat until creamy.

title: easy friendship cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute the onion, water chestnuts and bell pepper in the margarine.
Mix all ingredients together and put in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Bake, uncovered, 25 to 30 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle top of casserole during the last 5 or 10 minutes with grated cheese.
Bake until just melted or slightly browned.

title: popcorn crisp
directions: Pop popcorn and put in a large kettle in a moderate oven, 300°.
Bring to boil white sugar, brown sugar, glucose and water; wash sides down and add salt.
Cook to 300° and add butter.
When butter is well mixed in, take off the fire and add soda.
Mix with vanilla.
Stir in well.
Take the corn out of oven.
Set on warm part of stove.
Scrape all the syrup into the corn and mix the whole thing together.
Pour on a cold dry slab or wax paper. Spread out while hot.
This can be rolled into balls.
When cool, break into a size you wish.
A great caramel corn.
Store in airtight container to prevent corn from getting sticky.

title: raised doughnuts
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large mixer bowl.
Add milk, 1/2 cup sugar, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon, eggs, shortening and 2 cups of flour.
Beat on low speed 30 seconds.
Beat on medium speed 2 minutes.
Stir in remaining flour; continue stirring until smooth. Cover; let rise in warm place until double, 50 to 60 minutes. Turn dough onto well-floured board.
Roll to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into 2 1/2-inch doughnuts.
Cover; let rise until double, about 20 minutes.
Heat oil and deep fry until golden brown.
Drain; while warm roll doughnuts in sugar or spread with glaze.

title: grandma church's wonderful fudge
directions: Stir together in a large heavy pot or Dutch oven, over moderate heat, the butter, canned milk and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Cover. Boil 5 minutes and turn off heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Add the chocolate, one kind at a time, stirring as it melts.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Blend.
Pour into a buttered 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan and smooth evenly. Let stand until firm, then cut into 1-inch squares.

title: gotzbki(stuffed cabbage)
directions: Remove core from cabbage.
Place whole head in a large pot filled with boiling salted water.
Cover; cook 3 minutes or until softened enough to pull off individual leaves.
Repeat to remove all large leaves (about 30).
Cut thick center stem from each leaf.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Make a syrup of the vinegar and sugar.
Place this in a kettle with a spice bag containing the whole cloves and stick cinnamon. Pare and halve the peaches, leaving an occasional stone for flavor.
Peaches may be left whole.
Cook the peaches in the syrup until tender, then place in jars.
Fill jars with the vinegar syrup and seal.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and salt.
Gradually add milk.
Cook to a soft ball stage (small amount of mixture dropped in a cup of cold water will form a soft ball).
Add butter and vanilla.
Let cool, then beat on a marble slab.

title: frank's chuck roast
directions: Brown chuck roast on both sides in oil in a heavy pot.
Add light salt to taste, Dale sauce, celery, onion and green pepper. Cook on low 2 hours covered.
The last 30 minutes of cooking, add 1 cup large mushrooms.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Sprinkle 3 tablespoons sugar over crushed pretzels which have been spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together.
Pour melted margarine evenly over pretzel mixture and pat lightly into pan. Bake at 400° for 7 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs in a large bowl. Sift dry ingredients. Add and blend. Stir in vanilla, apples and pecans.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 3-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: gourmet chicken
directions: Mix soup, sour cream and wine.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: mom's cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine margarine, sugar, eggs, vanilla and almond extract. Beat until creamy. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. For best flavor, allow dough to sit covered on counter for a couple of hours. Roll out on floured surface. Cut out with favorite cutters or inverted top of glass or small bowl. Spray cookie sheets with nonstick spray. Bake 6 to 10 minutes, depending on thickness. Frost with icing.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Lightly salt chicken breasts on both sides.
Boil in water to cover until tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Chop into small pieces.
In a mixing bowl, combine soup, sour cream and 2 teaspoons poppy seed. Mix well, then set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish and layer half the soup mixture in the bottom.
Cover with chopped chicken, then top with remainder of soup mixture.
Combine the crushed crackers, 2 teaspoons poppy seed and margarine and mix well.
Spread over top of chicken mixture.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: coconut icing
directions: Cook sugar and milk together until it changes color from white to oyster white.
Remove from heat and add butter, mix, then add vanilla, mix well.
Stir in fresh or defrosted coconut.
Cool to luke-warm and put between layers and on sides and top of cake.

title: brownies
directions: Blend melted butter, sugar and vanilla in bowl. Add eggs; beat well with spoon. Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt. Gradually add to egg mixture until well blended.
Spread in greased pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool.

title: beef strips with vermicelli
directions: Partially freeze meat.
Trim fat from meat.
Thinly slice meat across the grain into bite size strips.
Cook pasta.
Drain; keep warm.

title: herb roasted chicken
directions: Combine flour and garlic powder in plastic bag.
Coat chicken with flour mixture.
Melt margarine in skillet.
On medium heat, fry chicken until done.
Combine chicken, celery and onion soups and milk.
Pour over chicken and let simmer in skillet for 10 to 15 minutes or until sauce is heated thoroughly.
Serve over white rice.

title: zell's chicken pot pie
directions: Boil hen until tender.
Remove meat from bone and cut into small pieces.
Melt butter in ovenware pan.
Add onion and celery. Cook very slowly for 15 minutes.
Add can of peas and carrots; blend broth and flour.
Add broth mixture, chicken and salt and pepper to taste.
Top with biscuits and bake at 425° until brown. If desired, add 1/2 cup chopped bell pepper or 1 can mushrooms as onion and celery cook.

title: red hot vegetarian chili
directions: Saute the onion, zucchini, garlic and red peppers.
Add spices, tomatoes and parsley.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Add kidney beans and dill.
Cook an additional 15 minutes.
Salt to taste. Serve in bowls topped with grated cheese or sour cream.

title: chinese chews
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, salt and vanilla.
Add sifted flour and baking powder.
Fold in dates and pecans.
Spread in 8 x 8 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° until done, approximately 25 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: homemade german butterhours
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, shortening, milk and dissolved yeast. Blend thoroughly.
Beat in flour.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.
Next morning, roll out using 1/4 of the dough at a time. Spread with melted butter.
Add chopped pecans or walnuts if desired.
Roll into horns and place on greased
baking sheet.
Let rise until double in warm place - (about an hour).
Bake 400° for 20 minutes until golden brown.
Spread with butter frosting.

title: veal with sherry and mushrooms
directions: Combine flour, nutmeg and salt.
Dredge veal in flour mixture and brown in hot butter.
Add broth, wine, onions and mushrooms. Cover and simmer until meat is tender (1 hour).
Just before serving, sprinkle with the parsley.
Serve over hot cooked rice (use half wild and half domestic rice).
Serves 4.

title: chicken breasts with angel hair pasta
directions: In small bowl, whisk together salad dressing and mustard; set aside.
In medium skillet, saute chicken in butter until browned; transfer to dish and keep warm.

title: easy raspberry pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a pan and add boiling water. Return to heat and bring mixture to a rolling boil for 1 minute. Cool.
Pour over raspberries.
Mix and put in pie crusts.
Chill all day, top with Cool Whip and serve.

title: peanut butter cups(balls)
directions: Cream margarine and peanut butter.
Add sugar until the consistency to form into balls the size of large marbles.
Add vanilla.
Mix thoroughly, using hands.
Melt chocolate and paraffin in small double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate, using a toothpick.
Place on waxed paper to cool.

title: hawaiian sweet bread
directions: Scald milk; add sugar, butter and salt.
Cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in water.
Add beaten eggs to yeast.
Then add milk mixture.
Beat in 2 cups flour.
Add enough remaining flour to make a smooth dough that doesn't stick to hands.
Cover with damp dish towel and let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Divide into 2 parts and shape into round loaves.
Place on greased sheet and let rise another 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until doubled.
Brush with beaten egg yolk and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Brush with butter.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Pour hot water over and boil slowly until thick.
Cool.
Place one layer of filling in shell, one layer of whole strawberries, then another layer of filling.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: no bake banana split cake
directions: Mix 1/2 cup melted margarine with 2 cups crushed vanilla wafers and spread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Beat the eggs, powdered sugar and 1 cup softened margarine for not less than 10 minutes.
Pour this mixture over the wafer crust. Slice the bananas evenly over the creamed mixture.
Spread the drained crushed pineapple over the bananas. Spread Cool Whip over the pineapple.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and dot with maraschino cherries.

title: cranberry goodin puddin
directions: Grease 8-inch pie pan.
Spread cranberries over bottom. Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar and nuts over cranberries.
Beat egg.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and beat.
Add flour, butter and shortening to egg and sugar mixture.
Beat.
Pour batter over cranberries.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: sweet potato casserole *
directions: Combine ingredients and place in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all together in mixing bowl and put in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In
very
large
pan,
melt
butter;
add 1 cup chicken broth. Add
onion and celery and cook until tender. Add soups and
Cheez Whiz;
simmer
and
stir until well blended.
Cook broccoli
and drain.
In a covered skillet melt 3 tablespoons butter;
add other
cup	of chicken broth.
Add rice and cook until
rice
is tender.
Add to soup, vegetable and Cheez Whiz mixture.
Blend well; add broccoli. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: ritz pecan pie
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Fold in egg whites. Pour into greased pie pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Slice pie and use whipped cream or Cool Whip for topping, if desired.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar and eggs.
Add oil.
Add rest of ingredients. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 375°.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Mix eggs, mayonnaise, milk, onion, salt and mushrooms.
Add hamburger and mix.
Slowly add cheese.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Increase temperature to 350° for 35 minutes.
Let them cool for 15 minutes before cutting them.
Can be frozen for later use.
Makes 2 quiches.

title: garlic chicken
directions: Mix melted margarine with garlic powder or salt.
Dip chicken in margarine mixture then roll in crumbs.
Place on large foil covered cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: cocoa creme pie
directions: Mix cocoa, cornstarch, egg yolks, salt and milk.
Cook until thick.
Stir constantly.
Add vanilla and pour into a baked pie crust.
Cover with meringue, made by beating the egg whites and adding sugar.
Brown pie.

title: "rock'n h barbecue beef sandwich"
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 1-quart ovenproof casserole. Cover.

title: antipasto turkey salad
directions: If using mostaccioli, cook and cool. Drain and slice artichoke hearts.
Lightly mix all ingredients except dressing.
Sprinkle with freshly ground pepper.
Mix half (or to taste) of the artichoke marinade with Italian dressing and pour over salad. Chill 2 to 4 hours if possible.
Serve on a bed of torn lettuce. Serves 4 to 6.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Simmer sauce for 20 minutes.
Add the cooked meat to it.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes in 1/4-inch slices.
Beat egg in bowl.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
Mix flour, meal or cracker crumbs and 1/2 teaspoon salt in second bowl.
Turn tomato slices over in egg mix, then in the flour mix.
Pan-fry in 1 cup vegetable oil at 350°. Brown on both sides.
Drain excess fat on paper towel.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix and soak 2 hours or overnight.
Fry in oil.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onions and pepper in margarine.
Fold corn into beaten eggs.
Add Jiffy mix to egg mixture, then add onions and peppers. Put into a well greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread with sour cream and cheese; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes. After removing from oven, cover for a few minutes before serving.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix together the flour and sugar.
Then beat the yolks slightly and add flour, sugar, butter and small can crushed pineapple.
Cook until thickened and pour into a baked pie shell. Top with your favorite meringue made from the reserved egg whites.

title: quick gingerbread
directions: Beat shortening, sugar and egg together.
Mix 1 tablespoon water with soda.
Add soda mixture, molasses, flour, salt and spices to first mixture.
Add hot water and mix.
Pour into square pan, greased, and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: parmesan oven fries
directions: Cut each potato lengthwise into 6 wedges.
Pat wedges dry with a paper towel and place in a bowl.
Add thyme and pepper; toss well.
Drizzle oil over wedges, tossing well to coat.
Arrange in a single layer on a baking sheet coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese and salt evenly over wedges. Bake an additional 10 minutes or until tender and brown.

title: eagle brand fruit cake
directions: Mix brown sugar, spices and cocoa in a small bowl.
In a large bowl, mix graham cracker crumbs and milk.
Add fruits, nuts and sugar-spice mixture.
Mix well.
Put into a tube cake pan lined with waxed paper.
Pack it down real good; put waxed paper on top of pan.
Wrap in foil, pan and all.
Put in refrigerator and let set 1 1/2 months.
This is real good for Christmas.

title: deep-dish apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place apples in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
In a small bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon; set aside 1 teaspoon of the mixture.
Stir cornstarch and salt into the remaining mixture and mix well.
Sprinkle evenly over apples in dish.
In a medium mixing bowl, stir together flour and nutmeg. Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon water over part of the mixture; gently toss with a fork.
Push to side of bowl.
Repeat until all is moistened.
Form into a ball.

title: lemon loaf
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add egg; combine vanilla, lemon extract and milk.
Add alternately with dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° in greased and floured loaf pan for 30 to 40 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes and remove from pan.
As soon as taken from oven and before removing from pan, top with 1/2 cup powdered sugar and 2 tablespoons milk, which have been stirred and heated together.

title: quick italian cream cake
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients. Stir in coconut and pecans. Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes. Cool in pans on wire racks 10 minutes Remove from pans and cool completely on wire racks. Spread cream cheese frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake.

title: faye reed's hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Top with slivered almonds and paprika.
Bake 30 minutes at 300° to 350°.

title: sweet-sour cabbage salad
directions: Place layers of cabbage and onion in large bowl; top with 1 cup sugar.
Set aside.

title: fancy hominy casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Cover and bake in greased casserole dish 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Add 1 cup grated cheese and bake 5 minutes more.

title: blue cheese walnut bites
directions: Use pastry cutter to cut Blue cheese and butter into flour; add slightly beaten egg yolks.
Stir.
Make a ball and knead. Divide in half and for each into a log (9-inches) long.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix all ingredients in a medium-sized mixing bowl.
Place in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours or until mixture hardens into a gel. Sprinkle on pecans (if desired).
Serve.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Cook zucchini and onion in boiling water until just tender; drain.
Add spices, cheese and eggs.
Spread crescent rolls in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Spread with mustard.
Pour vegetable mixture into the crust.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes, covering with foil the last 10 minutes.

title: applesauce honey cake
directions: Combine first 13 ingredients in large mixer bowl.
Beat together on low speed of mixer until combined, then on medium speed, scraping sides and bottom of bowl with rubber spatula.
Pour hot water over 1 cup raisins; let set about 15 minutes.
Drain and lay on paper towels to absorb excess water.
Stir raisins and 1 cup chopped walnuts into batter.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured baking pan.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: skillet stuffing
directions: In a bowl, combine the first 4 ingredients. Set aside. In a skillet, saute celery and onion in butter until tender. Add the cornbread mixture and seasonings. Mix well. Cook over medium heat until lightly browned. Yield: 2 servings.

title: pineapple sherbet
directions: Combine juice, sugar and cherries.
Beat until sugar is dissolved, then add milk (never add juice to milk or it will curdle) to combination, beating slowly.
Freeze.
When frozen, cut in pieces and beat in mixer until smooth and no chunks left. Return to freezer until ready to serve.

title: cheese logs for christmastime
directions: Fry the sausage until done; drain, then add all the cheese and the drained Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Heat all together.
(May add more chilies or jalapenos.)
Pour into a large pan to chill and then cut into logs.
Delicious.

title: lasagna romano
directions: Set out cottage cheese; drain and let stand at room temperature for 20 minutes.
Cook lasagna according to package directions.
Drain well and set aside.
Brown ground beef in a skillet.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add tomato sauce or tomatoes, water, sauce mix, salt and pepper.
Put a layer of sauce over meat; spoon in thin layer cottage cheese cheese, layer of lasagna and remaining layers of each.
Sprinkle with grated Romano or Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in a 325° oven for 20 minutes or until bubbles if it has been refrigerated.
Serves 6.

title: cooked fruit
directions: Mix cocktail, pineapple, cherries, oranges, peach pie filling and bananas. Melt margarine and add brown sugar and curry. Mix with the fruit. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: baked spinach and tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sprinkle cooked spinach with lemon juice and stir in sour cream.
Set aside.
If mushrooms are small, leave them whole.
If large, remove stems and quarter heads.
Melt butter in a skillet and saute mushrooms for 5 minutes, just enough to soften.
Fold into spinach.
Slice tomatoes 1/4-inch thick. Put half of spinach-mushroom mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle lightly with grated Cheddar.
Cover with a layer of tomato slices, half of the salt, a few gratings of pepper and more cheese.
Repeat layers using all tomatoes and all cheese.
Top with Mozzarella to seal.
Bake for about 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: french bread(for bread machine)
directions: Ingredients should all be at room temperature (except water). Whip the whites until stiff and set aside.
In the order listed, place the first 6 ingredients in the bread machine pan; select "French bread" and push "start."
Once all ingredients are moist, dump in the egg whites.
If you choose, lightly brush the top with a mixture of the optional water, salt and cornstarch and sprinkle with sesame or poppy seed after the second mixing is over.

title: weber chicken
directions: Soak charcoal for 15 minutes before lighting.
Separate coals into 2 sections (circular cooking).
Light coals and let them get hot.
Sprinkle pepper, seasoning salt, paprika and garlic salt all over the chicken and rub in.
Stuff chicken with quartered potatoes.
Place chicken on edge of rack.
Cover and let cook until tender.

title: slidders(french noodle)
directions: Mix flour and salt together.
Add enough water to make a soft dough the texture of pie crust.
Roll out on floured board; cut in 1-inch squares.
Drop in boiling chicken broth and cook until all noodles come to top and boil for 5 minutes more.

title: fruit juice punch with sherbet
directions: Add water to juice concentrate according to the directions on the cans.
Chill juices and just before serving add 1 quart ginger ale and pour over sherbet.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix vegetable ingredients together in large bowl.
Bring mixture of sugar, oil and vinegar to a boil.
Turn heat down and simmer for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour over sauerkraut mixture and mix well.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.
Will keep in refrigerator for several weeks; flavor will improve.
More sugar may be added to suit individual taste.

title: fresh peach muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and mix.
Stir in baking powder, flour, salt and nutmeg alternating with milk.
Stir in fresh peaches.
Fill greased muffin pan, filling each cup 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Preparation time:
15 minutes.
Yield:
12 muffins.

title: dorothy's chop suey
directions: Brown pork in heavy saucepan or wok.
Add onion, celery, bell pepper, soy sauce and chop suey vegetables.
Add cornstarch the last 15 minutes of simmering.
Add more soy sauce.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.
Add Chinese noodles if desired.

title: pink lady salad
directions: Stir together all ingredients in a large bowl.
Cover and refrigerate long enough for flavors to blend.
Serve cold.

title: beef jerky
directions: Cut all fat off flank steak; finely slice flank steak with grain.
Marinate for 24 hours in refrigerator.
Place strips or marinated steak across oven racks.
Use of heat: the heat of the pilot light is sufficient, remove from oven after 24 hours, store in a large wide mouthed jar that has air holes in lid.
If you have an electric oven, you will have to turn the heat on and off; never let the temperature rise above 100°.
The jerky may be done in less than 24 hours.
The secret is very low but consistent heat.

title: french meat pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in the saucepan and cook until hamburg and pork are cooked.
Drain grease from pan.
Add ingredients to 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add water and shortening, then eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 48 minutes. Allow cake to cool in pan for 15 minutes before removing.

title: brenda's apricot nectar cake
directions: Use method on cake mix box, except substitute apricot nectar for water and add 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix well.
Bake in tube pan at 350° until done.

title: aztec pyramid avocado dip
directions: For dramatic presentation, construct this dip in layers on a tray like a pyramid, with each layer smaller than the one below.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Add enough rice to cover the bottom of a large baking dish. Pour can of mushroom soup and 1 can water over rice.
Add chicken or pork chops on top.
Bake at 350° until the meat is done.
Add water to rice as needed to keep moist.

title: salmon bake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Put in a covered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Goes well with potatoes and peas.

title: zucchini pineapple jam
directions: Mix zucchini and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 6 minutes. Stir constantly.
Add lemon juice and pineapple.
Cook and stir for 8 minutes.
Add jello.
Stir for 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Skim and fill jars or plastic containers.
Cool before covering. Refrigerate up to 3 weeks.
Yields 4 cups.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix until smooth and creamy.
Slice apples and dip and enjoy.

title: poor woman's lobster
directions: Per pound of skinless frozen haddock fillets, use 2 tablespoons salt in cold water to cover in large skillet.
Boil gently for 10 minutes, then drain.
Again, cover with cold water, adding 2 tablespoons vinegar and 1/2 teaspoon sugar.
Bring to boil and boil for 10 minutes.
Drain well; remove to hot platter. Serve immediately with melted butter.
(Do not leave fish "standing" in water after it has cooked.)

title: texas pinwheels
directions: Mix the cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Season to taste with Tony's.
Spread small amount on tortilla and roll like jelly roll.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: parmesan butter pan biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In 9-inch square baking pan, melt butter in oven (3 to 5 minutes).
Meanwhile, in medium bowl, combine all ingredients, except milk.
Stir in milk just until moistened. Turn dough onto slightly floured surface.
Knead 10 times or until smooth.
Roll dough into 12 x 4-inch rectangle.
Cut into 12 (1-inch) strips.
Dip each into melted butter or until slightly browned.
Makes 1 dozen.
Time:
35 minutes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix the milk and Cool Whip into the frozen lemonade (do not add water to lemonade).
Pour mixture into graham cracker crust. Chill.

title: elegant italian cheese roll
directions: Grease 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly pan.
Line with wax paper; grease paper.
Sift cocoa, flour and salt into bowl.
Beat egg yolks in second bowl until thick and lemony.
Gradually beat in confectioners sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Fold in cocoa mixture.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar in bowl until stiff peaks form.
Gently fold into yolk mixture, half at a time.
Spoon into prepared pan; smooth top.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes or until center springs back when lightly pressed with fingertip.
Loosen cake edges with knife.
Invert onto clean towel.
Remove pan and wax paper.
Roll up cake and towels together from short end.
Place on rack to cool completely.

title: deep fried halibut
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 1/2 cup margarine in 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Roll fillets in melted butter and dredge in cracker/bread crumbs until well coated.
Return coated fillets to baking dish and bake for approximately 30 minutes or until desired doneness.

title: texas brownies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine flour and sugar.
In a heavy saucepan, combine margarine, shortening, coffee or water and cocoa. Stir and heat to boiling.
Pour boiling mixture over the flour and sugar in the bowl.
Add the buttermilk, eggs, baking soda and vanilla.
Mix well on high speed on electric mixer.
Pour into a well-greased 17 1/2 x 11-inch jelly roll pan. Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: deviled crab
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form crab shells from aluminum foil.
Spray with Pam.
Fill each shell with crab mixture and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until firm.

title: crustless pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs 1 minute.
Add flour, sugar and salt until smooth. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour and mix, then add vanilla and pecans.
Form into small balls.
Bake on greased baking sheet at 300° for 45 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar after cooling for a few minutes.

title: nutty putty
directions: Put starch in a bowl.
Add glue and let sit 5 minutes.
If desired, add coloring.
Mix until starch is absorbed and color is spread smoothly. Store in plastic egg or jar overnight before using to pick up pictures from comics.
Use to bounce, pick up pictures from comics or newspapers and mold into shapes.

title: cathie mcmahon's apple dip
directions: Mix together cheese, sugar, caramel topping and vanilla well in a bowl.
Serve with apple slices.

title: indian corn casserole
directions: Mix egg, flour and sugar.
Add cheese and corn.
Cook bacon; drain and crumble.
Stir 2 slices of bacon into mixture.
Turn mixture into a baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining bacon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: cheryl's yeast rolls
directions: In one bowl, combine the warm water and the yeast.
Add the sugar and 1 cup flour.
Mix to take out lumps; set aside.
In a larger bowl, combine the melted butter, eggs and salt.
Combine yeast mixture to egg mixture; stir.
Add 5 cups flour.
Stir in flour well.
Keep in large bowl.
Cover; set in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.

title: fettucine and chicken
directions: Bring a large pot of water to boiling.
Brown chicken breasts in large skillet sprayed with nonfat cooking spray.
Set chicken aside; remove any chicken fat from the skillet.

title: date nut balls
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar and chopped dates; cook 6 minutes. Add 2 teaspoons water to make light balls.
Stir in coconut.
Take off stove.
Add vanilla and the chopped nuts.
Cool a little and add Rice Krispies.
Form into small balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 12 dozen balls.

title: apricot slush
directions: Boil tea in 2 cups water.
Add sugar.
Pour into plastic container.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Freeze.
To use, place in glass 1/2 full.
Fill with very cold 7-Up.

title: berry rose jelly
directions: In large saucepan, combine sugar, cranberry-raspberry drink, cinnamon and cloves.
Bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve sugar. Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in wine and pectin.
Skim off foam with metal spoon.
Spoon into clean 8 ounce jars or moisture, vapor-proof freezer containers. Cover with tight fitting lids.
Lasts 3 weeks in refrigerator or 3 months in freezer.

title: jon's baked stuffed shrimp
directions: Arrange cleaned, deveined, butterflied shrimp into glass baking dish.
Make stuffing by finely crumbling crackers (use food processor or place in a plastic bag and roll with rolling pin). Combine with melted butter and seasoning.
Mix well with a fork or whisk.
Add sherry to moisten, until stuffing will hold when molded.
(Do not overdo sherry.)
Place stuffing on individual shrimp.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Serve with drawn butter.

title: mexican dish
directions: Grate cheese and set aside.
Combine hamburger, onion and pepper in skillet; brown and drain.
Add soup and enchilada sauce. Line casserole dish with tortillas.
Layer meat mixture, cheese and tortillas, ending, with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Dissolve strawberry Jell-O in boiling water.
Immediately add frozen strawberries or cold, fresh berries.
Allow to partially set up and then spread over top of cheese mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: mushroom gravy (for steaks)
directions: Drain mushrooms.
In a medium saucepan, melt butter and add mushrooms.
Saute for 3 minutes.
Add drippings from steaks
and flour; cook over medium heat for 1 minute.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in water.
Blend into mushroom mixture and bring to boil, stirring constantly, cook and stir for 1 minute and serve with steak.

title: honolulu style broiled chicken
directions: A long-standing tradition at "our" Italian home.
A recipe that goes back to the "homeland."
Sicily is where it all began many, many centuries ago at those large family gatherings on those special occasions.
Using the finest of meats and vegetables, sauces and doughs of the greatest quality.
Do like the Amentas do...1-800-DOMINOS.

title: caviar pie
directions: Mix eggs, mayonnaise and onion.
Spread in glass pie plate. Mix cream cheese and sour cream.
Spread over egg mixture.
Chill 4 hours or overnight.
Spread with 2 3/4 ounce jar black caviar. Garnish with lemon slices.
Serve with unsalted crackers (Matzos?).

title: decorator frosting
directions: Whip Crisco very well. Gradually add sugar and egg whites alternately. Add salt, vanilla and flavoring. Beat until light and fluffy. Spread on cooled cake.

title: dutch apple bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with juice; then fold in apples and walnuts.
Bake in greased loaf pans.

title: dirt cake
directions: Blend butter and cream cheese together.
Add pudding, milk, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Blend all together.
Blend a 20 ounce package Oreos in food processor until fine (can't see icing). Layer pudding and Oreos until top of flower pot, end with Oreos. Chill and serve.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Prepare dinner according to package directions. Add tuna, soup, milk and seasonings. Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Top with crushed potato chips or crushed crackers. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients.
May refrigerate overnight. Roll teaspoonful of dough into ball and roll into sugar or sprinkles.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 8 minutes.

title: microwave caramel
directions: Microwave 5 minutes on High; stir well.
Cook 5 minutes longer on High; beat well with wooden spoon.
Cook 8 minutes longer.
Add nuts.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes thick; boil in salt water until slightly tender.
In small skillet, saute onion in margarine until tender. In medium saucepan, combine soup, onion and cheese; heat on low until cheese melts.
In casserole dish, alternate potatoes and soup until all is used.
Top with cheese slices; bake in oven at 350° or in microwave until cheese melts.

title: trail jam - make fresh berry jam while camping!!!!!!
directions: In pan, combine berries, sugar, lemon juice and cinnamon.
Over brisk fire, boil fruit, stirring until it reaches desired thickness.
Serve warm or cooled.
Makes 1 1/4 cups to put on pancakes or spread on campfire biscuits.

title: baby food plum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Let cream cheese set out 1 hour to soften.
Beat sugar and cream cheese, then stir in Cool Whip.
Pour in pie crust, then add cherries.

title: best macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in large kettle in boiling salted water until al dente, pliable but not mushy. Drain well and return to pot. Add milk and butter and place over medium-low heat. When butter has melted, add cheese, a little at a time, until all have melted into a smooth sauce. Remove from heat and stir in egg. Season with salt and pepper. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until edges begin to set and casserole is bubbly.

title: chicken-noodle-cheese casserole
directions: Cook chicken; remove from broth and remove meat from bone. Cook noodles in
broth.
Cook
vegetables
separately,
save cooking water. Combine meat,
vegetables,
water and cheeses.
Add seasoning to taste. Bake 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: pork chops with sauce
directions: *You can use 1 (8 ounce) jar sweet and sour sauce, 1 (10 3/4 ounce) can cream of chicken soup, 1 (10 3/4 ounce) can chicken and rice soup or 1 1/2 cups barbecue sauce in place of the mushroom soup.

title: zucchini bread
directions: If using self-rising flour, omit salt and baking soda.
If using plain flour, use those ingredients.

title: yummy bread pudding
directions: Combine sugar, salt, vanilla, butter, cinnamon and egg. Slowly add scalded milk while stirring.
Add bread and raisins. Pour into a well buttered baking dish.
Set into a pan of warm water and bake about an hour at 350°.
Cool before serving.

title: rhinelander pork chops
directions: Brown chops in a large skillet; drain on paper.
Saute onion, green pepper and celery in drippings until tender.
Stir in onion soup mix and water.
Return chops to pan and cover to simmer for 45 minutes (stirring often) until chops are tender.
Serve over brown rice.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in a 13 1/2 x 9-inch pan in a 300° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Take pan out of oven; spread with marshmallows over top.
Put back in oven for about 5 minutes to let the marshmallows melt and begin to brown slightly.
Remove from oven; let cool while you make icing.

title: biscuit mix
directions: Stir dry ingredients together; cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stores up to 6 weeks at room temperature.

title: zucchini chow chow
directions: Combine zucchini, onions, peppers and salt.
Let set overnight, covered. Rinse with cold water and drain extremely well.
Press firmly to get water out (very important).

title: spicy rotini
directions: Prepare pasta according to package directions; drain. Keep warm. Heat olive oil in 12-inch skillet on medium heat. Add vegetables. Cook until lightly browned and tender, about 15 minutes, stirring often.

title: garlic potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into small wedges and arrange in baking dish. Melt butter in microwave or pan.
Mix garlic powder into butter and pour over potatoes.
Stir potatoes to make sure all are coated.
Arrange skins down.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Add parsley flakes.
Bake in 375° oven for one hour.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients.
Pour into shell.
Bake about 45 minutes until just lightly set.
Serves 8.

title: roasted pumpkin seed
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grind rosemary in a spice or coffee grinder.
Combine with remaining ingredients and spread on a baking sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, or until crisp and brown.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and season with salt and pepper. Wash chilies and remove seeds and strips. Place 1/2 of the ground beef on bottom of casserole dish.
Top with chilies and cheese and then repeat.

title: jam cake(layered fruit cake)
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs. Beat well. Sift dry ingredients. Add alternately buttermilk and flour into the egg mixture. Fold in jam, coconut and vanilla. Grease and flour 3 eight-inch pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked chilies rellenos
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut chilies in half.
Spread chilies on paper towel and pat dry.
Slip a strip of Monterey Jack cheese into each chili and lay them side by side in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.

title: veggie bars
directions: Bake crescent rolls 10 minutes at 350°.
Mix cream cheese, dressing and mayonnaise; spread over baked rolls.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread over rolls and sprinkle with cheese. Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours, overnight is okay.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: brunch casserole(serves 12)
directions: Grease your 9 x 13-inch dish first, then line your dish with bread.
Spread your fried sausage on top of your bread, then top with cheese.
Beat eggs and pour on top of your cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour on top.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: tuna salad
directions: Flake tuna.
Add rest of ingredients with mayonnaise.

title: boneless pork roast
directions: Place roast in a deep casserole dish.
Almost cover with water. Add seasonings of your choice to taste. Cover tightly. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Remove from oven.
Pour off part of the broth. Add barbecue sauce.
Return to oven and cook 30 minutes longer.
Remove from oven and let set, covered, for 45 minutes before slicing.

title: oriental pasta salad
directions: In a small skillet over low heat, toast sesame seeds, stirring occasionally, until seeds turn a light golden brown (about 3 minutes).
Remove from heat and cool.

title: stir-fried beef and tomatoes
directions: Partially freeze beef.
Thinly slice across grain into bite-size pieces; set aside.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine ingredients in blender.
Blend until mixture is smooth.

title: mississippi mud brownies
directions: Place butter in a 2-quart mixing bowl; microwave at High 1 minute, or until butter melts.
Stir in sugar and eggs; set aside. Combine flour, salt and cocoa; stir well.
Stir dry mixture into egg mixture.
Stir in vanilla and pecans.
Spread batter in a greased and floured 8-inch square baking dish.
Shield corners with triangles of aluminum foil, keeping foil smooth and close to dish.
Place baking dish on a microwave-safe cereal bowl inverted in the oven.
Microwave at Medium (50% power) 6 to 7 minutes, giving dish a half turn after 3 minutes.
Remove shields; microwave at High 2 to 3 minutes, or until top is almost dry.
Remove from oven; place directly on countertop to cool.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Beat shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk. Combine salt, baking powder and flour; add to sugar mixture.
Add flavorings and coconut.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Place on rack; cool.
Cover lightly until cold.

title: crab and shrimp dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Mix with cream of chicken soup. Place in a casserole dish and place Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Beat egg yolks; add milk, salt, sugar, flour, corn and butter. Fold in slightly beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes or until set.

title: crab ball
directions: Mix crab meat and cream cheese.
Add garlic powder to taste. Mold into ball shape.
Put a hole in the middle of ball and pour cocktail sauce over it.
Place Crab Ball on plate surrounded by Club crackers.

title: holiday confetti mix("reindeer mix")
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in an airtight container in a cool dry place.
Makes 11 cups.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together. Chill 24 hours.

title: brownies
directions: Make brownies according to directions; put in pan.
Sprinkle chips on top.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until done.

title: death by chocolate cake
directions: Pour oil into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan to cover the bottom. Add cake mix, eggs and water.
Stir in the pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top of cake, as many as will fit.
Bake in 350° oven, 30 to 35 minutes.
Take cake from oven and let set 10 to 15 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a casserole.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven, put the other half of the French onions around edge of casserole and bake 10 more minutes or longer until French onions have browned.

title: banana and spices bread
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Cream the butter and sugar. Beat in eggs until mixture is light and fluffy. Combine the first 6 ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with the mashed bananas. Add nuts. Turn into 2 well-greased and lightly floured loaf pans or muffin tins or a combination of both. Bake loaves about 1 1/2 hours, muffins about 30 minutes.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water. Cool. Cream butter and sugar. Add egg yolks, beating well after each. Blend in vanilla and chocolate. Sift flour with soda and salt; add alternately with buttermilk to chocolate mixture. Mix well. Fold in beaten egg whites. Bake in 4 (9-inch) pans at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: broke da mout ahu steaks
directions: Slice the ahi fillets into 2-inch steaks.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and let sit for 10 minutes.
Put bacon drippings into a frypan and heat.
When pan and drippings are hot, put in the ahi steaks.
Allow enough time to cook the fish through, without overcooking.
Overcooking will result in dry fish.
Serve the fish on a bed of lettuce.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in 1 c. boiling water.
Set aside to cool.
Roll out about 30 graham crackers.
Mix crumbs with butter. Sprinkle bottom of 8 x 12 in. baking dish with half of the crumb mixture.
Reserve the rest for the top of the cake.
Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Whip
chilled Milnot until thick.
Add cheese/sugar and jello and whip together.
Pour over crumbs.
Add rest of crumbs to top of cheesecake.

title: taco casserole
directions: In 9 x 13-inch casserole, layer beans, cooked hamburger seasoned with taco seasoning and cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°, covered.
Spread sour cream over dish and cover with layer of onions, tomatoes and avocado.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: mexican dip
directions: Put altogether in Crock-Pot.
It will never fail and it is a great dip.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix cherry pie filling and crushed pineapple; spread into a 9 x 13 pan. Mix cake mix, coconut and pecans; sprinkle over pie filling mixture. Slice oleo and place on the top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Bring water, margarine and cocoa to a boil.
Sift sugar and flour together.
Stir into water mixture.
Stir baking soda into buttermilk.
Add buttermilk, vanilla and eggs (slightly beaten) to mixture.
Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with hot water, vinegar and onion.
Cool until thickens.
Beat and add mayonnaise, cucumbers and cottage cheese. Pour into mold and congeal.

title: busy-day casserole
directions: Mix soups with sherry and onion soup mix and pour over meat. Bake 3 hours in 300° oven in a covered casserole.
Serve over rice, noodles or potatoes.
Serves 6.

title: nut roll
directions: Follow directions for hot roll mix.
Let rise.
Roll out dough into 4 sections.
Mix ground shelled walnuts, sugar and milk with mixer.
Spread thinly over 4 sections of dough.
Roll dough like jelly roll.
Pinch sides.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cool whip delight
directions: Pull angel food cake in pieces and place one layer in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then mix Cool Whip and jello powder together and place one layer of Cool Whip mixture on top of angel food cake.
Then place another layer of cake, then layer of Cool Whip mixture.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and beaten eggs.
Add rest of ingredients. Mix and pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: butterscotch dessert
directions: Mix and pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: hot and spicy pecans
directions: Melt butter in large, heavy skillet or saucepan.
Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients, except pecans, stirring well.
Add pecans, stirring to coat well.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add Chili-O mix, stewed tomatoes and beans.
Add water until all covered.
Cook on medium heat for 1 hour.
Serve over rice.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl with electric mixer and beat until smooth.
Dissolve baking soda in water and add with remaining ingredients.
Stir with wooden spoon until just combined.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: woody's best beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in shallow 3-quart baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain noodles and set aside.
Combine soups, milk, tuna and peas in saucepan and bring to a boil.
In casserole dish, layer 1/2 of the tuna mixture, 1/2 noodles, 1/2 tuna and 1/2 noodles.
Add crackers to top layer. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until sides start to bubble.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown hamburger in oil.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, kidney beans, chili powder and hot pepper sauce.
Mix in 3/4 cup water.
Cover; simmer for 2 1/2 hours or more, until meat is tender.
Add more water as needed. Makes 6 to 8 servings.
(May omit oil.)

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Sift together dry ingredients, stir into creamed mixture and blend well. Add chocolate chips.
Drop from teaspoon 2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes approximately 3 dozen.

title: dill pickles
directions: Bring to a boil the water, vinegar and salt.
Pour over cucumbers packed in jars with dill and alum.
Seal.

title: creamy baked chicken
directions: Put chicken in lightly greased pan.
Top with Swiss cheese. Cover with mushroom soup.
Sprinkle stuffing over top.
Drizzle melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: rice krispies and date skillet cookies
directions: Mix eggs, salt, dates, sugar and butter and simmer until thick, about 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cool slightly.
Roll into balls, then roll in powdered sugar.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Skin and bone chicken.
Combine crumbs, Parmesan and salt. Beat egg and oil in bowl.
Dip chicken in egg, then crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together and pour into a greased 9 x 13 in. pan.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and prepare to direction on box (adding cheese from box as well).
In small bowl mix tuna (and liquid from tuna), mushroom soup, milk, and salt and pepper to taste.
Lastly, add peas, but don't squish them.
Add the tuna mixture to mac and cheese; mix together but not too much because you can overmix and make it mushy.

title: marie's baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and cream of tartar in a bowl.
Add the shortening, butter or margarine to the flour mixture and blend together until of corn meal consistency.
Pour milk into flour mixture slowly.
Add the egg.
Stir to a stiff dough.
Knead 5 times.
Roll into 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with 1 1/2-inch biscuit or round cookie cutter.
Bake on aluminum cookie sheet 10 to 15 minutes at 450°.

title: bea's blueberry muffins
directions: In a large bowl, mix together the beaten eggs, oil, sugar and sour cream.
In a separate bowl, sift together the flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to the first mixture, mixing well. Flour the blueberries with the 1 tablespoon flour and fold into the batter.
Place in muffin tins which have been greased or paper lined.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Yield:
2 doz. muffins.

title: reese's no bake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate and press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: waldorf salad drop cookies
directions: In a medium-size bowl, stir together the flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
In large bowl of electric mixer at medium speed beat together sugar, mayonnaise, eggs and vanilla until smooth.
Add flour mixture and at low speed beat until smooth.
Stir in the apples, walnuts and celery.
Drop by level tablespoons, 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 350°
oven until lightly brown, 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning until well blended.
Place cream cheese mixture in the bottom of a glass 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour taco sauce over cream cheese mixture. Place a layer of lettuce on top of sauce; continue with a layer of tomatoes, a layer of celery and finally spread Mozzarella cheese over the top.

title: baked roast
directions: Place roast in 9 x 13 or larger pan. Pour dry soup mix over roast. Pour can of soup over dry mix. Pour 1 can of water around roast. Place onion in pan. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 2 hours. Remove and add vegetables. Cover and bake 1 more hour.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Roll into 58 balls.
Make design with fork on each rolled ball.
Bake at 250° for almost an hour.
While warm, roll in powdered sugar. Store in airtight container.
Serves 58.

title: italian beef
directions: Wipe meat with a paper towel and brown in the olive oil in Dutch oven. Add remaining ingredients. Cook on top of stove, covered, over medium heat for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until very tender. Add more broth or water as needed. When meat is done, shred into chunks and spoon out on hard rolls (hoagies) for delicious sandwiches.

title: sugar cookies
directions: *You may use butter or margarine, either one is good.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Shred FriChick and add to drained noodles.
Toss vegetables with noodle mixture. Add dressings, garlic salt and cheese; mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: smoked sausage skillet dinner
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions, omitting salt and fat. Drain well.
Set aside.
Cut sausage into 1/4-inch thick slices.

title: onion burgers
directions: Fry hamburger; drain.
Mix in soup and flour; simmer 5 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: stuffed steak
directions: Cut a deep slit horizontally in the steak to form a pocket. Cook the onion and mushrooms in butter or margarine until tender. Stir in ham, bread crumbs, parsley, oil and dash of pepper.
Cook 2 minutes more.
Spoon mixture into pocket in meat; place cheese in pocket.
Secure pocket with skewers.
