Place steak on unheated rack of broiler pan.
Broil 4 inches from the heat about 8 minutes per side for medium-rare or until of desired doneness.
To serve, slice meat crosswise.
Makes 2 servings.

title: 60 minute parker house rolls
directions: Pour yeast into tepid water.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar.
Stir and let stand 5 minutes.
(Place this in a 1-cup measuring cup as it will foam considerably.)
Scald the milk; add salt, remaining sugar and margarine.
Cool until tepid.

title: fudge
directions: Bring sugar, butter and evaporated milk to rolling boil; boil for 5 minutes.
Melt together in double boiler the chocolate bits, Baker's chocolate and milk chocolate bar.
Add melted chocolate to boiled sugar mixture, then add marshmallow, vanilla and nuts.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into buttered pan.
Makes 6 pounds of fudge.

title: shrimp tempura
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Beat egg and water.
Add dry ingredients and mix well. For thin lacy batter, add 2 tablespoons more water. Dip shrimp in batter and fry in hot oil.

title: homemade chocolate ice cream
directions: In a blender, mix some of the milk with the sugar and chocolate syrup.
Pour into freezer container.
Use some more of the milk in the blender to mix Cool Whip and pudding mix.
Pour into freezer container.
Use remainder of milk to fill freezer container to fill line.
Freeze in electric or hand-turned freezer.

title: easy macaroon cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Drop from teaspoon 1 inch apart on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden brown.
Remove at once from baking sheet.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: sausage stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Wipe mushrooms with damp paper towels. Remove stems; set caps aside.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Blend together beef, eggs, 1 teaspoon cornstarch, onion, pepper, nutmeg, salt and garlic.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Heat oil in skillet and brown meatballs on all sides.

title: broccoli pie
directions: Cook broccoli according to instructions on package.
Drain off water when cooked.

title: heavenly broiled fish
directions: Place fish in a single layer on a well-greased bake and serve platter 15 x 10-inches.
Brush fish with lemon juice; let stand 10 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients and set aside.
Broil fish about 4 inches from source of heat for 6 to 8 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Remove from heat; spread with cheese mixture.
Broil 2 to 3 minutes longer or until cheese mixture is lightly browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: salmon patties
directions: Remove dark skin and bones from salmon.
Mix all the above ingredients together thoroughly.
Shape into patties.
Shape into patties and brown on each side.
Served topped with creamed peas and a lemon wedge.

title: simple cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pie filling.
Pour into casserole dish.
Add pie filling, pouring it into the middle.
Do not stir! Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Preparation time:
10 minutes.

title: super sour cream banana bar cake
directions: Mix together the first 9 ingredients and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°
in a greased and floured jelly roll pan (with sides).
When cake is almost cool, mix together the last 5 ingredients and spread over the banana bar cake.
Great!

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut meat into strips.
Add soy sauce, toss and set aside, while preparing vegetables.
Heat oil in a large frying pan or wok.
Add beef and toss until browned.
Cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes over low heat.
Turn heat up and add vegetables.
Toss until vegetables are crisp.
Mix cornstarch with water and add to pan, cooking until thickened.
Serve over rice.
Makes 2 servings.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: Combine hot water and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Cook rapidly to soft ball stage.
Combine egg whites and cream of tartar.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Pour syrup slowly into egg whites, beating at high speed.
Add vanilla. Continue beating until frosting reaches spreading consistency.

title: hash brown casserole(microwave recipe)
directions: Saute onion in margarine approximately 2 to 3 minutes on High power (cover with lid or plastic wrap).
Mix cream of chicken soup, onion, margarine, salt and pepper with potatoes.
Place in casserole dish and cook on High power for 4 to 5 minutes.
Spread sour cream over top.
Sprinkle cheese next and then corn flake crumbs.
Cook at 70% power for 18 to 20 minutes (1/2 recipe, cook for 10 to 12 minutes).
Do not cover.
Make large casserole (10 to 12 servings).

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: Pare eggplant, cut in 1/4-inch slices.
Cook in salted water until tender, drain. Into 1-quart baking dish put a layer of eggplant, then a layer of white sauce, then a layer of buttered bread crumbs.
Do this until ingredients are used up.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: microwave pralines
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil, grease lightly.
Oil large soup spoon.
Mix sugars, syrup and water in 2-quart glass measuring cup. Microwave uncovered on High 6 to 8 minutes.
Do not stir until microwave candy thermometer reads 234° to 240°.
Stir in butter and vanilla, then nuts.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Stir vigorously 2 minutes until mixture thickens and turns opaque.
Drop by tablespoon onto foil (If mixture sets, pop bake in microwave 30 to 45 seconds.)
Let stand 1 hour until cool.
Store in airtight container.
Easy and great!

title: coconut cookies
directions: Dissolve baking soda in a little milk; add remaining ingredients and enough flour to roll.
Bake at 325° for 5 to 6 minutes or until golden brown.

title: banana bread(makes 1 loaf)
directions: Beat oil and sugar until mixture is smooth.
Beat in eggs until mixture is smooth.
Add soda and salt.
Mix well.
Add flour a little at a time and mix well.
Mix in bananas and add walnuts. Pour into an oiled and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or more (until a knife or straw inserted into the center comes out clean).

title: chicken 'n dumplings
directions: Boil whole chicken until tender.
Cover with water and 1 teaspoon salt.
When done, take chicken out of broth and save broth.
Debone chicken and set aside.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Thoroughly mix shortening, sugar, egg and molasses.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to shortening mixture; mix well.
Chill dough.
When dough is chilled, shape into balls the size of large nuts.
Dip tops in sugar.
Place cookies, sugared side up, on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle cookies with 2 to 3 drops of water.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: french toast souffle
directions: Place cubed bread in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish coated with nonstick spray.
Beat cream cheese with mixer until smooth; add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk, half and half, vanilla and 1/2 cup syrup until smooth.
Pour mixture over cubed bread; refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Remove bread mixture from refrigerator.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Uncover; bake at 375° for 50 minutes or until set.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve with 3/4 cup syrup.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar. Blend in eggs, salt, soda and vanilla. Mix in flour, then chips. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cafe houvelle mousse cake
directions: Bake a single layer chocolate cake in a spring-form pan.
Cool and top with blender mousse.
Combine all listed ingredients, but cream, in blender.
Heat cream, but do not let boil.
Through blender cap, gradually add hot cream, blending until smooth.
Pour on top of cooled cake in pan.
Chill overnight.
Run spatula around sides and release.

title: pickle rings
directions: Mix cucumbers, onion and salt; let stand 1 hour.
Drain. Bring remaining ingredients to a boil; pour over drained cucumbers and simmer for 20 minutes.
Pack in sterilized jars; seal.

title: a quick snack
directions: Place pepperoni slices on a microwavable dish.
Top with cheese and microwave for 30 seconds.
Place on bread of your choice.
Add sauce.
You may also add tomatoes, mushrooms, onion and green peppers.
Kids love them and can do it themselves.

title: hot punch
directions: Heat in crock pot on slow for 4 hours.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Mix all ingredients well with hands.
Roll into balls, the size of walnuts.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and press with tines of fork in crisscross.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on cake rack.
Serve at room temperature. They freeze very well.

title: cherry squares
directions: Gradually add sugar to butter in large mixing bowl, cream at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each at low speed.
Add flour and lemon juice. Pour batter into well greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan; mark 20 squares off.
Place 1 tablespoon pie filling in center of each square.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
While warm, sift confectioners sugar over.
Cool and cut into 20 squares.

title: orange pecans
directions: Cook the first two ingredients until soft ball forms in cold water. Remove from heat and add remaining three ingredients. Stir until mixture sugars, pour onto buttered pan and separate each pecan.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix 1 beaten egg, flour and sugar with 2 cups peaches.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and cover with crumbs made of teaspoon butter, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 2 teaspoons flour.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: apple refrigerator dessert
directions: Place 3 crackers in waxed paper-lined loaf pan.
Combine applesauce and nutmeg.
Spread over crackers.
Repeat, making 7 layers.
Chill several hours.
Cover with topping; garnish with citron.
Serves 6.

title: six point spread
directions: Combine cream cheese and Swiss cheese, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer, until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Beat cream cheese until soft.
Add confectioners sugar and extract.
Knead the mixture.
Pinch off small piece and roll in granulated sugar.
Press into candy mold.
Place on wax paper. Makes 40 to 50 mints.

title: caramel-nut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add brown sugar a little at a time, beating
well.
Add
white	sugar; beat until light and fluffy. Add
eggs
one
at	a time; beat well after each one. Beat	3 more minutes.
Sift baking powder and salt with flour and
add alternately
with
milk.
Stir
in vanilla and nuts. (Mix
a little
flour with nuts).
Bake in stem pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake about 45 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: tomato soup cupcakes
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and egg.
Add spices and remainder of ingredients.
Grease and flour cupcake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 14 cupcakes.
Frost with chocolate icing.

title: dill pickles
directions: Pour
brine
over
cucumbers
and
let stand overnight. Wash and sterilize 4 pint jars and lids.
Drain cucumbers and pack into
hot jars, leaving 1/4 inch headspace.
To each jar add
2 sprigs of dill or 1 tablespoon dill seed and 1 teaspoon mustard seed, pushing halfway down in jar.
Set uncovered jars on a cookie sheet and keep hot in a 250° oven.

title: pineapple squares
directions: Combine pineapple, cornstarch, granulated sugar and lemon juice in saucepan; cook until thickened.
Combine brown sugar, salt, flour, shortening and oatmeal in bowl.
Spread 3/4 of this mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan; pat down.
Spread pineapple mixture over this.
Sprinkle with remaining oatmeal mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: large jello mold
directions: Strain peaches and save juice.
Make lemon jello with 2 cups hot water and 1 cup peach juice.
Put peached in mold and cover with lemon jello (save 1 cup). Put 1 cup lemon jello in refrigerator to jell to egg white consistency.
Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions.
Cream the cheese, then add the 1 cup of lemon jello, add to Dream Whip.
Pour into set peach-layered jello in mold.
Chill.
Make strawberry jello with 2 cups hot water and 1 cup fruit cocktail juice. Put strained fruit cocktail into cooled strawberry jello, then pour on top of set white layer in mold.
Chill overnight.

title: quick and easy noodles(for working moms)
directions: Note:
Frozen broccoli or chopped chicken can be added for a meal.

title: easy tuna casserole
directions: Make macaroni as directed on package.
Mix all ingredients (do not drain tuna or corn).
Put in casserole dish; bake until heated through.

title: grilled shrimp
directions: Insert 6 peeled, deveined, raw shrimp onto 8 to 12-inch wooden skewers, putting skewers through the middle of tail and head end of the shrimp.
Soak in dish and cover with Italian dressing for 30 minutes (at least).
Cook skewers of shrimp on a hot grill, turning for even cooking, until shrimp are pink, approximately 3 to 5 minutes on each side.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour and milk alternately to creamed mixture.
Add salt, baking powder and flavoring; mix well. Pour into large tube pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
"Put in cold oven and then turn on."

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling salt water 10 to 12 minutes (until stems are almost tender); drain.
Place in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Heat oven to 400°.
Beat soup and milk with whisk or fork until smooth.
Pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese. Mix baking mix and margarine until crumbly.
Sprinkle over cheese. Bake until light brown, 20 minutes.

title: better than *** cake
directions: Bake cake as per directions. While cake is still hot, poke holes all over. Pour over sweetened milk and caramel.
Let set and cool.
When cake is cool, top with Cool Whip. Crush candy bars. Sprinkle on Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: icebox cake dessert
directions: Prepare chocolate pudding with milk according to package directions.

title: shrimp salad louis
directions: Combine mayonnaise, French dressing, catsup, horseradish, salt, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco.
Add shrimp and mix well. Serve on shredded lettuce.
One 7 1/2-ounce can crabmeat may be added to shrimp in salad.
Serves 4.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 40-50 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients well and refrigerated.
Serve with assorted raw vegetables.

title: ashley's cheese and ham grits
directions: Bring salted water to boil with butter.
Add grits.
Turn heat down and cover.
When almost done, put cheese slices and ham pieces in until done.

title: ann's peanut butter fudge
directions: Use one large pan, sprayed and refrigerated to cool.
Mix first 3 ingredients (also put pinch of flour back).
Cook on medium heat until boils.
Stir continuously; won't hurt if sticks to pan.
Take spoonful and drop in cool water until it forms ball, then taste.
If sugary, cook longer (approximately 10 minutes). Take pan off stove and place in sink of cold water.
Add peanut butter and mix.
Place in pan that is chilled.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes well; prick with a fork and rub with soft margarine. Bake at 350° until tender.
When baking potatoes, sliver carrots and boil until tender.
Saute onions in a little margarine until tender.
When potatoes are tender, let cool a few minutes and cut lengthwise.
Scoop out warm pulp and put in mixer; add onions and carrots.
Beat until smooth and fluffy.
Add half and half, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Fold in cheese.
Scoop in shells; sprinkle more cheese on top.
Bake until thoroughly heated.
They can be refrigerated until the following day or wrap well and freeze until ready to use.

title: bar b q pork chops
directions: 1. Mix mushroom soup, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, and onions together.
2. Pour over pork chops in a casserole dish. Bake for 2
hours at 375°.

title: ham rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients but ham.
Spread mixture onto ham and roll up.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Slice and serve with any cracker.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain cherries.
Boil cherry juice and gelatin together until completely dissolved.
Add cream
cheese and melt in hot gelatin. Cool and add nuts, pineapple, celery, cherries and 1 can of Coca-Cola.	Pour in
mold
and
place
in refrigerator. Serves 6 or 8.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Have fun.
Use your hands and form into walnut shaped balls.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet at about 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Enjoy.

title: nutty fingers
directions: Mix butter, sugar and flour.
Put water and nuts in last. Shape and put in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 275° for 45 minutes.
Remove and roll in powdered sugar.
(Do not grease baking sheet.)
Makes 4 dozen.

title: apple-raisin cake
directions: Grease and flour two 9-inch round baking pans.
In large bowl with mixer at low speed, beat first 10 ingredients for 2 minutes, scraping bowl frequently.
Stir in apples, raisins and nuts.
Pour into pans.
Bake in 350° oven until done.
Remove; cool completely.
Fill and frost with 2 cups whipped cream.

title: midnight funnel cakes
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients with mixer until smooth.
Chill for at least 2 hours.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water until tender; drain well. Arrange in greased casserole dish.
Arrange chicken on top of this. Combine soup, mayonnaise, sour cream, lemon juice and curry powder. Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine crumbs and melted margarine.
Sprinkle over other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
May be trimmed with pimento strips.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook rice per directions on box. Cook sausage; drain and break into small pieces. Mix rice, sausage, sour cream and water chestnuts together. Put into casserole dish. Cut sliced bread into small squares and cover top of ingredients. Sprinkle melted butter over bread. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bread is golden brown.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Place chicken in crock-pot; sprinkle lemon pepper over chicken.
Add soups, wine and seasonings.
Cook in crock-pot on low for 10 hours or high for 5 hours.
Shred chicken and pour over pasta, rice or baked potatoes.

title: squash supreme
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Drain.
Combine soup, sour cream and pimentos with squash mixture.
Melt oleo and toss with dressing.
Put 1/2 of dressing mixture in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour squash mixture over this, then top with remaining dressing.
Bake for 5 minutes or until brown in a 425° oven.

title: layered toffee cake
directions: Beat cream cheese just until it begins to thicken.
Gradually add the ice cream topping and vanilla. Beat until soft peaks form.

title: beanie weanie
directions: Mix all ingredients in large pot.
Heat over medium heat until just prior to boil; turn down to low.
After 40 minutes, taste and add more of last 4 ingredients if needed.
Stir often clear to bottom; continue cooking another 30 minutes.
Serve.
Is better next day.

title: low-fat carrot cake(yields 12 servings)
directions: Combine carrots with boiling water.
Let stand.
Combine dry ingredients; set aside.
Beat egg whites, oil, applesauce, vanilla and molasses and/or honey.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat on low speed for 1 minute; medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Frost with cream cheese and coconut frosting.

title: peanut butter logs
directions: Combine peanut butter and margarine; stir in sugar.
Add cereal.
Mix well.
Shape level tablespoon of mix into logs.
Roll in peanuts.
Place on wax paper-lined cookie sheet.

title: fish batter
directions: Break the eggs in a small mixing bowl and add all the ingredients, except for water.
I use about 1/4 teaspoon of each spice, except for the garlic powder; use less garlic, or just season to your taste.
Batter will be thick.
Stir in water until batter is of dipping consistency.

title: punch(serves 150)
directions: Mix juices. Add ginger ale to taste as punch bowl is filled.

title: crescent kolachy
directions: Mix all ingredients together to form a pie like dough.
Roll out a section at a time onto floured surface until thin.
Cut into 1 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch squares.
Add a drop of filling (Solo works best) into center.
Fold in two corners overlapping the tips (wet to seal if needed).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bottom is golden brown.
Dust with powdered sugar.
These can be frozen to keep.
Once thawed, keep tightly contained.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine. Add other ingredients. Put in casserole dish and cover. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Brown bacon and drain.
Layer above ingredients in large bowl. Spread mayo mixture on top.
Sprinkle bacon on top of mayo. Refrigerate overnight.

title: fan tail shrimp
directions: Mix flour, egg and enough water to make a medium batter.
Salt and pepper shrimp to taste.
Fry on medium to high heat, turning until golden.
Drain on paper towels.

title: pineapple date loaf
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and extract.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Add dry ingredients. Add dates.
Stir in dry ingredients alternately with reserved juice and 1/4 cup water.
Fold in cherries.
Pour in greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 55 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: peas with water chestnuts
directions: Add peas and sugar to boiling water in a large saucepan. Bring to boiling, gently separating peas with a fork.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Drain peas.
Add remaining ingredients and toss lightly to mix well.
Reheat gently.
Makes 12 servings.

title: squash surprise
directions: Cook squash in small amount of water until tender; drain and mash.
Season to taste.
Stir in remaining ingredients, reserving half the cornbread which has been mixed with the butter.
Line a casserole with reserved cornbread.
Set aside enough cornbread to sprinkle on top.
Fill casserole with squash mixture; top with remaining cornbread.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
May be prepared the day before and baked when needed.
Delicious!

title: greek style potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes, cool and peel; cut into quarters.
Put in baking dish and add oil, oregano, salt and pepper.
Bake in 350° oven until lightly browned, about 30 minutes.
Garnish with parsley. Serves 4.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Cake:
Mix flour, 2 cups
sugar, eggs, vanilla, salt, baking soda and pineapple well by hand.
Bake in 13 x 10-inch sheet pan for 30 minutes.

title: hamburg dish
directions: Brown lightly the hamburg adding chopped onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve with vegetables for a nice hot meal.

title: fruits royale
directions: Drain fruit well.
Stir sugar and ginger into sour cream in a medium-sized bowl.
Fold in drained fruit.
Spoon into four dessert dishes.
Chill.
Top with toasted almonds.

title: cheesecake supreme
directions: Crust:
Combine crushed crackers, nuts and cinnamon.
Stir in margarine or butter.
Reserve 1/4 cup of the crumb mixture for topping, if desired.
Press remaining onto bottom and about 2 inches up sides of an 8 or 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: jiffy rhubarb dessert
directions: In a greased 9 x 9-inch pan, spread the rhubarb.
Sprinkle over evenly the sugar, jello and cake mix.
Gently pour over the 1 cup water.
Drizzle over all the melted margarine.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve warm or cold.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray oblong cake pan with Pam.
Spread coconut and pecans evenly in bottom of the pan.
Mix cake mix as directed on box; spread over coconut and pecans.
Mix the cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar together; drop by spoonfuls over cake batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: hawaiian baked chicken
directions: Rinse chicken.
Place in a baking or broiling pan.
Pour pineapple over chicken liberally.
Sprinkle on the Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Then, place slices of green pepper on each piece of chicken.
Bake at 325° for about one hour.
Can be served over rice.

title: gooey cake
directions: Mix together yellow cake mix, 1 egg and butter and pat in 9 x 13 pan (greased or sprayed with Pam). Then mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar and beat for 3 minutes, then pour mix over top of cake mix, egg and butter that is patted in pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Then ENJOY!

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Melt margarine in heavy kettle.
Add onion and cook until soft.
Add ground beef and garlic and stir until lightly browned. Stir in flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms and cook for 5 minutes. Add soup and simmer 10 minutes more.
Stir in sour cream and serve over cooked noodles.
Start noodles first and both will be done together.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and spread over split rolls.
Top with ham and cheese.
Replace tops.
(These may be frozen at this point.)
Wrap in foil and heat 10 minutes at 400°.
Serve immediately.

title: cheesy broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli by package directions; drain and set aside. Combine rice, soup, milk, cheese, salt and pepper.
Heat until cheese is melted and ingredients are well blended, then add onion, celery, water chestnuts and broccoli.
Stir thoroughly.
Place in a lightly greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish and heat in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes.
Fifteen minutes before removing from oven, cover top with finely crushed cracker crumbs.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add shortening, cheese and milk. Stir until soft.
Beat 15 strokes.
Drop by tablespoons onto greased pan.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 14 large biscuits.
Place in ring around meat.

title: brownies
directions: Stir cocoa and baking soda in mixing bowl.
Blend in 1/3 cup vegetable oil.
Add boiling water; stir until mixture thickens. Stir in sugar, eggs and remaining 1/3 cup oil.
Stir until smooth. Add flour, vanilla and salt; blend completely.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan or two 8-inch pans.
Bake at 350° (325° for glass pans) for 30 minutes for 13 x 9-inch pan; 25 minutes for 8-inch pans.

title: mexican pecan candy
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and cook to soft ball stage.
Add marshmallows cut in half.
Cool.
Then add vanilla and beat into mixture until smooth and begins to harden.
Add chopped pecans and drop on waxed paper.

title: holiday fruit salad
directions: Reserve the pineapple juice.
Cut up all fruit into bite size pieces and pour the reserved pineapple juice over it.
Chill before serving.
You can also top with coconut or slivered almonds for a pretty garnish, if you like.

title: cheese pastries
directions: Crumble or mash the Feta cheese with a fork.
Add the grated Parmesan cheese, parsley, eggs and pepper.

title: baked cheese and tomato fondue
directions: Make fondue day before serving.
In small bowl, cream 1/3 cup margarine with the garlic and 1/2 teaspoon mustard until well blended.
Remove ends of bread; cut loaf into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Spread one side of each with butter mixture.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix well.
Pat in large pizza or 11 x 15-inch jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool completely.

title: barbecue pecans
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix pecans, butter and sauces.
Put on cookie sheet; cook 20 minutes.
Stir every 5 minutes.
Take out of oven; sprinkle generously with seasoned salt, onion salt, garlic salt and lemon pepper.
Any other salt you like can be used.

title: cheese sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Using a fork; mix cheese, sausage and biscuit mix.
Shape into balls; place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: chicken dip
directions: Heat mixture; stir and serve with chips.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into fourths with scissors.
Shake biscuits in a bag with white sugar and cinnamon.
Layer biscuits into greased tube pan.
Sprinkle chopped nuts between layers.
Melt the brown sugar and oleo and boil for 1 minute.
Pour over biscuits. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before removing from pan.
To serve, just pinch off a piece and eat with fingers.
Monkey see! Monkey do!

title: sausage cheese quiche
directions: Fry sausage, breaking it apart as it cooks, drain well. Sprinkle into bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan with cheese, onions and peppers over sausage.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over cheese and sausage.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes. Let stand at least 5 minutes before serving.

title: mushroom-cheese dip
directions: Melt oleo in large skillet.
Add diced mushrooms and cook until liquid evaporates.
Cool to room temperature.
Beat salt, cheeses and sauce in large bowl.
Stir in cooked mushrooms and raw green onions.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: corn chowder
directions: Boil smoked shoulder bone and onions.
Reduce to medium heat and cook for 1 1/4 hours.
Add potatoes and cook on medium-high heat for 20 minutes.
Add corn.
Boil and then turn to low.
Add evaporated milk.
Season with pepper.

title: turkey barbecue
directions: Cook and stir celery, onion and green pepper in oleo in medium skillet over medium heat until lightly browned. Add remaining ingredients except buns. Reduce heat to low and simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Spoon turkey barbecue on bottom halves of buns. Cover with the top halves.

title: strawberry punchbowl cake
directions: Mix sugar and milk together.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip, mix well.
Break cake into medium size pieces.
Add to mixture and toss lightly, coating the cake well.

title: fettucine and veggies
directions: Saute mushrooms and garlic in margarine.
Stir in vegetables of your choice.
Set aside.
In blender, blend egg and Ricotta cheese. Add milk and Parmesan cheese.
Blend well.
Add egg mixture to vegetable mixture.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Toss with cooked fettucine. Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: smoky barbecue sauce
directions: Combine in a saucepan.
Heat until well blended.
Very good mixed with ground chuck cooked as for Sloppy Joes or chopped roast pork on buns.

title: hormel chili dip
directions: Put in crock-pot on high 1 1/2 hours (stir).
Turn on low for 2 hours.
Use tortilla chips for the dip.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until firm in the middle.

title: fresh apple bread(yields 2 loaves)
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs, apples and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture.
Add nuts and mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.
Serve hot with butter.

title: fish bundles
directions: Arrange fillets in baking pan.
Stir together spaghetti sauce mix, vinegar, oil, tomatoes, pepper and cucumber.
Spread mixture over fish.
Sprinkle with croutons.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: dried cherry scones
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a bowl.
Cut in 6 tablespoons butter with two knives or a pastry blender until the mixture looks like fine meal.
In a separate bowl, mix together egg, buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix liquid ingredients slowly with dry ingredients.
Use fingers or a fork. Add dried fruit (cherries, cranberries, raisins, etc.).
Pat into 8-inch diameter disc on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken vegetable with rice soup
directions: Heat first 3 ingredients in a stockpot.
Do not boil. Add remaining ingredients. Reduce heat. Cook until vegetables are tender.
Serve with whole wheat rolls.
Noodles may be used in place of rice.
Yields a pot full of goodness.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion, drain, then beat lightly with mixer. Add egg and season.
Combine with mayonnaise and cheese.
Pour into buttered casserole and top with seasoned bread crumbs.
Bake in medium oven 1/2 hour until bubbly.

title: quick chili casserole
directions: Mix and heat chili, corn, and taco seasoning. Pour into a 9 x 13 pan. Mix cornbread as directed on package directions. Pour over chili mixture. Bake at 375° until cornbread is done.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli according to package.
Drain and arrange in oblong dish.
Layer chicken on top of broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs and margarine; sprinkle over all.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°. Garnish with pimento strips.

title: savannah red rice
directions: Fry bacon dry; remove from pan.
Saute onion in bacon drippings; add other ingredients.
Cook on top of stove 10 minutes.
Pour into casserole dish, covered, and bake approximately 1 hour and 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Add beaten eggs, milk and corn. Mix well.
Melt butter in pan or dish and pour in corn mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Test for done by putting a table knife in center.
If knife comes out without corn mixture, it is done.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Blend on low 2 minutes or mix by hand 3 minutes. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet 2-inches apart.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown on top.

title: peach jelly
directions: Cook 20 minutes; add 2 small boxes orange jello.
Cook 3 minutes.

title: barbecued limas and ham
directions: Heat beans
with
salt	in
boiling water for 1 minute. Lower heat;
simmer
for 1 hour, until done.
Drain, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Heat
oven
to
Layer
beans, ham and onion
in an ungreased casserole.
Stir remaining ingredients, plus liquid together; pour over beans.	Bake for 1 hour.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Grease 18 x 12-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle rice in bottom, then mix in soup, broth and water.
Place chicken breasts on top. Season with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered. More water may be added, if necessary.

title: aunt sue's peanut butter balls
directions: Melt butter and pour over graham crackers.
Add peanut butter and sugar.
Shape into balls.
Put on cookie sheet, then chill. Melt chocolate chips and wax; dip chilled balls into chocolate. Cool on wax paper.

title: ham and cheese buns
directions: Cut ham and cheese in small pieces.
Add onion, eggs and olives.
Mix mayonnaise and chili sauce.
Mix all together.
Spread on rolls, then wrap in foil.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 40 minutes at 400°.

title: neiman marcus cake
directions: Mix well cake mix, eggs, and butter.
Press in greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients well.
Pour on top of cake mix.
Sprinkle top with chopped pecans.
Bake in a 350 degree oven 35 - 40 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello with water.
Add pineapple, nuts and strawberries. Pour half of mixture in casserole dish, let this congeal.
Spread sour cream and add remaining mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: pizza fondue
directions: Brown onion and meat in shortening in the fondue pot on high heat.
Reduce heat to medium.
Mix corn starch and seasonings into pizza sauce.
Add sauce to other mixture when mixture thickens and bubbles.
Add cheese by thirds.
Stir well after adding each. Dunkers:
Toasted English muffin cubes or toasted garlic and/or plain bread cubes.
May be served over slices of bread as main dish.

title: tire blackened possum
directions: This is a naturally fatty meat and has now been pretenderized. I, none-the-less, recommend a good soaking in salt water and a thorough rinsing to get rid of all the possible floaters (be sure to scrape as much hair off as possible).
Bake at 450° for 3 hours with the rest of the ingredients.

title: chicken lush
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together. Cover with buttered bread crumbs and slivered toasted almonds, if desired.
Bake in uncovered casserole 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: side salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese and sugar.
Pour over lettuce, crumbled bacon and broken cauliflower.
Toss.

title: lemon garlic chicken
directions: In a nonstick skillet, saute minced garlic and margarine.
Add chicken cubes and brown lightly.
Add lemon juice and cook, covered, for 10 minutes.
Add thawed peas and cook, covered, an additional 5 minutes or until done.
Serves 8.
Serve with rice.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Beat together cream cheese and sour cream.
Stir in lemon juice, green onions, pepper, milk and shrimp.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 4 hours.
Top with almonds.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuit dough into quarters.
Mix cinnamon and sugar in separate bowl.
Roll each biscuit quarter in cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Place in ungreased Bundt pan.
Melt butter.
Add leftover cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Dribble mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: crab muffins
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Spread on 8 English muffin halves.
Broil 4 minutes.

title: pineapple icing
directions: Cook for 10 minutes on low heat, stirring often.

title: cinnamon breakfast rolls
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Pour nuts in bottom of pan; place frozen rolls on top of nuts.
Melt butter, brown sugar and cinnamon together.
Sprinkle instant pudding over frozen rolls, then pour melted mixture over top.
Let rise overnight.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery.
Heat broccoli in water; bring to a boil.
Add Cheez Whiz, butter and soup.
Stir until dissolved. Add rice, onion and celery.
Put in a 2-quart baking dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese pudding
directions: Beat eggs, milk and salt together.
Cut bread in cubes.
In a buttered baking dish put a layer of bread and a layer of cheese, ending with layer of cheese.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix well. Makes 2 layers.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: cream of cucumber soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Heat slowly until it reaches a boil and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Garnish with chopped dill.

title: creamed cabbage baked
directions: Boil
cabbage
in
salt water 8 minutes.
Drain out all water. Add 1 cup cream white sauce and 3/4 cup grated cheese. In baking dish,
put
layer
of
cabbage and cheese sauce; add seasoning. Place crackers
and
butter
on
top with salt and pepper.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients, except vinegar in blender.
Start at medium and then go to high speed to blend very well.
Then open hole in lid and add vinegar very slowly while continuing blending. Will be thick and creamy and doesn't separate.
Put in jar or bottle and refrigerate.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream 1/2 sugar with shortening and flavoring.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture and milk.
Beat egg whites and add remaining 1/2 sugar then fold into cake mixture after coconut has been added to cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Chill and serve.

title: stuffin burgers
directions: Combine stuffing mix and milk; when softened, add remaining ingredients.
Shape into patties; broil or grill.
Toast your buns for added taste.

title: linguini salad
directions: Cook linguini; drain.
Mix all ingredients together and marinate 24 hours.

title: old fashioned syrup cake
directions: Mix sugar, butter and syrup.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Mix alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla.
Bake in tube pan at 350° about 45 minutes or until done.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium mixing bowl; mix thoroughly. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Served with sliced tart apples (such as Granny Smith or Cortland) that have been dipped in lemon juice to prevent browning.

title: coconut supreme pound cake
directions: Cream oleo.
Add sugar gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Add flour with milk.
Blend in flavorings, coconut and pineapple; mix well.
Pour into tube pan. Bake for 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients. Wet the bottom of the skillet. Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: eggplant appetizer
directions: Dip eggplant fingers into Egg Beater liquid and then into crumbs.
Make sure they are covered on all sides.
Line up on ungreased pans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until tender.

title: mini turkey ham quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle ham and cheese over pie shell.
In a small bowl, combine egg and milk; pour evenly into pie shell. On cookie sheet, bake quiche 20 to 25 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Yield: 2 servings.

title: the world's best chocolate chip cookie
directions: Cream together butter and both sugars.
Add 4 eggs, vanilla and milk separately.
Add flour and oatmeal (that after being measured is 5 cups, is put into blender until it turns to powder). Add salt, baking powder and baking soda to flour mixture.
Add flour mixture to butter mixture slowly.
Add chocolate chips. Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet in a preheated 375° oven until light golden.

title: southern fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well (except shell); pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in preheated oven at 300° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: saute mushrooms with garlic
directions: In large skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat.
Add garlic, thyme and parsley and stir briefly.
Do not let garlic brown.
Increase heat to high and add mushrooms.
Stir and mix well with garlic, thyme and parsley.
Reduce heat to medium.
The mushrooms will exude a lot of water.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes until it has evaporated.
Add salt and pepper.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and chill.

title: john's old english turkey - chicken stuffing
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Add water. Mix thoroughly until quite moist. Either stuff fowl or place in container and cook with fowl.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in flour, baking powder, vanilla, Hershey's syrup and nuts.
Put in cookie sheet (10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch).
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, combine eggs, oat flakes, onion, Italian seasoning, green pepper, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Mix well.
Add ground beef and ground turkey.
Blend well.
Put into pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
You may top with Cheddar cheese.

title: basic pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Let "proof" for 5 minutes.

title: a happy day
directions: Measure words carefully.
Add understanding, time and patience.
Cook on the front burner.
Keep temperature low; do not boil.
Add humor and personality.
Season to taste with spice of life.
Serve in individual molds.
This recipe is guaranteed never to fail.

title: chunky soup
directions: Heat until boiling 2 1/2 quarts water, beef base, beef broth, butter, tomato juice, sugar and 1/4 cup salt.
Cut vegetables into small cubes.
Cook separately in salted water, then add to mixture.
Take a little less than 2 quarts flour and add enough water to make a smooth paste to thicken soup.
Season hamburger with salt and pepper (if not already seasoned).
Add onions; fry in flour and butter.
Mix hamburger and drippings with soup.
Some beef chunks can be added instead of all hamburger.
Cold pack for 2 hours.
Pressure cook for 40 minutes at 10 pounds.
Makes about 30 quarts.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix boiling water, oatmeal and margarine and let stand 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and stir by hand.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in an 8 x 10-inch pan.

title: lemon cheese pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Cool until just begins to set.
Cream together cheese, sugar and lemon flavoring.
Add gelatin.
Mix well.
Whip milk according to directions on can. Fold whipped milk into gelatin mixture.
Pour filling into crust. Chill several hours or overnight.
Garnish.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix all together well and refrigerate.

title: quick lo-fat herb spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion in vegetable spray (i.e., Pam); add garlic.
Stir in tomato paste, water, oregano and basil, sugar, salt and pepper. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer uncovered for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over spaghetti; sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Put raw hamburger in chunks on bottom of 2-quart casserole dish. Season with pepper and salt. Put 1-inch cubes of raw potatoes over hamburger. Put corn over potatoes, then place pats of butter on top. Put on casserole cover. Bake in microwave about 25 minutes, stirring gently once or twice.

title: no peek beef casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish and cover tightly. Bake in a 300° oven for 3 hours. DO NOT PEEK! Serve over noodles or yellow rice. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: calico beans
directions: Drain beans and save liquid.
Brown bacon and hamburger. Saute onions.
Combine beans, hamburger, bacon and onions. Combine remaining ingredients and mix.
Pour into pan.
If it looks too dry, add some of bean liquid.
Bake at 350° for at least 1 hour.

title: make-ahead eggs benedict
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, arrange muffins, cut side up.
Place 2 bacon slices on each muffin half.
Half fill 10-inch skillet with water; bring just to boiling.
Break one egg into a dish and carefully slide egg into water.
Simmer, uncovered, 3 minutes or until just set.
Remove eggs with a slotted spoon. Repeat until all eggs are done, placing one egg atop each muffin stack.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Combine and mix cake mix and eggs.
Stir in cherry pie filling.
Mix well until blended.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Frost as desired.

title: homestyle potato salad
directions: In large bowl, combine mayonnaise, vinegar, salt, sugar and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover; chill.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: In a large bowl, mix together the milk, salt and 1/2 cup of sugar.
Add yeast, eggs and 1/2 cup melted margarine.
Slowly add flour until sticky.
Cover with damp towel; let rise until doubled in bulk.
Divide dough in half; roll on floured board to 1/4 inch thick.

title: pizza swirls
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees.
Generously coat a rimmed baking sheet with cooking spray.

title: banana cake
directions: Stir shortening and dry ingredients.
Add 1/4 c. milk and mashed bananas.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs and remaining milk. Beat 2 more minutes.
Bake at 375 degrees about 30 minutes.
Use 13 x 9 inch pan.

title: vegetable bread
directions: Saute vegetables in margarine 3 to 5 minutes until tender.
Add fried and crumbled bacon.
Separate 1 can of biscuits into 3 to 4 layer sections and layer in Bundt pan (bottom and sides).
Sprinkle cheese and vegetables and cover with more layers of biscuits.
Do this 2 to 3 times, then put one more layer of biscuits over this mixture and fold over edges of biscuits from sides and middle. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until brown.

title: nut pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; add sugar gradually.
Add crackers, baking powder and vanilla.
Stir in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in greased pan.
Cool. Cover with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with toasted coconut.

title: cinnamon spiced pecans
directions: Beat egg white with cold water.
Pour over pecan halves and stir to coat.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Sprinkle over nuts and mix well.
Spread pecans on buttered 10 x 13-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: three bean pasta salad
directions: Cook the pasta according to the directions on the package. Drain the artichoke hearts and water chestnuts and chop into medium size chunks.
Add the drained and cooled pasta to the remainder of the ingredients; mix thoroughly and top with the cheese.
Salad should be refrigerated for at least an hour prior to serving.

title: special k bars
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a boil, add peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour over cereal.
Pat in pan.
Melt chips on low microwave, heat and frost.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar slowly while beating.
Add remaining ingredients, adding melted butter last.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased and floured baking sheet.
Bake about 15 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: skillet pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in 10-inch skillet until brown on both sides. Sprinkle with pepper.
Remove from skillet.
Mix potatoes, sauce mix and the remaining ingredients in skillet.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat.
Place pork chops on top of potato mixture.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: see's fudge candy
directions: Put first five ingredients into a large bowl.
Put sugar and milk into a large pan.
Stir and bring to a boil.
Pour all ingredients into boiled mixture and stir until melted. Pour into buttered pan about 1 inch thick.
Cool 2 to 3 hours before cutting.
Makes approximately 5 pounds.

title: hungarian potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into cubes.
Set aside.
In large saucepan, melt butter.
Add onion and saute 5 minutes.
Add potatoes, water and bouillon.
Cover; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium and cook until potatoes are tender.
Pour contents of saucepan into container of electric blender.
Holding lid on securely, blend until smooth.
Return to saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat through.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: *To make buttermilk, add 1 tablespoon lemon juice to a cup of milk; let sit for about 15 minutes.

title: oven hash potatoes
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex baking dish melt 1/2 of the stick of margarine.
Pour hash brown potatoes over margarine.
(Leave at room temperature for a few minutes or thaw in microwave for a few minutes.)
Put on salt, pepper and parsley.
Mix soup, sour cream, cheese and onion.
Pour on top of potatoes.
Melt other half stick of margarine and pour over crushed corn flakes.
Mix together and put on top of the casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven 45 minutes. Serves a large number of people.

title: texas millionaires
directions: Melt caramel candy, water and margarine in a double boiler. Mix in pecan halves and vanilla.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on buttered tray to cool.
Heat chocolate bar and paraffin in double boiler until melted and smooth.
Dip patties into chocolate until coated well.
Drop on wax paper.

title: pumpkin muffins(fat-free; sugar-free)
directions: Mix together at medium speed.
Bake in muffin pan sprayed with Pam.
Makes approximately one dozen medium size muffins.

title: berry sparkler
directions: Spoon the strawberry puree into the bottom of a tulip champagne glass.
Fill with champagne.
Float a strawberry and mint sprig on top.
Makes 1 drink.

title: pineapple slaw
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; chill at least 1 hour.
Just before serving, combine mayonnaise, lemon juice and pepper; stir. Fold in whipped cream.
Pour over slaw; toss gently.
Garnish with chopped pecans.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fruit nut crunch
directions: Spread pineapple over bottom of
lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Toss fruit with 1/4 cup
sugar
and
lemon juice. Layer over the pineapple.
Sprinkle dry cake mix
over fruit. Pour butter and remaining sugar over top.
Bake at 350°
for
50 to 60 minutes.
After it has baked 20 minutes, cut through to bottom
of dish to allow juice to rise to top.
Serves 12.

title: rice jambalaya
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add sausage.
Add chicken, onion, green pepper and garlic.
Cook and stir until chicken is cooked.
Stir in tomatoes, okra, sauce and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover.
Remove from heat when done.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
The day before, combine chicken broth, celery and cheese.
Refrigerate.
Before baking, add eggs, soup and 3 cups of cracker crumbs.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: play doh
directions: Mix flour, salt, oil, cream of tartar and water.
Cook on medium-high heat, stirring always until mixture turns loose of sides of pan and then looks like white play doh.
Divide into 4 small balls and add a different color of food coloring to each ball.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt peanut butter and margarine over low heat.
Stir in vanilla and powdered sugar.
Mix well; shape into balls.
Melt semi-sweet morsels and wax in double boiler.
Last, dip balls into chocolate.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix all together and beat thoroughly, then dissolve 4 teaspoons soda in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir this in slowly.
Add 5 1/2 to 6 cups flour or enough to make dough easy to handle. Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet and bake at 375° until done.

title: chile rellenos
directions: Cut cheese into strips and press into chiles.
Dredge with flour.
Whip egg whites until stiff.
Beat yolk, salt and 1/4 cup flour.
Fold in egg whites.
Heat oil in skillet (2 inches).
Dip chiles in egg mixture.
Place in skillet.
Fry until brown, turn and fry on other side.

title: baby food cake
directions: Mix together and cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: islander cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese and pineapple with mixer.
Stir in onion, green pepper, salt and 1/2 cup pecans.
Roll into one large ball, 2 loop or fill a scooped-out fresh pineapple half.
Roll or top with remaining pecans.

title: whole wheat bread in a bag
directions: Combine 1 cup all-purpose flour, undissolved yeast, sugar, dry milk and salt in a 1 gallon heavy-duty Ziploc freezer bag. Squeeze upper part of bag to force out air.
Shake and work bag with fingers to blend ingredients.
Add hot water and oil to dry ingredients.
Reseal bag and mix thoroughly.
Gradually add enough remaining all-purpose flour to make a stiff dough that pulls away from the bag.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil ingredients to 238° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat; add 1 1/2 cups Spanish peanuts.
Return to heat and cook to 300°, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add 2 teaspoons baking soda.
Stir thoroughly and quickly.
Pour on buttered cookie sheet.
Cool, then crack brittle and remove from cookie sheet.
Place in an airtight container.

title: zesty halibut salad
directions: Cook halibut steaks with onion and celery in small amount of water.
Cool.
Flake and remove all bones.
Mix fish with the rest of the ingredients, seasoning to taste with salt and pepper. Serves 4 to 6. Shape in a fish mold if desired or serve on lettuce leaf.

title: shrimp dip
directions: In a processor, add onion; chop fine.
Add drained shrimp, 2 teaspoons horseradish and cream cheese.
Blend together.
Serve on bed of lettuce.
Mix catsup with 2 teaspoons horseradish; pour on top of the shrimp mixture.
Wheat crackers around the bed of lettuce goes really well.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar, shortening, butter, egg yolk and vanilla in large bowl.
Mix in flour and salt to form dough.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Beat egg white slightly.
Dip dough in whites, then cover with nuts.
Place on cookie sheet, 1 inch apart.
Press thumb deeply into center of each.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes at 350°.
After cookies cool, fill center with jelly.

title: banana pudding
directions: Separate egg yolks from whites.
Mix yolks with flour and sugar; then add milk.
Cook until you have a pudding texture. Line a baking dish with wafers.
Pour 1/2 of pudding over wafers; cut up 1 1/2 bananas and put over pudding.
Repeat with wafers, pudding and bananas.
Beat egg whites until peaks form.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar gradually and 1 drop vanilla extract.
Pile onto the pudding and brown topping in oven.

title: chicken stuffing bake
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan over high heat, heat 3/4 cup of the milk and margarine to scalding.
In large bowl, pour hot milk mixture over stuffing.
Toss to mix well.
Pat half of the stuffing mixture into a buttered 12 x 8-inch baking dish.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix in order given and beat well.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Use greased 13 x 9 x 2 1/2-inch pan.
While cake is hot, poke it full of holes and pour glaze over it.

title: corn bread
directions: Bake in 450° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Roll in balls and cook at 350° until brown, about 10 minutes.

title: marinated asparagus
directions: Bring to boil.
Pour over asparagus.
Refrigerate 2 hours. Keeps for days.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding, then add remaining ingredients and mix.
Chill.

title: georgia peach chutney
directions: Combine all ingredients in Dutch oven.
Bring to boil and simmer uncovered for 1 hour, 15 minutes or until mixture is thickened and deep brown.
Pour hot chutney into hot clean canning jars leaving 1/2-inch head space.
Remove air bubbles.
Wipe jar rims.
Adjust lids and rings.
Process for 10 minutes in boiling water bath.
Remove jars from water.
Serving size = 1 tablespoon. Calories per serving = 23.

title: chicken in orange sauce with mushrooms
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Brown in margarine in a large skillet.
Remove chicken to paper toweling.
Wipe, trim and quarter mushrooms.
Add to skillet and cook until
golden.
Remove and set aside for use later.
Stir onion into remaining drippings in skillet and cook for a few minutes.
Add orange juice and sugar.
Cook over high heat until mixture is reduced by half.
Lower heat and stir in consomme. Arrange browned chicken in sauce.
Cover and cook over low heat until tender, about 1 hour.
Add mushrooms during last 10 minutes of cooking.
Makes 8 servings.

title: southern fried grits
directions: Boil
grits,
and 1 teaspoon salt until thick.	Stir in cheese and parsley.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with plastic wrap;
freeze
2 hours.
Cut grits into rounds.
Beat eggs	with 2 tablespoons of water.
Dip grits in and coat with crumbs.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in a large skillet.
Fry until golden brown.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix ingredients.
Let rise until double in size.
Punch down and make into 12 balls.
Pull or roll balls to about 6 to 8 inches long.
Roll in butter, then cinnamon and sugar.
Tie into knot and place into pan to rise.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: mint tea
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Cook until clear. Remove from heat, let mint stay in until it has cooled.
Then boil 2 cups water and steep tea bags until water is cool.
Remove tea bags and mint and mix the two together.
Add enough water to make a gallon.
Serve iced!

title: fried squash
directions: Cut squash in thin slices.
Pour enough can milk over squash to dampen them and mix.
Add flour and meal, then mix altogether. Sprinkle salt and pepper for taste.
Deep fry squash.

title: apple brown betty
directions: Combine apples, raisins, walnuts, honey, 1/4 cup brown sugar, lemon juice, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and nutmeg in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch microwave-safe dish.

title: mama tora's hamburger-meat loaf mix
directions: Shape into patties; broil for 10 minutes on each side or until done.
Or shape into loaf and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: nutty cream cheese bars
directions: Mix well the cake mix, pecans and melted butter.
Press evenly in greased and floured 9x
13-inch pan.
Mix softened cream cheese and brown sugar until smooth.
Spread on top of cake mix and sprinkle with remaining pecans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool, refrigerate, enjoy!

title: chocolate caramel cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake according to directions on box.
Pour half of mix in bottom of pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
In a double boiler, melt caramels with sweetened milk thoroughly.
When cake is done and caramels are melted, pour over cake, not touching sides of pan.
Pour rest of batter over caramel mixture and finish baking.
When cake has cooled, mix dry package of Dream Whip and Cool Whip (thawed) together and pour over top.

title: corn for freezer
directions: Boil lightly for 10 minutes.
Stir often; cool.
Put in Ziploc freezer bags and freeze.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix together.
Put into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: dacey cinnamon cookies
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar and cinnamon.
Beat in egg, flour and salt.
Refrigerate dough overnight.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve
yeast
in
warm
water.
Mix with buttermilk. Cut shortening in dry ingredients. Add liquid.	Put in plastic bag and put in refrigerator
until you want to bake.
Take out as much as you want at a time.
Roll out and cut.
Dip or turn in liquid margarine.	Let rise
for
hour. Then bake in a 425° oven for 12 to 15
minutes. Dough will keep a week in the refrigerator.

title: prize winning pound cake
directions: Mix together flour and butter.
Work until creamy.
Add eggs and sugar.
Mix well.
Add baking powder, salt, butter, flavoring, lemon and vanilla extract.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into large tube pan.
Bake 1 hour in 300° oven.
Increase heat to 325° and bake 15 to 20 minutes longer.

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine in large bowl and chill for at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: hot crabmeat salad
directions: Combine flaked crab, chopped almonds, chopped hard boiled eggs, pimentos and peas or beans; mix with white sauce made from milk, butter and flour, seasoned with onion and dash of Tabasco sauce.
Put in buttered pan.
Cover with bread crumbs and bake in pan of water at 350°.

title: chicken divan
directions: Spread chicken in buttered casserole dish.
Spread broccoli and mushrooms over chicken.
Mix soups and mayonnaise.
Spread over all.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese over all.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add beaten eggs; blend well.
Add flour, mashed banana and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Don't open door until done!

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake in 10-inch buttered pie dish for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Chop stems.
Set caps and stems aside.
Over medium heat, cook sausage until brown.
Save two tablespoons of drippings from sausage; drain the rest.
Finely chop the sausage.
Cook stems in drippings; stir frequently. Remove from heat; stir in sausage, cheese and bread crumbs.
Fill caps.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°.

title: lasagne
directions: Fix the night before or early in the day.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix butter and sugar; add eggs, pumpkin and water.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Pour into 3 bread pans.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery, onions, parsley flakes and bouillon cubes with water until tender.
Blend flour with small amount of milk; stir into tender vegetables.
Add remaining milk.
Add cubed cheese and set off stove.
Cover and let cheese melt.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Dice cooked chicken meat.
Thicken broth with a paste made of flour and fat seasoned with salt and pepper.
Fill a baking dish with alternate layers of crackers, chicken and potatoes.
Cover with crumbs. Pour in a gravy, dot with bits of butter.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° to 400° oven.
Serves 3.

title: hot bean-venison dip
directions: Saute
onions
in butter, then add meat and brown.
Add remaining
ingredients,
saving some of the cheese for the top and simmer
10	to 15 minutes.	Pour into a casserole dish and top with
remaining
cheese.
Bake
until cheese is melted. Serve with tostados or corn chips.

title: hard tack candy
directions: Line pan with foil and butter.
Ridge sides 8 x 8 x 2-inch. Butter 1-quart saucepan.
Combine sugar, syrup and water.
Bring to boil; stir until sugar is dissolved continuously.
Cook until hard stage.
Remove from heat; add flavor and coloring.
Pour into prepared pan.
When set around edges, take foil out and cut; work fast.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Cut with scissors.

title: grandma carter's macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil pasta to cook as directed on box, usually 12 minutes at a rolling boil.
Drain in colander.
Rinse pasta thoroughly with cold water to prevent finished product from becoming gummy.
Cube cheese into small pieces.
Cut whole tomatoes into smaller pieces.

title: punch
directions: Mix juices, Kool-Aid, jello and sugar in 1-gallon container. Pour one half of mixture in another gallon container.
Finish filling both gallon containers with water.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Heat water and margarine to boiling.
Stir in Bisquick all at once.
Stir over heat until mixture leaves side of pan and forms ball (about 1 minute).
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, beating until mixture is smooth.
Mix in cheese and seasoning.
Drop dough by teaspoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until puffed and light golden brown (18 to 20 minutes).

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Soften margarine at room temperature.
Add sugar and cream together.
Add flour and eggs; beat well.
Stir in butter, milk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: naomi chocolate fudge
directions: In large mixing bowl put Hershey bits, Marshmallow Creme, vanilla and nuts.
In large heavy pan or Dutch oven, put the sugar, canned milk and butter.
Cook together, after a rolling boil, for 6 minutes only.
Stir with wooden spoon all the time it is cooking.
Pour over first mixture.
Stir and mix well.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients in blender. Pour into a buttered 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes. Test with inserted knife in center to check doneness.

title: spiced cider
directions: Prepare cider using a large automatic coffee maker. Substitute the cider for water.
Place remaining ingredients in coffee basket with filter and brew.
Makes 2 quarts.
The aroma is fantastic!

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until done; reserve the chicken broth.
Debone chicken and cut into pieces.
Saute celery and onions in butter until done.
Cook spaghetti in the reserved broth until done.
Add celery, onions, soup, cheese and chicken to spaghetti and broth. Cook until cheese is melted.
Serve hot.

title: white trash
directions: Melt white bark.
Pour over 10 cups dry mix.
Mix and spread on wax paper.
Refrigerate until firm.
Break up and enjoy.
Dry ingredients can be varied to suit your tastes.

title: beef and chicken fajitas
directions: Cut sirloin tip steak into thin strips.
Cut chicken into thin strips.
Cut up onion, tomatoes and pepper into strips (not chopped into small pieces).
Cook steak and chicken until meat is almost done.
Separate meat in half.
Put tomatoes, peppers and onions in center to cook.
Let it cook on low heat until peppers and onions are tender.
Stirring vegetables helps season meat.
Serve on flour (brown) tortillas.	Top with sour cream, lettuce and tomatoes (optional).

title: easy christmas punch
directions: Mix gelatin with boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Then add cold water and fruit juices.
Pour over ice and add ginger ale just before serving.

title: cole slaw
directions: Pour dressing over cabbage mixture and let stand 2 to 4 hours before using.

title: mom's baked rice
directions: Stir all together in greased casserole.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Stir every 15 minutes for first hour.
May add raisins and nuts.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream 3/4 cup sugar and butter.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Stir in flour, salt, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Stir into butter mixture.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Mix 2 tablespoons of sugar and cinnamon together.
Roll 1-inch balls of dough in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 36 cookies.

title: peanut butter chocolate chunk cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil. Position rack in center of oven.
In a medium bowl, using a portable mixer at low speed, beat together peanut butter and oil just until combined.
Add the eggs and beat until combined.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except margarine and pour into a greased baking dish.
Cut up margarine and arrange on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: manicotti
directions: Mix eggs, grated Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese, Ricotta and oregano together well.
Set aside.
Cook shells for about 10 minutes.
Drain.
Set on wax paper.
Separate and cook Italian sausage and crumble.
Mix both cans of tomato paste and seasonings to taste.
Stuff cooled shells with cheese mixture and lay on foil covered cookie sheets.
Pour tomato paste over shells, then put Italian sausage over tomato paste.
Cook at 400° until cheese in shells are melted, about 20 minutes.
Take out of oven and serve with Italian bread.
Recipe yields 10 servings.

title: yogurt sip
directions: Let peaches stand at room temperature for 10 minutes.
In a blender container, combine yogurt, peach juice and honey.
Add undrained peaches; cover.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into glass; top with nutmeg.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together brown sugar, cinnamon, oatmeal and butter.
Empty apples into 8 x 10-inch dish.
Top with oatmeal mix.
Bake at 350° until crisp.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cut eggplant in cubes.
Steam until tender.
Drain.
Add peppers sauted in fat.
Add tomatoes, slightly cooked.
Add other ingredients.
Top with bread crumbs, bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars; add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Beat.
Add oatmeal, coconut and gumdrops.
Roll in small balls.
Press with fork on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: no bake, no hassle caramel popcorn
directions: Mix all ingredients over stove. Stir until marshmallows are melted and sugar dissolved. Pour over popped corn, toss and serve. Yum, Yum.

title: russian salad
directions: Bring to a slow boil: marshmallows, gelatin, cream cheese and water.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; put enough mayonnaise in it to make stick together.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix and take 1 teaspoon of dough and roll into a ball.
Roll this in sugar.
They will flatten out while cooking.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and divide. Shape into 2 balls. Roll in chopped nuts, covering entire ball.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Use 2-quart casserole dish. Slice squash and steam until tender. Beat eggs and milk; add butter, salt, pepper and all but 1/2 cup of cheese. Next, add the squash and onion. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Sprinkle remaining cheese.

title: bacon dip
directions: Cook bacon, drain and crumble. Combine first 5 ingredients and beat at medium speed until smooth. Stir in bacon, serve with assorted crackers. Makes about one cup.

title: rotel potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a bowl, mix Ro-Tel tomatoes, cheese and cream of mushroom soups, water, onion, salt and pepper to taste. Pour mixture over potatoes in a greased baking dish. Place margarine slices on top and bake for 1 hour or until potatoes are fork-tender. (Cheese is salty enough.) Serve with cornbread or tortilla chips.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in the butter. Set aside 3/4 cup of this crumbly mixture.
Press the remainder of this mixture into a 9-inch pie pan.
Combine the apples, 3 tablespoons flour, 1 cup sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Arrange in the pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Then sprinkle with the reserved crumbs and continue to bake for 20 to 30 minutes longer until browned.

title: fig cake
directions: Stir together first 7 ingredients.
Stir in eggs, oil and buttermilk, blending well.
Add vanilla.
Fold in figs and nuts. Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Pierce top of cake with toothpick; drizzle Buttermilk Glaze over cake.

title: pea salad
directions: Drain peas; mix together all ingredients.
Chill thoroughly. Serve on lettuce.
Delicious!
Makes 4 (4 ounce) servings.

title: quick pizza casserole
directions: Cook beef in a skillet until browned, stirring to crumble. Drain well.
Spoon beef into an 8-inch square baking dish.
Top with pizza sauce and cheese.
Combine biscuit mix, milk and eggs; beat until smooth.
Pour mixture over casserole, covering evenly. Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: ham and cheese ribbons
directions: Stack in order 1 slice American cheese, ham, Muenster, ham, American, ham and Muenster, spreading 1/4 teaspoon horseradish between slices.
Trim edges.
Repeat to make another stack.
Cut 1 stack into 4 squares, then cut squares in half diagonally to form triangles.
Cut second stack into 3 strips and each strip into 3 squares.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: tiny holiday wreaths
directions: Combine marshmallows, butter, vanilla and food color (2 teaspoons is correct) in top of double boiler.
Heat over water until marshmallows and butter are melted, stirring frequently. Gradually stir in corn flakes.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.
With hands shape into tiny wreaths, about 1 1/2 to 2 inches in diameter.
Decorate with small red candies (tiny red hots or other small candies).
Makes 33 (2-inch) wreaths.
Instead of tiny wreaths, you can make one big holiday wreath.
Drop mixture with spoon in a circle onto waxed paper.
With hands, shape to make a 9-inch wreath.
Decorate with red candied cherries and silver dragees.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Combine ingredients and heat in microwave for 4 to 5 minutes (until cheese melts).
Serve hot with crackers.

title: johnny marzetti casserole
directions: Brown meat; add onions, peppers and celery.
Simmer.
Add soups and cheese.
Simmer until cheese is melted.
Add the cooked and drained noodles.
Mix well.
Put into 2 large casseroles. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fritters (banana or apple)
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients together. Combine milk and well-beaten egg and add to dry ingredients, beating constantly. The batter should be thick enough to coat fruit. Cut up 6 bananas. Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Dip in batter and fry in hot deep fat (Crisco). If apples are used - chop or dice small and sprinkle with slightly more sugar and bake. Taste for sweetness.

title: vanilla nut crumb crust
directions: In a bowl, combine vanilla wafer crumbs, nuts and melted margarine.
Press mixture into bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool and fill as desired.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Cook noodles in lightly salted water with 1 tablespoon salad oil until tender (al dente).
Strain.

title: grandma's dessert
directions: Mix cherry pie filling and pineapple in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle cake mix evenly on top of pie filling mixture.
Spread nuts on top of it.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: betty's pound cake(vanilla pound cake)
directions: Cream butter and shortening, add sugar gradually.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat until very light.
Sift flour, measure and add baking powder and salt, sift together.
Add flour alternately with milk, starting and ending with flour.
Add vanilla.
Bake in a large tube pan (which has been greased and floured) at 325°F for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown chuck; pour of excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve on buns.
Add cheese, if desired.
To reduce fat content, boil ground chuck in 2 to 3 cups water; rinse well in colander.
Put back in pan; add remaining ingredients. Simmer 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and fold into Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust.

title: apple pecan crisp
directions: Place mashed apples in 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Sprinkle brown sugar, salt and dry cake mix over the apples.
Slice margarine on top and then add the pecans.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream.

title: easy hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and chopped onion; drain. Add enchilada sauce and taco sauce. Spray casserole pan with Pam. Cover bottom of pan with corn chips. Add meat mixture. Cover with cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted, approximately 25 minutes.

title: swiss mocha mix
directions: Mix together and store in airtight container.
Use 1 to 2 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: crawfish and wine soup
directions: Over moderate heat, melt 1 Tbsp. margarine.
Add carrots green onions (saving some for garnish) and salt & pepper.
Cook, stirring occasionally, 3 minutes or until softened.
In a saucepan over moderate heat,
bring bouillon to a boil.
Add crawfish and vegetables and return to a boil.
Add cream, bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Heat and stir for 2 minutes.
Add wine and reduce liquid, stirring occasionally, 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve with cajun spice to taste.

title: quesadillas
directions: Place tortillas on flat baking pan. Chop olives, combine olives, cheese, picante sauce, snip cilantro and add to cheese mixture. Evenly spread 1/4 cup mixture over a tortilla pressing down firmly.

title: pumpkin corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
In separate bowl, combine sugar, cornmeal, butter and eggs and stir into flour mixture until blended.
Add pumpkin and corn. Pour into greased and floured 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour or more (usually 1 1/4 hours) until center tests firm.
Cool 15 minutes and remove from pan.
Let sit several hours before slicing.
This bread is delicious toasted with butter.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: cream cheese pumpkin bread
directions: Beat cheese, sugar and egg together, set aside.
Combine all dry ingredients, mix egg, water, butter and pumpkin into batter. Take out 2 cups.
Put the rest in loaf pan.
Add cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining 2 cups batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Brown onions, pepper and celery in margarine.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add tomato sauce and vinegar.
Cover, simmer for 10 minutes.
Add cooked shrimp and serve over rice.

title: apple relish
directions: Mix all ingredients and boil over high heat for 30 minutes. Allow to cool.

title: miss virginia's potatoes
directions: Mix potatoes, sugar, salt, eggs, margarine, milk and vanilla together and place in casserole dish.

title: soy marinade for beef, pork or poultry
directions: In a small bowl, combine ingredients.
Pour over meat of your choice.
Refrigerate 6 hours or overnight, turning occasionally. Remove meat from marinade; grill or broil as desired, basting frequently with marinade.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: blender custard pie
directions: Put all in blender; blend all for 5 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until knife inserted comes out clean.
Crusts forms at bottom, then the filling.

title: creamsicle delight
