directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add the first 3 ingredients.
Bring to boil again; stir to make smooth.
Let completely cool (may put in freezer for a while), but not firmly set.
Drain oranges.
When mixture is cool, mix in Cool Whip and oranges.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Recipe is easily doubled for larger group.

title: quick beef and cauliflower
directions: Brown steak cubes in oil in skillet.
Add cauliflower, green pepper, garlic and soy sauce; mix well.
Simmer, covered, for 8 to 10 minutes.
Blend cornstarch, sugar and broth in bowl.
Stir into beef mixture with green onions and mushrooms.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Serve over rice.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Mix all together and put in pie crusts.

title: hard candy
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in heavy pan. Stir over high heat until mixture boils. Lower heat. Place candy thermometer in pan and cook to 280°. Lower heat and cook to 300°. Remove from heat and let stand until bubbles go out of candy. Add flavoring extract or only a few drops of oil. Add food coloring, stirring only enough to mix well. Pour onto a greased cold china platter or marble slab. Working very fast and as soon as cool enough to handle, pull edges and cut with scissors. Drop cut pieces into a small amount of confectioners sugar and roll around until each piece is covered. Store in airtight container.

title: quick casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Place in a 9 x 9-inch pan. Layer with frozen green beans and then layer of cream of mushroom soup.
Place Mozzarella cheese on top of soup.
Then a layer of Tater Tots.
Bake, uncovered, for 50 minutes at 350°.
Not salt is added to the recipe.

title: honey crunch cookies
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in bowl.
Cook the margarine, honey and brown sugar until melted.
Pour butter mixture over cereal mixture; mix until well blended.
Spread into a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden brown, in a 325° oven, stirring occasionally.
Spread on wax paper to cool; stir in 1/2 cup raisins.

title: tomato mustard(special secret recipe)
directions: Cook onions and tomatoes until soft; force through a sieve. Discard pulp.
Add sugar, salt and all but one pint of vinegar mixture.
Make a paste of mustard and vinegar.
Add to mixture and boil down until a consistency of boiled custard.
Grind peppers and add just before turning off the heat.
Pack as usual.
(Use the best vinegar.)

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix in gallon jug and shake; shake again several times.

title: my favorite hershey bar pie
directions: In a heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt Hershey bars.
Let cool completely or they will "melt" the Cool Whip.
Fold chocolate and Cool Whip together.
Spoon into graham cracker crust. Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: gator's light rolls
directions: Mix flours, sugar and salt.
Add yeast, dissolved in warm water, Crisco, egg, instant potatoes and water.
Knead hard for 10 minutes.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Refrigerate overnight. When ready to use, make out rolls.
Let them rise and bake at 425°.
Brush with butter when half done.

title: finger paint
directions: Mix starch and cold water.
Stir until very smooth.
Add boiling water and stir thoroughly.
Let mixture cool for 1/2 hour. Stir several times while it's cooling.
Pour into cups and add food coloring.
Can use sponge, cotton balls and Q-tips.
Make designs on construction paper with glue and sprinkle with sand.

title: easy cookies
directions: Mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Form into roll; refrigerate overnight.
Slice and bake.

title: fiery hot chicken chili
directions: *Substitute 2 cans pinto beans and 1 - 4 oz. can chopped green chilies.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Into an uncooked pie crust, put the rhubarb.
Mix and stir the sugar, eggs and flour.
Pour over the rhubarb.
Bake at 350° until set.

title: spicy beef salad
directions: Partially freeze beef. Slice across the grain into thin strips; set aside. For dressing, combine lime juice, sugar, soy sauce, basil and mint; set aside. In a medium nonstick skillet that has been coated with nonstick cooking spray, saute jalapeno, garlic and ginger for 30 seconds. Add beef; stir fry until cooked as desired. Remove beef from pan; gently toss with red pepper and cucumber. Place greens in a large bowl or divide among individual bowls or plates; top with beef mixture. Add dressing to pan and bring to a boil; remove from heat and drizzle over salad. Serve immediately. This has 11 grams carbohydrate.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Drain cherries; mix sugar, butter and syrup.
Knead mixture until smooth.
Shape about 1/2 teaspoon mixture around each cherry.
Place covered cherries on a cookie sheet lined with wax paper.
Chill until firm.
Melt chocolate.
Dip covered cherries into chocolate mixture.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in egg, shortening, milk and corn, mixing well.
Drop by tablespoons into hot oil heated at 375°.
Fry until golden (about 4 minutes), turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: rice dressing
directions: Melt the margarine in a saucepan over low heat.
Add the green pepper, onion and celery and cook for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except water chestnuts.
Drain water chestnuts.
Stir into rice mixture and place in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: champagne raisin sauce
directions: Cover raisins with 1/2 wine and simmer 5 minutes.
Add sugar, butter, seasonings and cornstarch, dissolved with 1/2 cup wine. Stir until thickened.
Serve hot.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: salsa
directions: Mix 1 pound cut up Velveeta and 1 cup salsa in large microwavable bowl.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes or until Velveeta is melted, stirring after 3 minutes.
Makes 24 servings. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: kathy palliser's microwave easy lasagna
directions: Set power on High.
In large glass bowl, crumble ground beef and microwave 2 to 3 minutes until browned, stirring once.
Drain and stir in spaghetti sauce and water.

title: country style green beans
directions: Boil fat meat 1 hour.
Pour in washed and broken green beans and cook until tender.
Lay squash and potatoes on top of green beans and simmer for about 30 minutes.
Serve with cornbread and onions.

title: lite orange salad
directions: Heat pineapple.
Bring to boiling point.
Add Jell-O.
Take off stove and let cool, then add low-fat buttermilk and Cool Whip. Chill until set.

title: turkey corn chowder
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, melt margarine. Add vegetables and saute until carrots are tender-crisp, about 5 minutes.
Add water, potatoes and broth mix.
Stir to combine and bring to a full boil. Reduce heat to medium and cook until potatoes are tender, about 10 minutes. Add corn and turkey.
Cook until heated through, about 5 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Simmer tea bags in 2 cups of water for 10 minutes; set aside. Boil sugar, 4 cups water, allspice, cloves and cinnamon for 10 minutes.
Strain, then add tea from part one.
Add 10 cups water, frozen orange juice, pineapple juice and juice from lemons.
Mix and refrigerate.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Layer 1:
Green beans, corn and onion, mixed well.

title: finger paints
directions: Mix the sugar and cornstarch together in the saucepan, then add the water and stir a little more.
Cook over low heat, stirring all the time, until blended, about 5 minutes.
Remove from stove, cool and pour into the plastic cups.
Add a couple of drops of food coloring and then a drop of dish detergent.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Save broth.
Brown ground beef and drain well.
Combine all ingredients and add chicken broth to make as soupy as desired.
Add salt, pepper and dash of Tabasco sauce to taste.
Simmer for approximately 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: giant nutty chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; blend well.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: california blend
directions: Combine in a casserole vegetables, soup, rice and cheese.
Melt butter and pour over the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: zippy celery
directions: Wash celery.
In mixing bowl, blend cheeses, peppers and chili powder.
Stuff celery.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add salt.
Gradually beat in the sugar until egg mixture looks like meringue.
With a large spoon, fold in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Drop the batter by rounded teaspoons onto a piece of foil (not a cookie sheet).
Put the foil in the oven directly on the rack. Immediately turn oven off and do not open the door until the next morning or for at least 4 hours.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: beefy cheese dip or spread
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients very thoroughly.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve with your favorite chips or crackers.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef. Add taco seasoning, chili powder and cumin. Mix well.
Stir in tomato sauce and water. Simmer about 20 minutes.
Spray vegetable oil on a 2-quart casserole dish. Place 4 tortillas on bottom of dish.

Pour 1/2 meat mixture over tortillas. Sprinkle with 1/2 onions and 1/2 cheese. Repeat with remaining tortillas, meat mixture, onions and cheese. Bake approximately 20 minutes until cheese is bubbly. This dish can be frozen.

title: praline ice cream sauce
directions: Spread pecans on baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes. Set aside.
Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Add light brown sugar, corn syrup and flour, stirring well.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and let cool to lukewarm.
Gradually stir in milk and pecans.
Serve over ice cream.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding as directed on box.
Add condensed milk and whipped topping.
In large bowl, line bottom with vanilla wafers. Add a layer of pudding, bananas, wafers, etc., until all pudding and bananas are used.
Top with wafers.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: grandma's crullers
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Rub in butter.
Add eggs and enough sour cream to make a soft dough.
Roll out thin.
Cut into strips and twist and fry in deep fat.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and flour and beat well.
Add melted butter to mixture and mix well.
Add chocolate chips and vanilla; mix well.
Bake in unbaked pie shell for 45 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: easy chicken chimichangas supreme
directions: In a large skillet with a little oil, brown the chicken with the green pepper.
Stir in the rice, olives, salsa and chili powder.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and cover.
Heat tortillas.
Place about 1/2 cup of filling in the middle of each tortilla.
Sprinkle 3 tablespoons cheese over mixture in each tortilla.
Fold up sides and ends of each tortilla and secure with toothpicks.

title: simple sugar cookies
directions: Beat sugar and lard together until light and fluffy.
Add egg and beat.
Put flour, baking powder, soda, and salt in after you add hot water.
Add flour mixture and vanilla.
Drop on greased pan and bake at 400° for about 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine sliced squash, onion, salt and pepper.
Simmer small amount of water for 30 minutes.
Drain; add eggs, butter, flour, milk, cheese and salt.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: honey pecan shortbread
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Allow butter to reach room temperature and then cream together with honey and vanilla.
Gradually add the flour and nut mixture.
Do not overbeat.
Pat dough into an 11 to 12-inch pancake on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Score halfway through into pie piece wedge shapes.
Bake 40 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool 10 minutes before cutting wedges all the way through.

title: black bean salsa(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Stir together first 6 ingredients. Whisk oil and next 3 ingredients. Pour over bean mixture and toss. Chill for about an hour before serving.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: First, brown chops in skillet in oil.
Place chops in casserole dish.
Add one layer potatoes and one layer onion; sprinkle 1/2 salt.
Repeat layers of potatoes and onions.
Use rest of salt. Add bread crumbs on top of casserole.
Pour oil from skillet over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: butterscotch cream pie
directions: Mix in saucepan, first 6 ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Gradually stir at least half of hot mixture into egg yolks (slightly beaten), then blend into hot mixture in saucepan.
Boil 1 minute more, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Blend in vanilla.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Ingredients to
be
chopped
can be done the day before and kept in the refrigerator overnight.
Soak all of the bread in the chicken
broth
and
add
all other ingredients.
When turkey has been
cooked,
add drippings.
Use two 9 x 18-inch baking pans and bake at 320° for about 30 minutes. Dressing is done when
it becomes firm and usually brown around the edges. This can be frozen after it has been cooked.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Grease an 8-inch square cake pan.
Beat the egg and add sugar, while beating.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture, then add milk, melted butter or margarine, lemon extract and vanilla.
Put in greased pan.

title: buttermilk chicken dinner
directions: In a 3-quart casserole, combine water, bouillon granules, thyme, rosemary and bay leaves.
Remove chicken and pat dry. Place chicken, breast side down, in casserole.
Cook, covered, in 100% power (High) for 10 minutes.
Turn chicken over.
If using new potatoes, put a strip around the centers.
Arrange potatoes, onions and carrots around chicken.
Cook, covered, on 50% power (Medium) 30 to 40 minutes or until done, sticks more easily in the sockets and vegetables are tender, giving dish a half turn and rearranging vegetables once.

title: chicken bake
directions: Boil chicken breasts in water seasoned with onion salt for about 35 minutes.
Place cooked chicken and mushrooms in baking dish and cover with soup and sour cream mixture.
Just before baking, garnish with crushed corn flakes mixed with a little melted butter.
Bake in 325° oven until hot, about 30 to 35 minutes.
Easy "company" dish.
It can be fixed the day before and refrigerated.

title: quick beef and beans casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Brown ground beef; drain. Stir in next 5 ingredients; heat until bubbly. Pour into 2-quart casserole. Cut biscuits in half to form 20 half circles. Place cut side down around edge of casserole. Sprinkle cheese over them. Bake 25 to 30 minutes until biscuits are golden brown. Serves 4 to 5.

title: grandma's peach cobbler
directions: Melt stick of butter into 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Mix 3/4 cup sugar, 3/4 cup milk, 1 cup flour and 3 teaspoon baking powder. Pour into pan. Mix 1 can sliced peaches, 2/3 cup juice from can (add water to juice if needed to make the 2/3 cup) and 1/4 cup sugar. Pour into batter. Do not stir.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes. Great with ice cream. Serve hot or cold.

title: cheese crackers
directions: Mix cheese with melted margarine.
Add flour and mix well. Stir in Rice Krispies.
Form into small balls or drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: meringue kisses
directions: Blend together egg whites and salt until very stiff.
Stir in gradually the sugar, beating after each addition of sugar until very stiff again.
Add vanilla and beat again.
Cover a cookie sheet with a brown paper bag.
Drop large spoonfuls on paper bag. Bake 50 minutes in 300° oven until light brown.

title: crock-pot macaroni cheese
directions: Grease crock-pot.
Combine all ingredients and pour into crock-pot.
Add extra cheese on top.
Cook on low 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, but only half the Cheddar cheese.
Put in a 2-quart casserole; sprinkle rest of cheese on top and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: In a deep baking pan or dish, pour batter in melted butter; do not stir.
Pour sweetened fruit over this.
Do not stir. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spiced tea
directions: Memo:
I put cloves and cinnamon in small cloth bag.
Take it out of the tea when it is spiced to taste.

title: new orleans shrimp salad
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine mayonnaise, olives, onions, relish, celery, oil. hot sauce, Worcestershire, salt, Grey Poupon and lemon juice.
Mix together thoroughly.

title: jack daniel's cake
directions: Sift cake and pudding mixes together.
Add eggs, milk, whiskey and oleo.
Beat long and hard by hand.
Add butterscotch morsels and walnuts, reserving 1/2 cup of each.
Pour batter into a prepared 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and sprinkle remaining morsels and nuts over the batter.
Bake at 350° for 46 to 60 minutes.
The bottom of the cake becomes the topping and it's easy to scoop out pieces with a spatula.

title: whole wheat pancakes
directions: Stir together dry ingredients.
Combine egg, milk and oil, then add to flour mixture all at once.
Stir until blended.
Pour 1/4 cup batter onto a hot lightly greased griddle.
Cook over medium heat.
Sprinkle fruit or nuts just before turning.

title: braised pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops slowly on both sides in amount of hot shortening; season with salt and pepper.
Add a little hot water if desired.
Cover tightly.
Cook over low heat about 45 to 60 minutes or until tender.
Make gravy from pan juices if desired.

title: raspberry sandwich cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll and cut with a glass and bake separate.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
When cool, ice with raspberry jelly and put together.

title: teacher's chicken bake
directions: Layer chicken and onions in baking pan and salt to taste. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours, basting occasionally.
Quick and tasty; even after a hard day at school.

title: mints
directions: When mixed, it should be like play dough.
Shape into your favorite shapes or use molds.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Mix well.
Sift together and add dry ingredients.
Mash bananas with fork and blend in first mixture with lemon juice and nuts.
Bake for 55 minutes at 325° in loaf pan.
Makes good muffins; bake about 20 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt oleo and beat eggs before combining with other ingredients.
Bake 60 minutes at 350°.
Use casserole dish equivalent to 10 x 10 x 2-inch.

title: southern fried catfish
directions: Fill a fryer or a deep pot halfway with oil. Heat oil to 350°. Sprinkle both sides of each catfish with salt and Old Bay seasoning. In a separate bowl, combine flour and cornmeal. Dredge catfish in flour mixture and place in fryer. Deep fry for approximately 7 to 8 minutes until done. Drain on paper towels.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer together 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: noodle-rice chicken bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 5-quart Dutch oven, melt butter over medium heat.
Add noodles and cook, stirring constantly, until noodles are crisp and light brown, about 5 minutes.
Add rice, water, soy sauce, broth, undiluted onion soup, water chestnuts and chicken.
Mix well.

title: surprise hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix salad dressing, cheese and onion.
Spread thickly on bread; cut crusts off white bread.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes. Toast brown under broiler.
Serve hot.

title: praline cake
directions: Melt oleo in hot buttermilk.
Add brown sugar and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, cocoa and soda.
Blend with other ingredients.
Pour into rectangular 2-inch deep pan, lightly greased.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until done.
Remove cake from oven and spread with glaze. Serves 20 to 24.

title: sprits cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add sifted flour and eggs.
Add nuts.
Stir.
Put through a cookie press.
Bake for 7 to 10 minutes in a 400° oven.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: "good"
directions: Lightly butter bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan and cover with vanilla wafer crumbs.
Mix raspberry jello with boiling water. Add vanilla ice cream.
Stir until ice cream is melted.
Add crushed pineapple and diced walnuts.
Pour into pan.
Cover top with more wafer crumbs.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Saute onions in the 1/4 cup butter until tender, but not brown in large soup pot.
Blend in flour to make a pasty substance. Gradually add chicken broth or bouillon to flour mixture stirring out lumps.
Bring to a boil.
Add salt, broccoli and cream.
Cook and stir about 30 minutes.
Freeze or refrigerate until serving time.
This soup is better the second day.

title: coffee cake with yeast
directions: Scald milk. Stir in sugar, salt and shortening. Cool to lukewarm. Sprinkle yeast into warm water. Stir to dissolve. Add milk mixture, eggs, 3 cups flour, beat until smooth.

title: barb's cheese balls
directions: Mix together cheese, pecans and garlic.
Blend the cream cheese and salt into mixture.
Roll into balls and dust with paprika.
Cover and keep in refrigerator.

title: chunky potato soup
directions: Melt butter or margarine in heavy pan.

Add flour to make a light roux, cooking approximately 1 minute (don't overcook). Gradually add milk, stir in potatoes, onion, salt and pepper. Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently (don't let mixture scorch) until mixture is thickened and potatoes are done.
Serve warm.
Makes 5 cups.
Can be doubled.

title: sour cream burritos
directions: Mix together soup, sour cream and chilies.
Set aside.
Brown hamburger with onion.
Warm tortillas in a frying pan with butter to soften.
On each tortilla, add some of the soup mixture, some of the hamburger and some of each of the cheeses down the center. Roll to seal.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together the cream cheese, peanut butter, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Freeze.
Serve frozen.

title: apple butter
directions: Mix all ingredients. Cook 10 to 12 minutes.
Pour into jars, seal and store.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to directions and drain.
Brown beef, onions and garlic in skillet.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, spices, salt, pepper and 1 1/2 cups water.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Alternate layers of noodles, meat sauce and cheeses in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: range or man cookies
directions: Melt shortening.
Add sugars.
Cream well.
Add eggs.
Mix until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt together.
Add oatmeal, cereal, coconut and nuts.
Form balls and press down.
Bake in 350° oven for about 12 minutes.

title: norwegian lefse
directions: Chill potatoes and mash or rice them.
Add all other ingredients blending and rolling out 6-inch tortillas of potato on floured surface.
Bake on griddle until brown spots begin to appear.
Serve with butter.

title: mexican fritters
directions: Combine water, butter, 1 teaspoon sugar, salt and nutmeg in 2-quart saucepan.
Heat over medium-high heat until butter is melted, stirring occasionally.
Increase heat to high.
Bring to a full rolling boil.
Add flour all at once to saucepan; remove from heat.
Beat with wooden spoon until mixture forms smooth, thick paste.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat 1 to 2 minutes until mixture pulls away from side of pan and forms a ball and a film forms on bottom of pan.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating vigorously after each addition until dough is smooth and shiny. Stir in vanilla.
Let dough stand at room temperature 15 minutes.

title: any occasion punch
directions: Soften sherbet at room temperature for 10 minutes before using.
Mix fruit punch and Sprite in punch bowl.
Add sherbet, floating on top.
Let set for a few minutes.
Stir again and serve.

title: onion casserole
directions: Slice onions into rings.
Saute in margarine.
Pour onions in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Top with cracker crumbs.
May be put in layers.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: m&m and chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, soda and salt in a small bowl.
Beat butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla in a large bowl.
Add eggs.
Beat in flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips, M&M's and nuts.
Drop by rounded tablespoonful onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake for 8 minutes.

title: tomato molded salad
directions: Mix lemon Jell-O with 1 cup of hot water until dissolved.
Add 1 can stewed tomatoes and let set.
Serves 4.

title: jeweled cheese ball
directions: Chop all but the white ends of the green onions and the Armour dried beef and put in a bowl.
Add the softened cream cheese and mix well.
Shape into a ball and refrigerate until firm.
Roll cheese ball in desired coating: chili powder, paprika, chopped nuts, seasoned pepper, chopped parsley, etc.
Serve with crackers.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: peanut patties
directions: Bring the peanuts, Karo syrup, pinch of salt, sugar and milk to a boil, then simmer for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Add the vanilla, food coloring and butter.
Beat until thickened.
Drop by tablespoonful onto waxed paper.

title: peter paul mound cake
directions: Follow directions on cake mix; bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan. In a separate pot, cook milk and sugar together; boil for 5 minutes.
Stir all the time.
Take off stove; add marshmallows. Stir until melted.
Add coconut.
Pour this on top of baked sheet cake, then cover cake with icing.

title: layered taco casserole
directions: In 2-quart casserole, place beef. Microwave at High 5 to 6 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes. Drain beef and remove from casserole.

title: peanut butter cup bars
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, peanut butter, 3/4 cup butter and powdered sugar.
Work well with fingers and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine remaining butter, milk and brown sugar in a small saucepan; boil for 1 minute.
Add chocolate chips and stir until smooth.
Spread on top of first mixture.
Let cool and cut into squares.
Makes 32 (1 1/2-inch) squares.

title: parmesan curry dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in blender container or food processor; process until blended.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Pressure cook the chicken until tender and save the broth to use.
Cook celery and onion in a small amount of butter until tender.
Mix other ingredients and pour in greased baking dish. Bake, covered, for 30 to 40 minutes (then uncover and finish baking an additional 10 minutes).
Bake at 350°.

title: crab supreme
directions: Thaw crab and drain.
Mix these 5 ingredients in a large bowl. Place in a large, shallow casserole 12 x 10 x 1 1/2 inches.
Melt butter in a large frying pan.
Stir in stuffing and mix well. Spread stuffing mixture on top of crab mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10.

title: sweet-tart franks for a crowd(microwave)
directions: Stir together in a small bowl the small jars of jelly and mustard.
Microwave mixture on High setting 2 to 3 minutes, until stirred smooth.
Stir together frankfurter pieces and sweet-tart sauce in 3-quart casserole dish.
Microwave on High setting 6 to 81 minutes, stirring after 4 minutes.
Serve immediately or transfer to a chafing dish, if desired.
Makes about 80 hors d'oeuvres.

title: rum cake
directions: Put cake mix and pudding mix in bowl, add oil, water, rum and eggs and beat until smooth.
Grease and flour a 12-cup Bundt pan and sprinkle with nuts.
Pour in batter.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet on medium heat.
Add onion, celery, green pepper and carrots. Stir-fry until softened.
Add meat. Cook and stir until lightly browned. Stir in ketchup, water, chili powder, salt, pepper and hot pepper sauce.
Simmer, uncovered, on low heat 15 minutes or until thick enough to spoon on buns.
Makes 8 servings.

title: marshmallow creme
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold water in a mixing bowl; set aside 5 minutes to soften.
Add to boiling water in saucepan, cook and stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Cool to consistency of thick syrup.
Add sugar replacement and vanilla, stirring to blend.

title: southern fried hush puppies
directions: Sift cornmeal, flour, baking powder, garlic salt and salt together in a bowl.
Add egg and milk to cornmeal mixture.
Stir until well mixed and set aside for 5 minutes.
Add more milk if needed and drop by small spoonfuls into hot oil in skillet.
Fry until golden brown.

title: heavenly biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add liquid ingredients slowly.
Mix well.
Store in a tightly covered bowl in refrigerator.
Roll out on a lightly floured surface; cut into biscuits and put on a greased pan.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Dough will keep in refrigerator for 2 weeks.
You can use as much as you want each time.

title: vegetable patch pita sandwich
directions: Combine vegetables with mayonnaise and mustard.
Split pita bread; fill with vegetable mixture.
Add lettuce, if desired. Serves 4.

title: ruth dickey's raisin filled cookies
directions: To make filling:
Grind raisins and walnuts together.
Add 4 teaspoons flour, 1 cup sugar
and water.
Cook until thick and set aside to cool.

title: orange slush
directions: Mix all ingredients in a gallon milk jug.
Freeze overnight. Thaw to a slushy consistency.
Shaking the jug every 15 minutes will help.

title: pickled okra
directions: Use small, tender pods of okra, leaving a little stem on.
Put dill, pepper and mustard seed in jar first; pack okra.
Boil water, vinegar and salt until salt dissolves.
Pour into sterilized jars; seal.
Put in hot water bath and boil for 5 minutes.
Yields 5 pints.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook sugar, syrup, water, oleo and vanilla.
Cook until mixture threads, but not brittle.
Add soda and pour over popped corn.
When slightly cool, make into balls.

title: wiener schnitzel
directions: Pound meat until 1/4-inch thick with mallet.
Flour the meat; dip into salted beaten eggs, then into bread crumbs.
Fry in deep hot oil until done, 7 to 10 minutes.
Drain on paper towel. Serve.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients.
Mix avocados with lemon juice. Mix sour cream, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt.
Spread on tray the bean tip, avocado mix, then sour cream mix.
Then top with last 5 ingredients as topping.

title: coconut dream pie
directions: Prepare whipped topping.
Mix with 1 cup of milk as directed on package using large mixing bowl.
Add remaining milk and pudding mix.
Beat on high for 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Fold in coconut.
Spoon in crust.
Chill at least 4 hours.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: *Or 18 finely crushed Oreos.

title: banana bites
directions: Cut bananas into 1-inch lengths.
Dip in thawed lemonade concentrate (undiluted).
Roll in coconut flakes.
Serve on toothpicks.

title: wassail
directions: Pour first 4 ingredients in percolator.
In the top of the percolator, put the cinnamon sticks, cloves and red hots.
Let perk.

title: macaroni 'n cheese
directions: Toss cooked macaroni in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Pour into lightly greased crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low for 3 to 4 hours; stir occasionally.

title: sour cream fudge
directions: Butter an 8 x 8
x 2-inch baking pan.
Set aside.
Butter the sides of a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
In saucepan, combine sugar, sour cream and butter. Cook over medium-high heat to boiling, stirring constantly, with a wooden spoon.
Clip a candy thermometer to side of pan. Reduce heat to medium.
Continue to cook to 238° (soft ball stage), stirring occasionally.
Mixture should boil at moderate, steady rate over entire surface. Remove from heat.
Chop almond bark into pieces and stir in.
Add vanilla, stirring until coating is melted. Add walnuts, stirring until smooth and mixture starts to thicken (about 3 minutes). Pour into pan.
Score candy while still warm into 1-inch pieces. Cool until firm. Cut into pieces. Store in tightly fitting container.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Quarter tomatoes and put spices in with them.
Boil for 2 hours (taste).
Makes 4 pints (hot jars).

title: pickled eggs
directions: Blend mustard with a little vinegar.
Add remaining vinegar, water and spices.
Cover; heat to boiling, then simmer 10 minutes. Pour over onions and eggs.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
I usually keep in 1/2 gallon canning jar in fridge.
Keeps about 1 month.
As eggs are eaten, more can be added.
Change brine every month.

title: meat balls
directions: Form into balls; brown.
Add to sauce.
Cook on low heat until thickened.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix first layer together (1 stick margarine,
1 cup flour and 1/2 cup chopped nuts).
Press into Pyrex dish.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.
Let cool and dry.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, biscuit mix, eggs, oleo and vanilla in electric mixer.
Blend on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Let stand about 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with coconut and bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: mystic tofu
directions: In bowl, add soup, onion, spices and milk and mix.
Add sliced mushrooms and diced green pepper; stir.
Boil noodles to only 3/4 cooked.
Drain and add to mixture, then add tuna and frozen peas, stirring gently into even chunks.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Simmer onion and green pepper; add hamburg and brown.
Core and crush tomatoes and add to mixture.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 1 hour.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Drain fruit cocktail; place in large bowl.
Sift sugar, baking soda, sifted flour and salt.
Add dry ingredients to fruit cocktail.
Add butter and egg.
Fold mixture carefully to keep from mashing fruit.
Spread mixture in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nut meats.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with Cool Whip or Lemon Butter Sauce.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs and shortening.
Dissolve baking powder and soda into buttermilk.
Mix well.
Add plain flour to make a soft dough.
Roll, cut and bake in 350° oven.

title: frozen salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese that has been softened.
Whip Dream Whip as directed.
Add sugar and cream cheese; whip again.
Add well drained fruit, nuts and marshmallows.
Stir until well mixed. Pour into a glass dish and freeze.

title: moravian cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and molasses.
Then add dry ingredients and grape juice and stir to mix well (very stiff dough).
Cover and keep in cool place at least 3 days to ripen.
Roll very thin (use a cloth-covered, floured board and plenty of flour).
Cut with fancy cutters.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush crackers;
mix all ingredients.
Pack in cake tin (about a 5
pound size).
Refrigerate at least 24 hours before cutting cake.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, 1 small can tomato sauce (reserve 1/4 cup), Worcestershire sauce, egg, onions, salt and pepper. Spread into iron skillet. Mix remaining ingredients for topping. Pour over meat loaf. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: banana chocolate chip bread
directions: Mix soda and sour cream together and set aside.
Cream butter with sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add flour and sour cream alternately to butter mixture.
Stir in bananas, chocolate chips, vanilla and salt.
Bake in a loaf pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Freezes well.
(Does better in two smaller loaf pans or 6 mini loaf pans; adjust cooking time.)

title: salsa
directions: Put tomatoes in large bowl; cut or tear.
Add other ingredients (vinegar and oil last).
Mix well and refrigerate. Serve with corn chips.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Add oil, sugar and zucchini to beaten eggs and blend.
Combine dry ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Stir well.
Blend in chocolate and nuts.
Bake in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool and frost.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and onion together and make into small balls.
Place in frying pan with melted butter and let brown.
Drain grease.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour over meatballs.
Simmer for 1/2 hour on low heat.

title: cornstarch pudding
directions: In large skillet or flat pan mix cornstarch and sugar.
Mix in milk.
Stir constantly until mixed.
Turn on heat, stir constantly so it does not stick.
When it comes to full boil take off heat. Add vanilla.
Cool.

title: cabbage roll casserole
directions: Fry meat.
Add onion, salt, pepper and rice.
Add soup and water.
Mix well.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar together. Combine oleo, oil, water and cocoa in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Pour chocolate mixture over flour mixture and mix well. Dissolve
baking soda in buttermilk.

title: 5 minute creamy coconut pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, milk and coconut in a blender container.
Cover and blend at low speed for 30 seconds.
Fold into whipped topping.
Add extract.
Spoon in Ready-Crust pie crust.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Let stand at room temperature about 5 minutes (or longer for softer texture) before cutting.
Store leftover pie in freezer.

title: sticky buns
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small pot, mix all sugars, lemon juice, margarine and cinnamon.
Boil for 1 minute.
Set aside 1/4 cup.
Place remaining mix in bottom of round cake pan.
Sprinkle in nuts and/or raisins, if desired.

title: rye bread dip
directions: Mix all dip ingredients together with mixer.
Refrigerate. Scoop out center of rye boat or round and make dipping pieces with them.
Fill hole with dip and serve with bread pieces.

title: cream of chicken
directions: Cook rice in chicken broth until soft. Strain liquid into another pot. Puree the rice in a blender with a little broth. Return it to the pot. Add hot milk or cream. Salt and pepper. Simmer a few minutes.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time beating after each addition.
Add vanilla wafers, alternating with milk. Add pecans and coconut if desired.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour 15 minutes.

title: cran raspberry ring
directions: Dissolve raspberry and lemon jello in boiling water.
Stir in frozen raspberries, breaking up large pieces with fork.
Stir in cranberry relish.
Slowly pour in lemon-lime soda; stir gently. Turn into a 6 or 6 1/2-cup ring mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold on lettuce-lined platter.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: buffalo style deep-fried wings
directions: Preheat plenty of peanut oil in electric deep-fryer, set at 375°.

title: cauliflower and peas salad
directions: Clean and core cauliflower, then cut up into bite size chunks. Place in a large bowl.
Add onions, peas, celery and cashews. Pour dressing over all ingredients, then toss.
Chill for 3 hours, stirring every hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in an iron skillet at 450° for 40 minutes.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Microwave caramels and water in medium bowl on High for 1 minute and 30 seconds.
Stir. Continue microwaving 30 seconds to 1 minute or until sauce is smooth, stirring every 30 seconds.
Pour over popped corn; toss until well coated.
Spread onto greased cookie sheet.
Let stand until set; break apart.

title: chocolate marshmallow cookie pie
directions: Microwave marshmallows and 2 tablespoons milk in medium microwavable bowl on High for 45 seconds.
Stir.
(Marshmallows will be partially melted.)
Refrigerate 15 minutes to cool.
Stir in 1 cup of the whipped topping.
Pour 2 cups milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat with wire whisk 2 minutes.
Let stand 1 minute or until thickened.
Stir in remaining 1 1/2 cups of whipped topping.
Spoon into crust.
Arrange cookies over pudding mixture.
Spread marshmallow mixture over cookies. Refrigerate 4 hours or until set.
Drizzle with chocolate topping just before serving.

title: baked beans
directions: Day before serving, soak beans in cold water, covered, overnight.
Water should cover beans completely.
Next day, drain beans in colander.
Rinse under cold water.
Turn into 6-quart kettle.
Cover with 5 cups cold water.
Add onion, bay leaves, salt, pepper, ham bone and leftover ham.
Bring to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour or until beans are tender.
Add more water as needed.
Remove ham bone and bay leaves.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Wash chicken.
Place in 9 x 12-inch glass baking dish.
Lay strips of Swiss cheese over the chicken.
Pour spaghetti sauce over the chicken and cheese.
Sprinkle over croutons.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Great with rice or pasta.

title: texas caviar
directions: Soak beans in hot water in a large saucepan for 1 hour. Drain.
Add water to cover, about 3 inches.
Place over high heat, bring to a boil, turn down to a simmer, and cook until tender.
Drain.
Add Italian dressing while beans are warm. Marinate 2 to 4 hours, then add remaining ingredients and marinate overnight.

title: california cheddar chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in Italian dressing for 30 to 45 minutes. Place chicken under the broiler until it's nearly cooked.
Then sprinkle onions and tomato over chicken and top with cheese.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, flour and gelatin. Add vegetable oil, water, eggs and strawberries.
Mix well.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until they test done.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni; drain, cover with cold water until the macaroni swells up.
Grate cheese.
Beat the egg, then add the milk, flour, salt and pepper.
Beat with a fork until there are no lumps of flour.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Mix the flour, nuts and oleo and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan to make crust.
Bake at 350°
for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add sherbet and stir until melted.
Add oranges and pineapple.
Pour into 5-cup mold and refrigerate until set.
(I used the juice from the pineapple and oranges, plus water to make 2 cups.)

title: bean dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with sour cream.
Mix in taco seasoning.
Add refried beans, onion and Tabasco sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until bubbly 20 to 30 minutes. Cover for the first 15 minutes.
Serve with chips.

title: tina's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350 for 45 minutes. Top with ketchup and let it sit in the oven for a few more minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides, then place in a baking dish. Place a layer of onions on top, then place a layer of potatoes. Repeat until all ingredients have been used. Add 1/2 can of water to the can of mushroom soup; mix well. Pour over casserole and cover with aluminum foil. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken until tender and debone.
Line bottom of an 8 x 10-inch baking dish with chicken.
Crumble Doritos on top of chicken.
Sprinkle onions on top of Doritos.
Mix cream of chicken and cream of mushroom soups with 1 cup chicken broth and Ro-Tel. Warm this up and pour over ingredients in dish.
Put in a 450° oven for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle on cheese and cook for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add pineapple, marshmallows and strawberries. Place in refrigerator and chill until set.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water.
Add frozen strawberries; stir until strawberries are thawed.
Add bananas and crushed pineapple.
Put 1/2 of this mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan, then put in freezer to jell quickly.
Set the other half aside.
Mix the cream cheese, sour cream and nuts.
Add to the first layer of Jell-O mixture, spreading evenly.
Then add the other half of the Jell-O mixture. Put in the refrigerator to jell.

title: golden isle goodies
directions: Mix well the first 3 ingredients and spread in bottom of Pam sprayed 11 x 14-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, eggs and sugar well and pour over crust.
Sprinkle nuts over cheese mixture.
Sift remaining 1/2 cup powdered sugar over all.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl and roll into balls the size of a walnut.
Put on cookie sheet and cook at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: celery seed deli slaw
directions: Mix all the ingredients and chill before serving.

title: pineapple muffins
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Combine egg and remaining ingredients; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon batter into paper-lined muffin pans, filling two-thirds full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 22 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: cake decoration cookies
directions: Mix and chill dough overnight.
Roll into balls and roll in white sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Mix 1st five ingredients together and put in greased baking dish.
Cover with fried onion rings.
Bake at 350° until onions are brown and casserole is bubbling.

title: best ever rum cake
directions: Before starting, sample the rum to check for quality.
Good, isn't it?
No!
Go ahead.
Select a large mixing bowl, measuring cup, etc.
Check the rum again.
To be sure it is of the highest quality, pour one level cup of rum into a glass and drink it. Repeat.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix in large bowl.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Cook all together, stirring until thick.
Pour in baked pie shell. Use egg whites for meringue topping.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes, until meringue is cooked and brown.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix water and sugar.
Add orange juice and the pineapple grapefruit drink.
To this add bananas.
Pour into an appropriate freezer container and freeze for 1 hour before serving.
Remove from freezer; add 1 quart club soda to each 2 quarts of punch mix. Makes approximately 1 1/4 gallons.

title: naomi's chicken soup
directions: Cook chicken thoroughly and bone.
Add the chicken broth and equal part water.
Dissolve the chicken bouillon cubes in hot water and add to broth.
Cut carrots, potatoes and celery; add to soup.
Simmer.
Add 2 to 3 cups of water, then add 1/2 pound pasta.
Boil until noodles are done.
Enjoy!

title: venison stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into very thin strips or cubes.
Trim off excess fat. Brown meat in butter.
Add onions.

title: no cook candy balls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a medium bowl. Mix well.
Shape into 1/2-inch balls.
Roll each ball in coconut and chill. Yields about 3 dozen.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Insert cloves into apple.
Add apple and orange slices to juice mixture and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove cider from heat and let stand about 5 minutes.
Yield: 2 quarts.

title: green beans and shoepeg corn
directions: Mix together and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: indonesian gado gado
directions: Boil water, brown sugar and salt.
Add the peanut butter, stirring, until the mixture is a thick consistency.
Remove from the heat and squeeze in the lemon juice, stirring until the the sauce is smooth.
Steam or lightly cook the vegetables.
In a large bowl, mix the vegetables and the peanut butter sauce; serve.

title: shom tortes
directions: Beat the egg whites until frothy.
Add vinegar, vanilla and salt; beat with Mixmaster.
Beat in sugar, adding slowly.
When peaks form and hold on mixture, drop on lightly greased cookie sheet with spoon.
This makes 6 tortes.
Place in cold oven.
Turn oven on to 275° and bake for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: easy potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, chopped onion, chicken broth and water in Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in soups and milk; heat thoroughly.
Garnish.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Put 1/3 to 1/2 cup in mug and add hot water.
Stir well and add Cool Whip or marshmallows.

title: pickled beets
directions: Drain the beets, reserving the juice.
Combine the juice, sugar, vinegar, and spices in a small saucepan.
Heat until sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat and add beets.
Refrigerate for flavors to blend.
Makes about 4 fat free servings.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Mix, then spread on cookie sheet.
Bake for 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: french dressing
directions: Put in quart jar; shake.

title: whole wheat oven pancakes
directions: In medium bowl, stir together flour, cereal, wheat germ, baking powder and soda.
Add egg and rest of the ingredients. Beat until smooth.
Spread on greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes.
(Great for when you have company.)

title: rice casserole
directions: Cut large mushrooms in half and leave small ones whole.
Boil mushrooms in 1 1/2 cups of water for 10 minutes.
Save 1 cup of mushroom stock.
Add olives, mushrooms, stock, rice and seasoning packet; stir well.
Add olive oil.
Drop tomatoes in boiling water and remove as soon as skin loosens.
Peel and quarter, then add to rice.
Add onion and cheese and stir.
Refrigerate overnight, then add 1 cup of boiling water and bake for 1 hour at 425°.

title: brownie swirl cheesecake
directions: Grease bottom of 9-inch springform pan.
Prepare brownie mix as directed on package.
Pour batter evenly into spring-form pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Pour over brownie layer.
Spoon chocolate over cream cheese mixture; cut through batter with knife several times for marble effect.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Loosen cake from rim of pan; cool before removing rim of pan.
Chill.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Dice 6 slices of bread.
Put in large greased baking dish. Mix chicken, onion, celery and mayonnaise.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over bread and spread.
Cover with rest of bread. Over this, pour eggs and milk.
Refrigerate overnight.
When ready to bake, pour soup over preceding and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: carrot-fruit toss
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a medium bowl; stir well. Cover and chill 2 to 3 hours.
Gently stir sour cream into carrot mixture.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Yields 8 servings.

title: skillet supper
directions: In large skillet, add all ingredients and cook over low heat 15 to 20 minutes.
tags: cream of potato soup plus milk

title: simple brownies
directions: Mix and bake in greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: green salad with strawberries
directions: Combine orange juice, mint, lemon juice and sugar in small bowl.
Add strawberries; toss gently and set aside.
Combine lettuces, onion and sprouts in a large bowl; toss gently.
Add strawberry mixture; toss gently.
Sprinkle with Gruyere cheese. Serves 4.

title: squash casserole(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Combine stuffing and butter and press half into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lightly steam squash and onion until barely cooked.
Drain thoroughly.
Combine soup, sour cream and carrots.
Fold in cooked squash and onions.
Gently spoon mixture over stuffing and top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° until brown, approximately 30 minutes.

title: super sandwich
directions: Smear Marshmallow Creme on one slice of bread and peanut butter on the other.
Put two pieces together and eat.

title: party cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package.
Add 1 cup hot water to jello.
Poke holes with fork in warm cake and pour hot jello over cake.
Cool.
Spread Cool Whip over cake and then add cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: baked chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces on a greased shallow pan. Spread soup evenly over chicken. Sprinkle with cornflake crumbs. Salt and pepper as desired.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours. Bake, uncovered for crispy; cover for softer coating.

title: chicken vegetable casserole
directions: Boil chicken and remove from bones.
Cook mixed vegetables and drain.
Saute onion in magarine.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour in 12 x 7-inch baking dish, sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes, until casserole bubbles.

title: apple butter
directions: Core and quarter peeled apples.
In 4 to 6-quart Dutch oven, combine apples and cider.
Cook until soft, about 30 minutes.
Run through blender.
Boil gently 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Add sugar and spices.
Cook and stir over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil gently, stirring frequently until desired thickness.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until pepper changes color.
Put in a large pan.
Add tomatoes.
Add pimentos and cream of mushroom soup.
Add salt and chile powder.
Simmer for 45 minutes.
Boil chicken and bone.
Boil spaghetti in chicken broth.
Layer spaghetti, cheese and English peas.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and pepper for several minutes.
Add both cans of soup and mix well.
Cook noodles as directed and drain, then mix noodles with hamburger mixture.
Put into a baking dish and top with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dilly vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill several hours to let flavor enhance.
Serve with carrot and celery sticks or any other type of raw veggie you desire.

title: french silk pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter, then add the chocolate.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat 5 minutes after each egg addition.
Add vanilla. Put into baked one crust pie shell.
Refrigerate and top with whipped cream, if desired.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter, sugars, egg and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients and blend.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Press into a 1 1/2-inch muffin tin.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Remove and immediately press one miniature peanut butter cup into each hot cookie.
Cool.

title: apple bread
directions: Beat by hand the oil, sugar, apples, eggs and nuts.
Add the flour, salt, soda and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 90 minutes in an ungreased loaf pan or angel food pan.

title: holiday fruit cookies
directions: Combine shortening, sugar and eggs.
Mix and stir in sour milk.
Sift dry ingredients together and stir in pecans, cherries and dates.	Chill at least 1 hour.	Preheat oven to 400°.
Drop by teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 8 dozen.

title: quick fudge
directions: Heat chips and milk.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Spread butter in pan.
Pour mixture into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Chill until firm (at least 4 hours).

title: communion bread
directions: Work butter into flour, salt and sugar.
Mix with half and half to make stiff dough.
Knead well (30 minutes).
Roll out thinly and place on cookie sheet.
Mark with ruler 1-inch squares (not cutting through).
Prick each squash with fork twice clear through.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 12 minutes or until lightly brown. Makes 4 pans.

title: yankee pot roast
directions: Heat a large Dutch oven (about 6 to 7-quart) and brown the salt pork.
Remove the pork from the pan, leaving the fat in the pan.
Salt and pepper the roast and brown it in the fat.
Brown well on all sides using a wooden fork to prevent puncturing the meat.
When brown, add 2 cups of water to the pot and then the bay leaf, garlic, thyme and parsley.
Cover and simmer slowly for 2 hours, keeping about 1 cup of water in the bottom of the pot.
Add the carrots, onions and turnip; cover and cook 1/2 hour.
Add the potatoes and cook until the potatoes are tender.
Watch the water.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops in large, heavy skillet and stir in rice. Add soups, drained mushrooms, water, salt and pepper.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan you bake brownies in.
Add melted margarine to sugar.
Add eggs, flour, flavoring and nuts. Mix by hand and do not overmix.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. Cut in squares.
Makes 24.

title: don's chili
directions: Cover with water and cook on medium-high until water cooks down (mash meat as it cooks). Add salt and pepper. Put in crock-pot on LOW and cook overnight. One hour before you serve, add catsup.

title: chocolate caramel fudge cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool 15 minutes.
Poke with large fork.
Pour a jar of heated caramel sauce over cake.
Let cool.
Frost with chocolate fudge frosting.
Whip the whipping cream with powdered sugar.
Spread over frosting.
Crush Heath bars and sprinkle over whipped cream. Cover and freeze overnight.
Leave out several hours to defrost and enjoy.

title: fat free mock guacamole
directions: Place asparagus in bowl of food processor fitted with steel blade or into blender container.
Cover and process until smooth. Add remaining ingredients, cover and refrigerate at least one hour.

title: golden tuna supreme roll
directions: Cream the cheese in bowl.
Add all but last 2 ingredients. Roll in parsley and corn flakes.
Serve with crackers.

title: christmas punch
directions: In punch bowl, combine fruit punch and limeade concentrate. Chill. Just before serving, add the sparkling water. Keep cold with ice ring or chunk of ice. Makes 28 servings (about 1/2 cup each).

title: depression cake
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar with raisins, hot water, vegetable oil, cinnamon and nutmeg. Bring mixture to a boil. Continue cooking at a low boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from fire and cool completely.

title: jogging in a jug
directions: Combine and drink 2 ounces twice a day.

title: pecan pie surprise bars
directions: In large bowl, mix all except 2/3 of yellow cake mix, melted margarine and 1 egg.
Press in greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes until light brown.
Prepare filling in same washed bowl.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Wash unpeeled potatoes and cut lengthwise into 4 wedges.
Place skin side down in 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish or pan.
Combine remaining ingredients; brush over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, brushing with oil/cheese mixture at 15 minute intervals. Turn potatoes over for last 15 minutes.
(These are wonderful with any roasted meat or fine as a snack.)
Yield:
4 servings.

title: chocolate pudding dessert
directions: Cook together the pudding mixes and milk until thick.
Cool until lukewarm or cooler.
Blend the flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, margarine and 1/4 cup pecans as for pastry.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Cream 1 cup sugar and cream cheese until smooth.
Blend in a regular size Cool Whip.

title: sunshine ham and pasta(casserole)
directions: Saute onion in butter in large saucepan until tender.
Stir in flour and salt.
Gradually add milk and water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture just comes to a boil and thickens.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Add mustard, macaroni, ham and green pepper.
Heat to serving temperature.

title: refrigerator cabbage slaw
directions: Put salt over cabbage and let stand.
Boil the sugar, vinegar, water and seeds together for 2 minutes.
When boiled mixture cools, pour over cabbage and vegetables.
Mix.
Keeps in refrigerator a month and makes a 1/2 gallon of slaw.

title: gingerbread(one serving)
directions: Stir and pour in kitchen Dixie cup.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes in covered electric skillet.

title: hamburger and rice dinner
directions: Brown beef and onion together.
Add rice, tomato juice and salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and cook until rice is done. Pour whole tomatoes over rice and meat.
Warm tomatoes.
Serve right from skillet with salad and rolls.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Use same size cans of beans.
Combine all beans in a casserole dish.
Add brown sugar and ketchup.
Add ham or sausage.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: bill's hot wings
directions: Cover chicken wings with flour.
Cook in iron skillet until done.
let cool for 5 minutes, then soak the chicken wings with hot sauce.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Do not overbeat.
Mix in coconut and crumbs.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: lemon torte cake
directions: Melt margarine over crackers.
Spread evenly in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat egg whites and sugar until stiff.
Spread evenly over crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool. Top with pie filling.
Spread Cool Whip on top of lemon pie filling.
Keep refrigerated until ready to use.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour in baked pie shell.
Save egg whites and mix with 1/2 c. sugar and beat to make meringue. Put meringue on top and bake until lightly brown.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Pour into greased round layer pan or square 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 450° until golden brown, 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm.
Or make fried corn bread.
Drop by ladleful into hot grease in frying pan.
Turn as you would a pancake.

title: italian creme cake
directions: Cream oleo and Crisco until lite cream.
Add sugar gradually. Add egg yolks and beat well.
Add flour and soda (which have been sifted togehter) alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in 3 greased and floured pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: stained-glass salad
directions: Chill canned fruit before mixing.
Drain fruit. Slice bananas.
Add strawberries and pie filling.
Mix together and serve.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into cakes and fry in butter until golden brown.

title: walnut chicken struedel
directions: Finely chop 3/4 cup walnuts.
Coarsely chop 3/4 cup walnuts. Combine chicken, broccoli, soup, cheese and coarsely chopped walnuts.
On wax paper, place one sheet of phyllo dough.
Brush with butter.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon finely chopped walnuts. Repeat layers 4 times.
Spoon 1/2 of chicken mixture along lengthwise edge.
Roll up as for jelly roll; tuck in ends as you go.
Place seam side down on greased cookie sheet.
Brush with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cut 4 slashes in top of dough. Repeat to make second struedel.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Can be frozen.
Makes 2 streudels.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: *cucumber with yogurt
directions: Slice cukes very thin into bowl.
Let stand in refrigerator for 20 minutes. Just before serving, mix yogurt with sugar, salt, pepper and scallions. Squeeze excess liquid from cukes and toss with scallions and yogurt dressing.
Serves 4.

title: cherry fudge
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Melt chocolate chips and butter in double boiler.
Add nuts and vanilla to chocolate mixture. Combine with eggs and sugar.
Quickly stir in cherry chips and pour immediately in buttered pan.
Refrigerate.
Will set when cold.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Add 1 egg at a time; mix well.
Add milk, bananas and nuts; mix well.
Bake in a greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour or more, until done.
Cool for 20 minutes, then remove from pan.
(Slices better if chilled first.)

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Add flavoring.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: preposterous pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Beat 4 minutes.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until set.
Cool completely before cutting. Serve with whipped topping.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Bring to boil asparagus soup and cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir.
Pour into oiled mold. Refrigerate to congeal.
Serve mold on lettuce.
Good for parties. It's delicious!

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: Mix together oats, coconut and nuts in a large bowl.
Combine all other ingredients, except vanilla, in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until reaches full boil.
Stir constantly.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove; add vanilla.
Pour over oat mixture.
Mix with fork until cereal mixture is well covered.
Drop from teaspoon to wax paper.
Work fast.
Let stand until firm.
Makes 50 cookies.

title: mom's fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl until well blended.
Place in a loaf pan that has been lined with foil and wax paper.
Cover well and let set in refrigerator.
Best if made at least 2 weeks before serving.

title: mexican cheese spread
directions: Combine mayonnaise and cheese.
Frost each bread round with mixture.
Top with a piece of artichoke heart.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve hot!

title: cottage fried potatoes
directions: Slice or dice potatoes.
Heat butter in a skillet.
Add potatoes; saute, without stirring, until golden on underside. Turn; brown on other side.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar, egg yolk, margarine and butter.
Add cream cheese and vanilla.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Place dough in cookie press; form desired shapes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until set for 8 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place layer of beans in casserole dish; add 1 layer onions and repeat.
Pour mushroom soup on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese and pineapple salad
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until thick; beat eggs and add to cooked mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: calico bean bake
directions: Cook ground chuck, ham, onion and pepper; drain well.
Add catsup, brown sugar, white sugar, vinegar, salt, dry mustard
and the 3 cans of beans which have been drained of 1/2 their liquid. Mix all together well and bake at 350° for 1 hour or at least 6 hours in an electric bean pot or slow cooker.

title: chocolate mounds cake
directions: Add all together and beat well.
Bake in 3 layers at 325° or 350° for 30 minutes.

title: herbed biscuit ring(a quick dinner bread)
directions: Blend together butter or margarine, lemon juice, paprika, celery seed, thyme and sage. Separate biscuits. Spread tops with herb butter.
In an 8 x 1 1/2-inch round layer pan, arrange biscuits, buttered side up, to form a ring, overlapping slightly. Bake in
a 400° oven for 15 to 18 minutes or until golden.
Makes 10 servings.

title: perfect cutout cookies
directions: In a small mixing bowl, stir together the flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In a medium bowl, beat together the margarine and shortening until well combined.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour mixture; beat until well mixed.
Cover and chill 3 hours.
Roll out on lightly floured pastry sheet and cut out with favorite cookie cutters.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes, until lightly golden at edges.

title: mom's cranberry salad
directions: Grind together in food chopper the cranberries and oranges. Take the ground mixture and place in gelatin mold.
Add sugar, apples and nuts.
Prepare gelatin according to directions on the box (less 3/4 or 1 cup of water; the oranges and cranberries have at least that much juice already).
Allow to chill in refrigerator until it gels.
Serve on a bed of lettuce.
Great for Thanksgiving or Christmas dinner!

title: 4 dozen rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup water.
Mix sugar, salt, oil and 1 1/2 cups water in large bowl.
Beat in yeast and eggs.
Add 2 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Stir in enough flour to make soft dough; knead several times.
Place in large greased bowl.
Cover and let rise until doubled in size, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down; cover tightly and refrigerate.
Will keep 3 or 4 days.

title: amy's favorite cookie
directions: Cream the
cheese.
Add
the
egg
yolks and blend very well. Cut
the
butter into the flour until the particles are fine.
Add the
cream cheese mixture to the flour mixture and mix well. Roll
the
dough
into a ball and refrigerate for 1 hour.
(I leave
it
overnight, covered well, then get up and bake cookies in a clean kitchen!) Roll the dough out on a very lightly floured surface
to the size of a cookie sheet and cut out small rounds with
a
cutter.
Lay the rounds on a cookie sheet.
Press
your thumb
into
the center of each round and fill the
depression with apricot jam.
Use small amounts and do it neatly
or
it will overflow and burn.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.
Dust with confectioners sugar when cool.

title: a-p cakes
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add milk, flour and baking powder mixture.
Place batter in 4 pie tins.
Sprinkle with 1 1/2 to 2 teaspoons granulated sugar, then cinnamon.
Dot with butter. Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: pancakes a la consumers union
directions: Let griddle preheat while you prepare the batter.
Set at 400° or medium-high.
Grease griddle lightly with vegetable oil, margarine or butter.

title: easy baked corn
directions: Mix and pour into a buttered 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: cucumber sweet pickles
directions: Cover whole cucumbers and soak for 7 days in brine water using 4 cups salt.
Rinse cucumbers.
Cut and place back in churn with 2 large boxes of alum with just enough water to cover cucumbers for 2 days.
Take out of alum water and drain.
Put back into churn with vinegar for 1 day.
Drain vinegar and place back into churn:
layer of pickles, layer of sugar, 10 pounds of sugar.
Midway up churn, place a cloth with bag and 1 box pickling spice.
Let stand for a week or more, mixing by hand every day.
Then put in jars with a few drops green food coloring to keep pretty and green.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; cream well.
Add egg and cream again.

title: blue fish or trout
directions: Rinse and pat dry fish. Dip in	egg.
Roll in crumb and cheese mixture. Oil or spray
baking
dish.
Baste with melted margarine. Bake in 350° oven until fish flakes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Put cut up chicken, green onion, celery and pineapple in a large bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, milk, vinegar, pepper and salt in small bowl and pour over chicken mixture and stir.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Reserve 1 cup nuts.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in reserved nuts.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and sugar.
Spread in a 9 X 13 pan and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400. Cool.
Blend cream cheese and sugar. Fold in cool whip.
Spread on cookie crust.
Dissolve jello in water.
Stir in strawberries.
When partially set, pour over top and refrigerate.

title: dirty rice
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in casserole in order listed. Sprinkle onion soup mix on top. Cover and bake 60 minutes at 350°. Remove cover the last 10 minutes.

title: lisa's won tons
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Mix soy sauce, chopped water chestnuts, chopped green onions, beaten egg and salt.
Mix well.
Place small amount of mixture in center of won ton wrappers.
Fold in half like a triangle and then take each side and meet in the middle. Pinch the ends closed so they seal.
Deep fry in hot oil until golden.

title: skillet enchiladas
directions: In Dutch oven skillet, combine the cream of mushroom soup, enchilada sauce and milk; heat until bubbly.
Heat cooking oil in small skillet; dip corn tortillas until limp.
Drain tortillas. In skillet, cook beef and onion until meat is brown and onion is tender; drain off fat.
Set aside half of meat mixture.
Add the other half of meat mixture to sauce mixture in Dutch oven pan. Place some meat and shredded cheese on each tortilla.
Roll up each tortilla as for jelly roll.
Arrange tortillas, seam side down in Dutch oven skillet.
Sprinkle remaining shredded Velveeta cheese on top of tortillas.
Cover and cook about 10 minutes on low heat until cheese on top melts.
Makes 8 enchiladas.

title: carrot souffle
directions: In a mixing bowl, blend the butter and flour; add the milk and remaining ingredients. Mix thoroughly. Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter play doh
directions: Mix all together.
Add dry milk gradually to make consistency of Play Doh.
You can eat it as you play with it.

title: one pan pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease bottom of loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inches).
Stir vegetable oil, pumpkin, eggs, baking mix, sugar and cinnamon together in pan with fork until moistened; beat vigorously for 1 minute.
Stir in raisins.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Run knife or metal spatula around sides of loaf to loosen; remove from pan.
(If loaf sticks to sides of loaf pan, press gently on sides of loaf with knife.)
Makes 1 loaf.

title: grilled corn
directions: Buy ears of corn in shucks and soak in water.
When water is absorbed into shucks, place on a hot grill.
Grill about 20 minutes on low heat.
The heat causes the water to steam inside shucks and cooks the corn.
Serve with butter and salt.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat sugar and oil until fluffy. Add eggs and cream well. Add dry ingredients. Mix well. Pour into two round pans and bake at 300 degrees for one hour or until done.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix and cook in unbaked crust at 350°. Alice Ellis is in the Attala County Nursing Home now, but, she remembers making this pie for eatings at Springdale.

title: rice hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef.
Combine beef, rice, soups, 1 1/2 cans water, soy sauce and celery in a casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Add noodles on top and bake 15 to 30 minutes longer.

title: no bake strawberry whip cream cake
directions: Separate ladyfingers into single layers.
Line sides and bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan; press them in firmly.
(I spray sides and bottom of pan with Pam.)
Set aside.

title: no fail meringue
directions: Blend cornstarch and water in a saucepan, stirring, until it gets clear and thick.
Cool.
Beat egg whites until foamy. Gradually add sugar, vanilla, salt and cooled cornstarch mixture. Beat until stiff.
Spread over the pie and bake at 425° for 4 to 4 1/2 minutes.
Makes enough meringue for 1 pie.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Spray nonstick coating in roasting pan with a lid. Mix the rice, soups and water together.
Pour into pan.
Lay chicken in and sprinkle onion soup on top. Cover securely with aluminum foil and then put the lid on.
Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.
Do not peek.
Be sure and use a good heavy baking pan or roasting pan so the rice does not dry out.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water; set aside.
Grind together next 3 ingredients.
Mix all ingredients together and mold or freeze in casserole dish.

title: potatoes with cheese
directions: Boil and mash potatoes; add butter, salt and pepper.
Add eggs, beating well.
Stir in onion and cheese.
Turn into a buttered casserole.
Dot top with butter and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pretzel jello
directions: Mix together 2 1/2 cups crushed pretzels, 3/4 cup melted margarine and 3 tablespoon sugar.
Press into buttered 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Soften cream cheese and mix with 1 cup sugar.
Prepare Dream Whip according to directions.
Fold Dream Whip into cheese mixture and spread over pretzel mixture.
Dissolve strawberry jello in 2 cups of boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries; stir until berries thaw. Carefully pour over the top of other mixture.
Chill.

title: adams county apple cake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, 2 cups sugar, oil, eggs, orange juice, salt and vanilla.
Beat until combined.
In another bowl toss apples with cinnamon and 5 tablespoons sugar.
Spread 1/3 of batter in a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Cover with 1/2 of apples. Repeat layers.
Spoon remaining batter over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan for 20 minutes.
Remove to a wire rack to cool completely.
Just before serving, dust with confectioners sugar if desired.

title: peach, apple or apricot cobbler
directions: Melt butter in large baking dish.
Mix sifted dry ingredients with milk.
Pour the batter carefully over the butter.
Pour fruit over top of batter.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix mayonnaise, cheese, soup and eggs in a small pot.
Simmer until cheese melts (on low).
Cook broccoli and drain.
Pour broccoli in a baking dish.
Pour mixture over top, then add dressing and butter.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: date candy
directions: Process dates and raisins in food processor.
Remove to waxed paper. Add nuts, shape into 12 inch log roll.
Roll in coconut. Chill and thinly slice.

title: hawaiian drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and extracts.
Beat in egg until fluffy.
Add pineapple and dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet 3-inches apart.
Sprinkle with coconut and then bake at 325° for about 20 minutes.

title: noodles and cabbage
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions and drain.
Saute onion in butter.
Add cabbage and cook until tender.
Add noodles and toss gently.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: sweet and sour red cabbage
directions: Lock bowl in position and insert steel blade.
Chop onion at low speed.
Melt margarine or butter in a Dutch oven and saute onion over medium heat until tender.
Meanwhile, insert slicer disc and process cabbage at high speed.
Add cabbage to onion and toss to coat evenly with margarine or butter.
Cover and cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Insert shredder disc and place apples in chute.
Process to shred at low speed.
Mix apples, salt, brown sugar, vinegar and pepper into other items in Dutch oven.
Cover and cook 20 to 25 minutes or until cabbage is tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Stir soda and cocoa in mixing bowl.
Blend in 1/3 cup oil. Add boiling water; stir until mixture thickens.
Stir in sugar, eggs and remaining oil (1/3).
Stir until smooth.
Add flour, vanilla and salt.
Blend.
Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix together 1/2 cup butter and the graham cracker crumbs and pat in a 13 x 9-inch pan and press down.
Beat eggs on high speed until light, about 4 minutes.
Add confectioners sugar, butter and vanilla.
Beat 5 minutes and spread over crumb mixture.
Chill for about 30 minutes.
Spread drained crushed pineapple over the crumb mixture.
