Arrange sliced bananas over the pineapple and cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle chopped pecans and chopped up red cherries on top for decoration.
Cover and refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.

title: vegetable scallop
directions: Slice onion thinly and saute in small quantity butter until soft.

title: tea cakes(aunt evie's)
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and work in the flour and other dry ingredients.
Roll and cut with cookie cutter. Bake at 400° until very lightly brown.

title: country pie
directions: Mix and press into 9-inch pie plate.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine sugar, Wesson oil, eggs and hot water in mixing bowl. Beat for 4 minutes. Sift dry ingredients together. Add to mixture and beat. Add carrots and nuts; mix well. Bake in greased and floured angel food pan at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: vanilla cream pie
directions: Combine the sweetened condensed milk, water and pudding mix; mix for about 30 seconds or until the pudding is dissolved.
(Do not overmix.)
Fold in the sour cream, then fold in the whipped topping.
Pour mixture into pie crust and refrigerate for at least 4 hours, or overnight.

title: tailgate cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Watch closely. Do not overcook.

title: delicious sauerkraut and beer
directions: (Amounts to meet your desire.)
Brown spareribs.
Rinse sauerkraut in cold water and pat dry with paper towels.
Either in same skillet you browned the spareribs in or a roasting pan, put layer of sauerkraut and then layer of ribs.
Repeat, ending up with layer of sauerkraut on top.
Add beer to cover.
Simmer several hours if using skillet method or bake at 350° in covered roasting pan for 2 hours or until meat is tender.
I like to add quartered potatoes the last half hour and season with black pepper.

title: lime salad
directions: Melt the marshmallows in 7-Up.
Remove from stove and add other ingredients.
Place in refrigerator for several hours.

title: party hash browns
directions: Mix together all but the last two ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Top with corn flakes and melted margarine.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: make ahead potato casserole
directions: Place a layer of potatoes in bottom of a greased loaf pan. Combine soup with cheese, onion and seasoning.
Alternate layers of cheese and mixture of diced potatoes, ending with cheese on top. Cover with buttered crumbs.
Refrigerate until baking time. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate melt-away cake
directions: Cream brown sugar and butter.
Melt chocolate and add hot water.
Add egg yolks, beaten and vanilla.
Sift salt, cake flour and soda.
Add alternately with buttermilk or sour milk.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into 2 (8-inch) layers (pans).
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: carrot cake with buttermilk topping
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and baking powder. Beat oil and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, flour mixture, carrots and nuts.
Bake in oblong pan 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a medium bowl, combine potato flakes, Parmesan cheese, parsley flakes, paprika, onion powder, garlic salt and pepper.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat with chopped onion.
Drain.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Cook in heavy pot for 30 to 45 minutes.
Check for taste.
Add more chili powder and a dash of red pepper for a "hotter" chili.
Serves 6.

title: fresh tomato salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; stir until well combined. Cover and chill.
Makes 24 servings, 3 ounces each.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and flour until fine crumbs.
Keep 1 cup for frosting.
Add rest of ingredients to mixture.
Mix well and put into greased pan.
Sprinkle top with 1 cup of the saved crumb mixture.
Sprinkle top with miniature chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Place a layer of spareribs in bottom of heavy roaster.
Cover with layer of sliced onion; add more meat (if wanted).
Then cover with the sauce which has been mixed together thoroughly.
Put in oven at 325°.
Bake for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until tender; uncover the last half hour of baking.
Serve hot.

title: microwave fish
directions: Place fish in low microwave dish; sprinkle top with onion, paprika, parsley and pepper to taste.
Dot top with butter or oleo.
Bake on Medium-high for 10 minutes.
Rearrange fish for even baking.
Continue baking on Medium-high checking at 2 to 3 minute intervals until fish flakes with a fork.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Score the surface of each side of the slices lightly with the point of a knife.
Arrange the slices in a single layer on paper towels. Sprinkle with salt and let stand 10 minutes.
Dredge with flour. Heat the oil until very hot.
Brown sliced eggplant briefly on both sides, then drain on paper towels.
Season tomato sauce to taste with oregano, pepper and garlic powder.
Pour 1/4-inch layer of tomato sauce in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish. Cover with 1/3 eggplant slices, then 1/3 Mozzarella.
Repeat to form 3 layers.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Uncover and continue baking 10 minutes.
Place under broiler 2 minutes to brown cheese.
Serve.
Serves 8.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix together and store in airtight jar.
Use 2 tablespoons in 8 ounces water or more or less to your taste.
A real winter warmer-up!

title: strawberry-fruit punch
directions: Season to taste with 1 Kings 10:10 and Leviticus 2:13.

title: aloha loaf
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and eggs. Stir in bananas. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done. This is a moist loaf bread.
May add nuts (1/3 to 1/2 cup), if desired.

title: pea-potato stick salad
directions: Break up and thaw peas 45 minutes before time to make salad. Mix all ingredients just before serving.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Combine margarine, oil and sugars in large mixing bowl; mix well.
Add eggs and blend well.
Gradually add dry ingredients and vanilla; mix well.
Drop by small teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°
for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about
5 dozen cookies.

title: tasty dip
directions: Cook beef and onion until browned and onion is tender in skillet over medium heat.
Drain and add cubed cheese and chili. Cook, stir occasionally, until cheese is melted.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: lamb stew
directions: In a 4-6 qt pan, brown lamb cubes and onions in oil.
Cut ends off fresh green beans and add to meat.
Add potatoes, salt and seasoning.
Let steam through about 15 mins.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Season to taste.
Cover slightly and let cook down till vegetables are cooked.

title: pecan squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each. Sift flour and salt and add to mixture. Add vanilla. Fold in nuts which have been floured. Bake in oblong or square pan at 350° about 1 hour or until done.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Bake in fast oven for 10 minutes.
Turn down to moderate temperature and finish until golden brown.

title: old timey chocolate cake
directions: Mix and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook at 350° until done.

title: crystal candies
directions: Line an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan with foil, extending foil over edges of pan.
Butter the foil.
Set pan aside.

title: kara's chocolate mint cookies
directions: Cook butter, sugar and water on low heat until melted.
Add chips until partly melted.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add flour, eggs and peppermint extract.
Chill.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Crust 1 cup strawberries.
Add water and bring to boil; simmer for
minutes.
Combine	dry ingredients, add to hot liquid, and
return
to
heat.
Stir
until mixture thickens. Cool and pour over berries in baked pie shell.

title: deep south ovenly chicken
directions: Wash chicken pieces; drain and pat dry.
Combine biscuit mix, seasonings and chopped pecans.
Dip chicken into evaporated milk, then coat well with biscuit mixture.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch shallow baking dish.
Pour melted butter or margarine over chicken pieces.
Bake uncovered in a 375° (moderate) oven for 1 hour or until chicken is fork-tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Lay chicken on bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Cover with celery soup. Make stuffing mix according to box directions, except substitute cream of chicken soup and chicken broth for water. Spread stuffing over top of celery soup. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add cold water, then remaining ingredients.
Pour into an 8 x 12-inch glass Pyrex and chill.

title: pork steak deluxe
directions: Bake as many pork steaks as desired first.
Boil water; add equal amount of rice.
Let stand for five minutes and fluff.
Add tomato soup to rice and mix together.
Put on top of steaks and return to oven for 5 minutes at 350°.

title: green chili casserole
directions: Fry tortillas in oil.
Layer tortillas in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Heat tomatoes, soup, butter, onion and green chilies in saucepan. Pour mixture over tortillas, top with grated cheese.
Layer until mixture is gone.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and mix.
Add oleo and mix.
Add pineapple and mix.
Fold in bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° until brown or 30 to 40 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion and green pepper.
Drain off fat.
Spread tortilla chips in a single layer in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine hamburger with enchilada sauce and mushroom soup.
Pour meat mixture over chips.
Spread sour cream over this. Sprinkle on Cheddar cheese.
Sprinkle black olives and green onions on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with chips and sour cream.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine shortening, sugar, salt and boiling water.
Beat eggs and add to first mixture.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and add. Add flour and mix well.
Place in refrigerator to chill.
Remove dough from refrigerator and roll to 1/4-inch thickness.
Spread with butter and then with cinnamon sugar.
Roll into a long roll; cut into rolls 1-inch thick.
Put in buttered pan and mash down lightly.
Put back in refrigerator until needed.
Turn oven and set temperature to 400°.
Put rolls into cold oven and bake until done.

title: waikiki beans 'n wieners
directions: Cut pineapple into chunks, reserving 3 or 4 rings for garnish. Saute green pepper, onion, pineapple and wiener chunks in margarine.
Simmer 5 minutes; add pineapple syrup, vinegar, soy sauce, catsup and brown sugar and heat until bubbly.
Pour pork and beans into baking dish; add pineapple mixture and stir gently to blend.
Place halved rings on top of casserole and bake in moderate (350°) oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 generously.
It's delicious and economical!

title: no cook pudding cream pie
directions: Follow directions on pudding packages.
Place evenly in pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Serve.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale and freeze.
When ready to use, let thaw to a thin ice or slush, place in punch bowl and add ginger ale.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan.
Add marshmallows a little at a time; add more as they melt.
When it has all melted, add nuts. Pour over popcorn and mix well.
Then pour onto buttered tinfoil (butter your hands).
Then shape into loaves or balls.
Let set overnight.

title: sesame peas
directions: Cook peas as directed on package; drain.
Cook remaining ingredients over medium heat, stirring constantly, until golden brown; pour over peas.
Makes 4 servings.

title: margie's sugar cookies
directions: Place all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Mix until smooth. Grease and flour cookie sheet.
Drop mixture on sheet and sprinkle with sugar before baking.
Bake on middle rack.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake approximately 17 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat. Stir in vanilla, pineapple, nuts and bananas.
Spoon batter into 3 greased and floured 9 inch cake pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes until done.
Cool completely.
Spread frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake.
Put nuts on top.

title: baked potato cubes
directions: Shake potato wedges in flour mixture while the butter is melting in an oblong baking dish.
Place potatoes in the butter mixture and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough on pan.
Bake at 350° until light brown. Cook.
Mix together sugar and cream cheese.
Spread on cooled crust.
Arrange sliced fruit on crust.
Chill and serve.

title: granny's divinity
directions: Place sugar, corn syrup and water in pan over low heat.
Stir until sugar is dissolved, then cook to soft ball.
In a bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Pour 1/2 of cooked syrup mixture over egg whites and continue to beat.
Cook the other half of syrup mixture until hard ball and then add gradually to the syrup and egg white mixture.
Add vanilla.
Beat until thick enough to drop from spoon.
Add nuts and drop on wax paper.

title: russian tea
directions: Put cinnamon sticks and cloves into 1 1/2 cups water.
Let boil for several minutes.
Turn off heat.
Cover.
Let steep for 15 minutes or longer.
Strain and add all ingredients together. Then let boil for 3 minutes.
Stir.
Ready to serve.
This makes 1 1/2 gallons.
Serves about 20 people.

title: carney christmas cookies
directions: Cream softened butter and sugar together; sift salt and flour together, then add to butter and sugar.
Add nuts and vanilla. Roll into 2-inch long shape.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Roll hot cookies in rest of confectioners sugar several times. Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: hot taco bean dip
directions: Spread cream cheese
(room temperature) on a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread Hormel chili on top of cream cheese.
Spoon salsa on next (1/4 to 1/2 cup).
Sprinkle on Cheddar cheese.
Top with sliced black olives.
As an option, you can add chopped onions on top of Cheddar cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and corn meal.
Add eggs, butter, milk, lemon rind and lemon juice.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut top out of peppers and hollow-out inside pulp.
Brown hamburger and onion.
Cook rice as directed on box.
Mix hamburger with rice; add shortening, catsup, salt and pepper to taste.
Fill peppers and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese.

title: asparagus quiche
directions: Layer asparagus on bottom of pie crust.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Pour on top of asparagus.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together cheese, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in flour and flavorings. Fold in dry Dream Whip.
Bake in greased tube pan at 325° for 45 minutes, then at 300° for another 30 minutes or until done.

title: bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place milk and butter in a buttered baking casserole dish and scald in microwave.
Add beaten eggs, sugar and salt.
Next, add bread cubes and raisins.
Mix thoroughly.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes until set.
Test by inserting a paring knife.
When knife comes out clean, pudding is done.
Chill in refrigerator.
Serve topped with lemon sauce.

title: chocolate kiss cookies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients and pour in melted butter.
After all is mixed thoroughly, refrigerate for 10 minutes.
Roll in balls. Flatten out a bit and press one Hershey Kiss into each cookie. Grease cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: old fashion chess pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter; beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add cornmeal, vanilla, milk and vinegar.
Bake in an unbaked pie shell for 45 to 60 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: easy cupcakes
directions: Mix.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Makes 16 cupcakes.

title: cake dessert
directions: Make pudding.
Mix with cream cheese, then spread that over cake, then spread pineapple over that.
Spread topping over the whole thing.
Refrigerate overnight.
Nuts on top (optional).

title: bundt coffee cake
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Break dinner rolls apart and place in Bundt pan.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and pudding mix well.
Sprinkle pudding mixture over rolls.
Cut oleo into squares and place on top of rolls.
Place in cold oven and leave overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Dump and serve.

title: great cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together leaving 1 cup crushed nuts to roll ball in after it has chilled.
Roll into ball.
Wrap in foil to chill.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: hot dip
directions: Melt together in crock-pot.
Serve with chips.

title: marion's chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add water, vanilla and mayonnaise.
Beat until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 2 (8-inch) layers or 1 (13 x 9 x 2-inch) cake. Delicious with peanut butter icing.

title: raggedy robins(cookies)
directions: Boil cocoa, sugar, margarine and milk.
Place over medium heat until it comes to a boil.
Boil for one minute.
Remove from stove.
Add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Put on wax paper.
Add raisins (optional).

title: pineapple cheese pie
directions: Blend the cream cheese with the egg, 3 packages Equal and 2 teaspoons reserved pineapple juice.
Pour into crust and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: 3 bean bake
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon, onions and bell peppers, then mix remainder of ingredients and bake 1 hour or more at 375°.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Combine rice, seasoning packet from rice mix, and hot water; place in lightly greased 13x9x2-inch baking dish set aside.

title: chili skillet supper
directions: Melt fat in heavy skillet.
Add onion, green pepper and ground beef.
Brown lightly.
Add tomatoes, salt, chili powder and pepper, mixing well.
Bring to boiling.
Gradually stir in spaghetti.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer gently, about 20 minutes or until spaghetti is done.

title: many layered mexi
directions: Note:
Four ounces chopped green chilies may be layered over the beans.

title: party snack
directions: Put all ingredients in Tupperware container and toss or shake until everything is absorbed.
Shake every 15 minutes for 1 hour. Let air dry and store in Ziploc bag.

title: chicken and rice chow mein
directions: Cook and stir chicken in hot oil in large skillet over medium heat until lightly browned.
Stir chicken broth, soy sauce, cornstarch, ginger and garlic in small bowl.
Add broth mixture to skillet and bring to boil.
Mix in vegetables; reduce heat and simmer until heated through.
Stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.

title: honey applesauce oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Place walnut half on each cookie.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: cinnamon bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 9 x 5-inch pan.
In medium bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon; mix well.
Separate dough into 20 biscuits.
Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Toss in sugar mixture. Place coated pieces in greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Remove from pan and drizzle with Powdered Sugar Glaze.

title: montgomery inn boat house ribs sauce
directions: Blend together over low heat.
Spread over meat to be baked or barbecued.

title: mock shrimp cocktail
directions: Bring to boil 6 quarts water; add shrimp boil seasoning and fish.
Bring back to a boil and let cook 5 minutes.
Drain fish well; place in bowl.
Add cocktail sauce and mix lightly so fish stays in pieces about 1-inch square.
Serve on Ritz crackers. Tastes like the greatest shrimp cocktail you ever had.

title: beef and gravy
directions: Place roast, chopped onion and 2 cans of cream of mushroom soup in foil.
Seal foil and place in roasting pan.
Cook at 400° until done.

title: sinful brownies
directions: Bake brownies per the directions on the box (chewy recipe is best).
Just before removing brownies from the oven, melt caramels in microwave.
Remove brownies from oven and drizzle caramel over top.
Immediately sprinkle chocolate chips and pecans on top. Allow to cool completely before cutting brownies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and save the broth. Mix cream of chicken soup and milk together.
Melt margarine in casserole dish. Mix broth and stuffing together. Pour over margarine.
Place chicken on top of stuffing.
Pour soup and milk mixture over the chicken and stuffing.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: garlic tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes in 4 squares.
Crush up garlic cloves.
Add garlic salt to taste.
Add oregano and 1 cup of olive oil (depending on texture, 1 1/2 cup of olive oil).
Chill and serve with Italian bread.

title: rigatoni a la masters
directions: Cook rigatoni noodles, rinse in cold water and drain.
Lightly grease dish.
Cut cheese into small strips (approximately 1-inch long, 1/2-inch thick) and stuff each rigatoni noodle.
(Don't panic, it doesn't take that long.)
Place a layer of stuffed rigatoni noodles in pan, cover with sauce, sprinkle with Italian seasoning and garlic powder.
Grate a thin layer of Mozzarella cheese on top.
Repeat the process for the next layer.
Cover with foil and bake in oven at 375° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 or more servings.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos until fine.
Set aside. Cream butter, cheese and sugar. Mix pudding with milk.
Add Cool Whip.

title: speedy taco bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook ground beef and onion until beef is brown.
Drain.
Spoon into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Stir in taco seasoning mix (dry), tomato sauce and corn. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: texas hash
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in an oblong pan, covered, for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 15 minutes at 350°.

title: quick pizza casserole
directions: Cook ground beef until browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain off grease and rinse with hot water.
Spoon beef into 7 x 11 or 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Top with pizza sauce and cheese.
Combine biscuit mix, milk and eggs; beat until smooth.
Pour mixture over meat, covering evenly.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: coconut filling for cake
directions: Combine sugar and milk and cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and coconut.

title: korean hamburger
directions: Mix all ingredients; shape into patties and fry.

title: southern family swiss steak
directions: Dredge steak with flour; brown in hot oil in heavy skillet or Dutch oven.
Remove steak and set aside.

title: hot wine punch
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat either in a large pan on stove or in percolator coffee pot.
Serve warm.
Can store in coffee pot and warm as needed.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in a sheet cake pan. Layer everything in a punch bowl twice in the following order: pudding, 1/2 sheet cake, crumbled, cherry pie filling, 1/2 can pineapple, Cool Whip and nuts (optional).

title: baked beans
directions: Wash beans and let drain, no soaking necessary.
Mix together navy beans, bacon, onion, sugar, salt, soda, dry mustard, mild molasses and catsup.
Add hot water; stir.
Put in crock-pot and cook 12 to 14 hours on low, with high about 4 hours.

title: split pea soup
directions: Rinse and sort peas.
Place in large kettle with remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and let simmer for at least 3 hours. Season to taste.
Add more water from time to time, if necessary. Put soup through sieve, food mill or blender.
Reheat and serve.

title: potato and broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan lightly with margarine.
Mix potatoes, soup mix and melted margarine.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Add broccoli and cheese.
Bake an additional 20 minutes.

title: blueberry glaze
directions: Mash blueberries and add 1/2 cup water; bring to a boil. Strain juice into a cup from cooked berries.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 full cup.
In the same saucepan, combine 1/2 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in the cup of blueberry liquid.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Cook about 1 minute more.
Remove from heat, stir in lemon juice and cool.
When cool, add about 2 cups of fresh blueberries.

title: hamburger relish
directions: Grind and drain the cucumbers, onions and green pepper.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer 20 minutes & can.
Makes around 5-6 pints.
It's great.

title: chicken twists
directions: Cut chicken into strips; flour and dip into egg and bread crumbs.
Twist and deep fry until done.
Serve with favorite dipping sauce.

title: lil's salad
directions: Combine lime and lemon gelatin.
Dissolve in boiling water. Cool.
Stir in evaporated milk and lemon juice.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in cottage cheese, pineapple, nuts and celery.
Pour into 2 quart mold.
Can be served with mayonnaise topping.
Blend mayo and horseradish for topping.

title: watergate salad
directions: Pour undrained pineapple over pudding mix and stir.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cherry glazed ham
directions: Rub ham with cloves.
Place ham on cookie sheet covered with foil.
Pour powdered jello over top of ham.
Pour on honey.
Place another piece of foil over top of ham.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Open foil; bake 15 minutes more.

title: mom's raisin creams
directions: Simmer raisins covered with 1 1/2 to 2 cups water.
Save the liquid.
Dissolve the baking soda in 1 cup of warm liquid from raisins.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and blend well. Add liquid alternately with flour.
Fold in raisins.
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes in a large jelly roll pan.
Drizzle with thin powdered sugar icing while warm.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix flour, milk, mayonnaise and salt.
Pour into greased muffin cups.
Bake at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: angel's cookies
directions: Mix flour and baking soda together.
Combine margarine, sugar, vanilla and pudding mix in a large bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Mix until smooth.
Stir in chips, nuts and candy.
Batter will be stiff. Bake in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheets.

title: fresh peach tapioca
directions: Mix ingredients in 4-quart saucepan.
Let stand for 5 minutes. Cook as pudding until thickened.
Pour into serving dishes. Cool.
Top with ice cream or Cool Whip, if desired.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: carolyn's artichoke spread
directions: Drain and chop artichoke hearts.
Mix garlic, mayo and artichokes.
Spread in baking dish; bake at 350° for about 40 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: cheesy oven fries
directions: Wash potatoes well and cut each into 8 wedges; set aside. Combine Parmesan cheese and next 4 ingredients, stirring well. Dip potato wedges in melted butter; arrange in a single layer in a lightly greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Sprinkle cheese mixture over potatoes.
Bake at 375°, uncovered, for 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and browned.

title: caramel corn(recipe from high school friend, karen randolf, 1968)
directions: Note:
One-half cup popcorn equals 1 1/2 quarts popped corn.

title: date balls
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients in frying pan and cook over low heat until eggs are cooked.
Add dates.
Cook until soft.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and Rice Krispies.
Grease hands well and form into balls.
Roll in coconut.

title: beef hot pockets for 4
directions: Brown beef, onion, celery and bell pepper until meat is cooked thoroughly. Drain off all but 2 tablespoons fat. Add rest of ingredients and all spices. Mix well. Make a small amount of flour and water to make paste for thickening. Mix into meat mixture. Pour in puff sheet and put diced tomatoes on top. Fold sheet. Turn upside down (closed on top and sides) on foil lined pan. Bake at 350° until done. The slower it bakes, the better the taste. Slice and eat as main course.

title: shrimp and black olives over spaghetti(can be used as a first course or a main course)
directions: Combine wine, stock and shrimp shells.
Boil, uncovered, until reduced to 1 cup.
Strain; cover and chill until needed.
Heat about 3 to 6 tablespoons olive oil in saute pan.
Cook onions, parsley and herbs until onions are a pale gold.
Add garlic and saute briefly.
Remove from heat and set aside.

title: chicken broth
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry; put in soup kettle and cover with 2 quarts of water.
Bring to a boil.
Skim foam and lower heat. Cover kettle and simmer for 2 hours.
Add onions, celery, carrots and bay leaf.
Simmer an additional hour, skimming foam as necessary.
Remove from heat and cool.

title: mocha bavarian
directions: Dissolve instant coffee in water. Mix sugar, cocoa, gelatin and milk, heat until gelatin dissolves. Remove from heat and add coffee and vanilla. Cool until partially set, fold in Cool Whip. Pour into dessert cups and chill.

title: ginger raz freeze
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into blender; blend until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Yield: 2 cups.

title: mexican red rice
directions: Heat the oil in a deep saucepan and saute the rice until golden.
Add chicken stock, garlic, onion and tomato sauce.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil; lower the heat.
Cover and cook until almost all liquid has been absorbed.
Uncover; fold in the peas and carrots carefully.
Cover again and cook until all liquid has been absorbed.
Can serve garnished with avocado slices and sliced ripe bananas.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottoms only of loaf pans.
Mix shortening and sugar in large mixing bowl. Add eggs, water and pumpkin.
Stir in flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix in chopped nuts and raisins, pour in loaf pans.
Bake approximately1 hour and 10 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center of loaf comes out clean.
Remove from pan and let completely cool before slicing.

title: whipping cream cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream butter and sugar until creamy; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour alternately with the whipping cream.
Add extract and mix well.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 1 hour and 20 to 30 minutes or until cake is done.
When done, cool on rack about 10 minutes before inverting pan.
Cake freezes well, tightly wrapped.

title: spinach rice salad
directions: Precook rice; cool and marinate in Italian dressing overnight in refrigerator.
Drain excess dressing before using.

title: zucchini italiano
directions: Brown sausage, onion, mango and garlic in Dutch oven.
Add next 9 ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes or until noodles are done.
Top with cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.

title: almond tea
directions: Boil water.
Add tea bags and Kool-Aid.
Steep for 3 minutes. Add almond flavoring and sweeten to taste.

title: grape leaf rolls
directions: Wash grape leaves; wash and drain rice.
Mix rice, lamb, spices and juice of one lemon.
Place about 1 tablespoon meat mixture on veined side of each grape leaf.
Spread across in a line; turn in the side ends and roll up completely.
Line bottom of pan with 3 or 4 grape leaves on pan rack.
Place evenly in rows in layers, crisscrossing each layer.
Use an inverted plate to hold down rolls.
Add water to cover.
Bring to boil; reduce to low heat and cook 20 to 30 minutes.
Add juice of 1 lemon five minutes before removing from heat.
Can be served with yogurt or sour cream.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill for 2 hours or more, roll 1/4-inch thick.
Bake at 350°
for 7 to 8 minutes until golden, not brown.

title: onion bacon dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill.
Serve with chips or fresh vegetables.
Serves 8.

title: guacamole tomato salad
directions: Core tomatoes; scoop out center.
Sprinkle insides with 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Turn over to drain.
Chill.
Chop tomato centers fine.
Add onion, chilies, lemon juice and salt.
Mix. Just before serving, mash avocado and blend into tomato mixture.
Fill tomato cups.
Top with crumbled bacon.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into sprayed baking dish.
Sprinkle 1 package Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix together well.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
In separate bowl mix eggs, sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice together slowly.
Add dry ingredients.
Grease and flour a cookie sheet; pour mix on cookie sheet and tap on table until even.
Top with pecan pieces.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Let cool for 15 minutes.
Take dish towel, sprinkle powdered sugar on towel, and roll up.
Mix icing, unroll and put icing on roll.
Roll up.
Ready to eat.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix mayo and sugar.
Mix all ingredients.

title: golden salad
directions: Heat 1 cup of water and dissolve both packages of gelatin in it.
Blend softened cream cheese with salad dressing until smooth and add the gelatin mixture.
Add remaining cold water.
Let stand until syrupy.
Add pineapple with its juice.
Pour into mold and refrigerate.

title: peach pie(serves 6)
directions: Combine crushed peaches, water, sugar and cornstarch.
Bring to a boil and cook until clear and thick.
Add butter.
Spoon this mixture over the sliced peaches which have been put in the pie shell, covering all peaches.
Chill well.
Serve with whipped cream.
